INSERT INTO `services` VALUES (27,'Bank Street Writers and another','Rod Riesco','Bank Street Unitarian Chapel','Crown Street','','Bolton','BL1 2RU','01204 692110','bswscribe@gmail.com','https://sites.google.com/site/bankstreetwriters/','<p>We are a group of writers who meet once a month in the centre of Bolton, Lancashire (UK) for readings, discussions, workshops and visits. Our regular meeting place is the historic Bank Street Unitarian Chapel in Crown Street, just off Deansgate. Members&#39; interests include poetry, fiction, scriptwriting, factual writing - in fact, almost everything you can do with the written word! Newcomers are always welcome at our informal meetings. There&#39;s no commitment to join - but if you do, you&#39;ll also receive our regular newsletter and be able to have a say in how we develop our range of activities.</p>\r\n','','','',1,150,1,1,53.580283,-2.427096,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2015-03-04 15:27:29',NULL,0,'bank-street-writers'),(28,'Blackrod Library book groups',NULL,'Church Street','Blackrod',NULL,'Bolton','BL6 5EQ','01204 332380','blackrod.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/BlackrodLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity; you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels.  We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader.  Monday book group: This group meets on the first Monday of the month from 2.00pm until 3.00pm. Thursday book group: This group meets on the third Thursday of the month from 6.00pm to 7.00pm.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.593887,-2.584373,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'blackrod-library-book-groups'),(29,'Bolton U3A','Ann Waring','St Andrew and St George URC','St George Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2BS','01204 492343','ann.waring@hotmail.co.uk','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=495&page=1','U3A stands for the University of the Third Age, which is a self-help organisation for people no longer in full time employment providing educational, creative and leisure opportunities in a friendly environment. Interest Groups meet at various venues in the town centre in these subjects; archaeology, art appreciation, basic Italian, biology, crafts (cards), creative writing, European studies, film forum, gardening, French, history, literature, local history, mah-jong, play reading, philosophy, poetry for pleasure, recorded music, scrabble, Saturday ramblers, singing for pleasure, solo whist - cards, walkabout, transactional analysis, world’s religions, women’s history. General meeting are held on the 4th Friday of the month, 2pm – 4pm. Annual Subscription; £18.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.581602,-2.432203,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-u3a'),(30,'Bromley Cross Library Book Group',NULL,'The Crescent','Bromley Cross',NULL,'Bolton','BL7 9JU','01204 332354','bromley.cross.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/BromleyCrossLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity: you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels. We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader. This group meets on the first Thursday of the month from 11.00am to 12.00 noon. Contact the library for details.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.616931,-2.418892,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bromley-cross-library-book-group'),(31,'Central Library book groups',NULL,'Central Library','Le Mans Crescent',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1SE','01204 333173','central.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/CentralLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity: you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels. We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader. Thursday book group: This group meets on the third Thursday of the month from 6.15pm until 7.15pm, in the central library\'s fiction area. Graphic Novel book group: The Central Library has its own graphic novel group. We\'ve got a pretty good collection of graphic novels, and we\'re working to make it even better. The group meets every four weeks on Saturday from 3.30pm - 4.30pm.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.577385,-2.431294,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'central-library-book-groups'),(32,'Enjoy Learning Bolton','Tom Smith',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bolton',NULL,'01204 811163','tomsmith.belmont@talk21.com','http://www.enjoy-learning.org.uk/','Enjoy Learning is a not for profit organisation that provides courses and events without examinations. Information is on our website. This is being updated over the next few weeks to include our 2012/13 programme and venue changes. We offer courses to anyone over the age of 18 but in reality the majority of people who attend are over 50 and around 60% are 60 and over. The courses and classes recruit well and we are growing year on year (we started in 2006) - we have had over 1000 enrolments this year. Most of our classes are languages, art and craft, history based, with a little music and creative writing included as well. We respond to demands and this determines our programme offer . This year however we have commissioned a report on what we can offer to stroke victims and are running a one day event in Bolton Library around older people and mobile digital devices as part of adult learners week (May 2012). We offer our courses in the north Bolton area at Delph Hill Community Centre Doffcocker, Horwich Resource Centre, St. John\'s Breightmet and Theatre Church. Fees vary.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.584441,-2.428619,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'enjoy-learning-bolton'),(33,'Harwood Library book groups',NULL,'Gate Fold',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL2 3HN','01204 332340','harwood.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/Harwoodlibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity; you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels.  We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader. Tuesday book group: This group meet on the second Tuesday of the month between 11am and 1pm. Thursday book group: This group meet on the second Thursday of the month between 6.15 and 7.15pm.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.600725,-2.389849,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'harwood-library-book-groups'),(34,'High Street Library book group',NULL,'High Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 6SZ','01204 332358','high.street.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/HighStreetLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity; you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels.  We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader. This group meets on the third Tuesday of the month from 2.30pm until 3.30pm.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.561233,-2.367136,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'high-street-library-book-group'),(35,'Library Link',NULL,'Central Library','Le Mans Crescent',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1SE','01204 338755','libraries@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/Specialneedsfacilities.aspx','Bolton libraries provide a free delivery service to Bolton residents who are unable to visit libraries and do not have friends or relatives who are able to collect books for them. Staff and volunteers deliver books to your home at the same time every two weeks.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.577385,-2.431294,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'library-link'),(36,'Westhoughton Library book group',NULL,'Library Street','Westhoughton',NULL,'Bolton','BL5 3AT','01942 634640','westhoughton.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/WesthoughtonLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity; you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels.  We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader. This group meets fortnightly on Tuesdays from 1.30pm until 3.30pm.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.549088,-2.520647,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'westhoughton-library-book-group'),(37,'Tyldesley Library',NULL,'Stanley Street','Tyldesley',NULL,'Wigan','M29 8AH','01942 404738','tyldesley.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/tyldesley-library.htm','Tuesdays - Creative Writers 10.30am -12.30pm: Creative writing group, share and discuss work, refreshments included. Bookchat (every 6 weeks) – adult reading group every 6 weeks 2.00pm-3.00pm (ring library for dates ). Thursdays - Evening Reading Group: (every 6 weeks) 6.30pm-8.00pm Discuss a selection of books, every 6 weeks, refreshments included.',NULL,'wlct','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.523419,-2.491547,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'tyldesley-library'),(38,'Wigan Library','Wigan Library','Rita Musa','Wigan Life Centre','The Weind','Wigan','WN1 1NH','01942 404126','wigan.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/wigan-library.htm','English Conversation Wednesdays 4.30pm - 6.00pm and Bookchat for Adults - 1st Wednesday every month 10.30am - 11.30am. Fridays - BBC First Click IT Course 10 - 11.30am. Fridays - Craft Chat 2.30pm - 3.30pm. Saturdays - Knitted Bliss 10.30am - 11.30am.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.545508,-2.631163,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-library'),(39,'Shevington Library','Bill Gaskell','Gathurst Lane','Shevington',NULL,'Wigan','WN6 8HA','01257 252618','shevington.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/shevington-library.htm','Tuesdays - Bookchat – adult reading group (last Tuesday in month 2-3pm). 2nd and 4th Tuesday in mon - Councillor 5.45-6.45pm. Wednesdays - One Stop Shop - Police, councillor, Resident and Tenants Association 1.30-3.30pm.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.566516,-2.695558,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'shevington-library'),(40,'Salford U3A/ Salford Life Long Learning','Carole Bowler','Eccles Gateway','28 Barton Lane','Eccles','Salford','M30 0TU','0161 790 2372/0','carole@bowler.plus.com','http://www.salfordu3alll.colsal.org.uk/','U3A\' stands for The University of the Third Age. The \'Third Age\' is a time of creativity and fulfilment for older people. The \'Third Age\' refers to the periods of time after the First Age of childhood dependence and the Second Age of full time employment and parental responsibility. Salford Life Long Learning is a group of approximately 250 people within the U3A who are seeking to swell their numbers so why not join us. They have a range of groups which do different activities including: memories of Salford, discussion groups, bird watching, drama, gardening, family history, french, Mahjongg, music, poetry (Fri afternoon-please call), opera ballet on video, painting, science and maths, scrabble, walks, Eccles local history, A toast to Salford, Spanish, summer schools, no vices bridge, book club (first Wednesday of the month @ Walkden Gateway), quilting, theatre group and keep fit. Monthly general meetings take place at the Eccles Gateway.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482579,-2.338968,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-u3a-salford-life-long-learning'),(41,'Cadishead Library Book Group',NULL,'126 Liverpool Road','Cadishead',NULL,'Salford','M44 5AN','0161 7753457','cadishead.library@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/cadisheadlibrary.htm','The reading group at Cadishead Library meets on the second Monday of the month from 1.45pm to 2.45pm. For more information contact Sue Thomas. Meetings usually last about an hour with the emphasis being on having fun and getting to read things that you might not normally read. Groups usually agree to read one book per month and then come together to talk about what they thought about it. It is not vital that you have read the current book in order to join in but if you do want to, copies of all books are available to borrow at your nearest library.',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.428051,-2.435953,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'cadishead-library-book-group'),(42,'Eccles Library Book Group','Sue Thomas','28 Barton Lane','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0TU','0161 9096528','eccles.library@scll.co.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/eccleslibrary.htm','There are now two reading groups at Eccles Library. The morning group meets on the third Wednesday of the month from 11.00am to 12.00 noon. The evening group meets on the first Thursday of the month from 7.00pm to 8.00pm. Meetings usually last about an hour with the emphasis being on having fun and getting to read things that you might not normally read. Groups usually agree to read one book per month and then come together to talk about what they thought about it. It is not vital that you have read the current book in order to join in but if you do want to, copies of all books are available to borrow at your nearest library.',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.482602,-2.339239,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'eccles-library-book-group'),(43,'Height Library Reading group','Janet Lyons (Supervisor)','Height Library','King Street','Height','Salford','M6 7GY','0161 736 1907','height.library@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/reading-groups.htm','There are two reading groups at the Height Library one meets on the fourth Monday of the month from 5.30pm to 6.30pm and another on the fourth Thursday of the month from 10.11am-11.00am. Meetings usually last about an hour with the emphasis being on having fun and getting to read things that you might not normally read. Groups usually agree to read one book per month and then come together to talk about what they thought about it. It is not vital that you have read the current book in order to join in but if you do want to, copies of all books are available to borrow at your nearest library.',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.499664,-2.308909,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'height-library-reading-group'),(44,'Irlam Library Book Group',NULL,'Hurst Fold','Liverpool Road','Irlam','Salford','M44 6FD','0161 7753566','irlam.library@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/irlamlibrary.htm','The reading group at Irlam Library meets on the second Monday of the month from 1.45pm to 2.45pm. Meetings usually last about an hour with the emphasis being on having fun and getting to read things that you might not normally read. Groups usually agree to read one book per month and then come together to talk about what they thought about it. It is not vital that you have read the current book in order to join in but if you do want to, copies of all books are available to borrow at your nearest library.',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.450242,-2.415671,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'irlam-library-book-group'),(45,'Winton Library Reading Group',NULL,'Old Parish Lane','Winton',NULL,'Salford','M30 8BY','0161 9212180','winton.library@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/wintonlibrary.htm','The reading group at Winton Library meets on the second Thursday of the month from 10.30am to 11.30am. Meetings usually last about an hour with the emphasis being on having fun and getting to read things that you might not normally read. Groups usually agree to read one book per month and then come together to talk about what they thought about it. It is not vital that you have read the current book in order to join in but if you do want to, copies of all books are available to borrow at your nearest library.',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.489643,-2.368549,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'winton-library-reading-group'),(46,'Worsley Village Reading Group','Chris Carson  or  Phil Carey','Worsley Village Library','Worsley Road','Worsley','Salford','M28 2BP','0161 9096518','WorsleyVillage.library@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/libraries/locations/worsley-village-library','There are two groups at Worsley Village Library. The first group meets on the first Tuesday of every month from 2.00pm to 3.00pm and the second group meet on the second Tuesday of every month from 2.00pm to 3.00pm. Meetings usually last about an hour with the emphasis being on having fun and getting to read things that you might not normally read. Groups usually agree to read one book per month and then come together to talk about what they thought about it. It is not vital that you have read the current book in order to join in but if you do want to, copies of all books are available to borrow at your nearest library.',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,NULL,NULL,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'worsley-village-reading-group'),(47,'Eccles Library Writers Group',NULL,'Eccles Gateway','28 Barton Lane','Eccles','Salford','M30 0TU',NULL,'EcclesLibraryWriters@gmail.com','http://www.salford.gov.uk/ecclescr.htm','Our self-supporting group meets at Eccles Gateway to write, read and discuss our work. but always welcome enquiries.Opening times alternate Fridays from 10.00am to 12.00pm. Self referral; Contact via email; From 18 years; Both males and females.',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.482579,-2.338968,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'eccles-library-writers-group'),(48,'Boothstown Community Centre','Marjorie or Susan','Standfield Drive','Boothstown','Worsley','Salford','M28 1NB','0161 7999425','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/boothstowncc.htm','Activities and groups include Cafe 55 (meals start at 11.30am); Older persons meeting (first Monday of the month); Grow your Own (6 weeks from 13th Feb, Mon 2-4pm); Healthy walking group (Mon 2-4pm); Men\'s Health Group (Mon 3-4.30pm); Writers Group (Mon 7-9pm); Curling; Healthy Hips and Hearts (Tues 2-3.30pm); Weight Watchers (Tues 5-6.30pm, 6.30-8pm); Zumba (Tues 8-9pm); Lunch Club (Wed 12.30-2pm); Over 60s Club (Wed 1.30-3.30pm); Local Histories (Third Wednesday of month 7.15-9.15pm); Ladies Group (last Wednesday of month 7.30-10pm); Art group (Thurs 11.45-1.45pm); Tai Chi (Thurs 2-3pm); Yoga (Thurs 7.15-9.15pm); Transport meeting; Reading Group (Fri 2-3pm).',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.504413,-2.417325,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'boothstown-community-centre'),(49,'Ordsall Community Cafe Project','','172 Tatton Street','Ordsall','','Salford','M5 3PS','0161 8726011','ordsall.cafe@hotmail.co.uk','http://www.ordsallcommunitycafe.co.uk/','<p>The project provides a friendly, inviting cafeteria and a variety of much-needed services and facilities for the local community, and those further away who find them beneficial. Our services and relaxed atmosphere are enjoyed by men and woman, babies and teenagers, old and young from all races and backgrounds - come and join them! Has classes for basic computer skills, bingo, cafeteria, community teas, gentle exercise classes, guitar lessons, hair salon, IT suite and internet access, skills and work, writers group, volunteering.</p>\r\n','','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Ordsall-Cafe-Project-Ltd/6541793001',1,150,1,1,53.475492,-2.275304,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-06-19 11:12:30',NULL,NULL,'ordsall-community-café-project'),(50,'Classic Fiction Reading Group',NULL,'Bramhall Library','Bramhall Lane South','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 2DU','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/bramhalllibrary/','Enjoy reading? Read a book that you just had to talk about? Love talking about books? Whatever your reading taste we have a reading group for you. Our groups are informal and relaxed. Discover new authors and titles, widen your reading choice and meet other readers in a friendly, relaxed and informal setting. Suitable for all ages. Thu, 17 Nov 2011 to Thu, 20 Dec 2012, 18:45 - 19:45. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.359998,-2.164852,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'classic-fiction-reading-group'),(51,'Creative Writing for Pleasure',NULL,'Cheadle Library','Ashfield Road','Cheadle','Stockport','SK8 1BB','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/chelibinfo/','Writing for Pleasure (WFP) is for people who want to write, who derive pleasure from words and ideas, and who love reading. WFP is a writers\' workshop where you can meet other writers, tackle writing activities with others, and share feedback. Everyone is welcome to attend. Suitable for all ages. Thu, 03 Nov 2011 to Thu, 06 Dec 2012, 18:00 - 19:45. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.393393,-2.212908,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'creative-writing-for-pleasure'),(52,'Heald Green Library Reading Group',NULL,'Heald Green Library','Finney Lane','Heald Green','Stockport','SK8 3JB','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/heglibinfo/','Enjoy reading? Read a book that you just had to talk about? Love talking about books? Whatever your reading taste we have a reading group for you. Our groups are informal and relaxed. Discover new authors and titles, widen your reading choice and meet other readers in a friendly, relaxed and informal setting. Suitable for all ages. Tue, 01 Nov 2011 to Tue, 04 Dec 2012, 14:30 - 15:30. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.370202,-2.228756,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'heald-green-library-reading-group'),(53,'Heatons Library Reading Group',NULL,'Heaton Library','Thornfield Road','Heaton Moor','Stockport','SK4 3LD','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/hetlibinfo/','Enjoy reading? Read a book that you just had to talk about? Love talking about books? Whatever your reading taste we have a reading group for you. Our groups are informal and relaxed. Discover new authors and titles, widen your reading choice and meet other readers in a friendly, relaxed and informal setting. Suitable for all ages. Wed, 16 Nov 2011 to Wed, 19 Dec 2012, 18:30 - 19:30. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.416687,-2.19071,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'heatons-library-reading-group'),(54,'Marple Bookworms','Sharon Goddard','Marple Library','Memorial Park','Marple','Stockport','SK6 6BA','0161 217 6009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/libraryonline/libraryevents/marplebookworms','Marple Bookworms is a small group of adult readers who meet on the last Monday of every month at Marple Library. Our books are provided for us free of charge from Stockport\'s excellent library service. Our meetings are informal and relaxed, allowing everybody the opportunity to contribute. Discussion is always interesting and often lively! We often share a poem as well which is related to the book we have read; we also share \"other\" reads of the month. Anyone is welcome to join. This group meets every month, on the Last Monday, between Mon, 30 Jan, 2012 - Mon, 26 Nov, 2012 at 6.45pm - 7.45pm.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.396624,-2.061927,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'marple-bookworms'),(55,'Marple Writers Workshop','Sylvia Christie','Marple Library','Memorial Park','Marple','Stockport','SK6 6BA','0161 4271665','sylviachristie@googlemail.com','http://www.marple-uk.com/community/writers.htm','Currently there are about twenty members whose ages range from seventeen to seventy plus. Meetings are friendly and informal and new members are always welcome. We sometimes invite visiting speakers - these have included poets, novelists, playwrights and a publisher. Most evenings though we organise our own creative writing activities. We do not feel the need to have a formal committee so individuals and small teams of members volunteer to organise events and to run workshops which inspire the group to write at home as well as in the sessions themselves. No one is ever required to share their writing unless they are happy to do so. Abilities range from interested beginners to winners of national short story and poetry competitions. Current membership fees are £5 twice a year at Easter and in September and new attendees are invited to spend several free evenings with us before they join officially. We meet on Tuesday evenings at 7.15 for a 7.30 start in the upstairs room of Marple library.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.396624,-2.061927,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'marple-writers-workshop'),(56,'Non-Fiction Reading Group',NULL,'Greatermoor Library','Gladstone Street','Greatmoor','Stockport','SK2 7QF','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/grelibinfo/','Enjoy reading? Read a book that you just had to talk about? Love talking about books? Whatever your reading taste we have a reading group for you. Our groups are informal and relaxed. Discover new authors and titles, widen your reading choice and meet other readers in a friendly, relaxed and informal setting. Suitable for all ages. Sat, 19 Nov 2011 to Sat, 15 Dec 2012, 14:15 - 15:15. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.388433,-2.133072,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'non-fiction-reading-group'),(57,'The Mobile and Home Library Service',NULL,'Pheonix House','Bird Hall Lane','Cheadle Heath','Stockport','SK3 0RA','0161 4745600','homelibraryservice@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/morelibraryservices/mhls/','The aim of the Mobile and Home Library Service is to provide a service to members of the Stockport community who are unable to access their local library due to disability, ill health, mobility problems or caring commitments. Community Library Bus - provides a full range of library services on the premises of residential homes and sheltered accommodation. The Home Library Service - this free service is available for people living in the Stockport area who find it difficult to visit a library.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.391528,-2.184703,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-mobile-and-home-library-service'),(58,'Asian Elders Resource Centre',NULL,'61 Northfield Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 5JH','01204 651123','eamil@aercbolton.co.uk','http://www.aercbolton.co.uk/page/737-welcome.aspx','We provide specialised day care and day centre provision for local older Asian people. We provide a wide range of activities, and entertainment, along with useful information. Daily activities and services include: ESOL English classes, ICT with basic English, cookery class, art & craft, massage & holistic therapy, yoga, chair based exercise, swimming sessions, local & abroad trips, advocacy work, home visits (additional support), interpretation and translation service, transport facility, vegetarian and halal meal provision, chiropody service, health checks, information sharing sessions with various topics, eye tests arranged through AERC, indoor games and entertainment. The Service Users Forum, and Asian Carers Forum are our two main groups, developed to empower and support our service users and their carers. To become a member it is £10 per year.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.571009,-2.447911,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'asian-elders-resource-centre'),(59,'Bolton Art Circle','George Hull','Highfield Hall','Highfield Road','Farnworth','Bolton','BL4 0AW','01204 841172','geoleshull@talktalk.net','http://www.boltonartcircle.org/','We provide facilities for artists to practice, exhibit, promote and sell their works. We arrange demonstrations and workshops, as well as informal, and formal exhibitions. We run Art Fairs at the Last Drop Village Hotel and outdoor exhibitions in Bolton Town Centre precincts. A library of books and videos are available for members. We also provide a library of books and videos for the use of our members. Meet Monday, Wednesday 2 - 4pm and Thursday 7 - 9pm for 50 weeks of the year.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.546753,-2.421173,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-art-circle'),(60,'Bolton Floral Art Club',NULL,'Festival Hall','Bolton Town Hall',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1RU','01204 882301','bolton@flowersnorthwest.net','http://www.flowersnorthwest.net/club/Bolton-Floral-Art-Group','We have demonstrators who design approx six arrangements which are raffled at the end of the evening. Tea and coffee is available afterwards. We have various stalls which change as the seasons progress. Each year we organise trips to gardens and the NAFAS National Show for our members. We are always pleased to welcome new members you will find us a friendly and helpful club. Meet on a Wednesday at 7:30pm in the Festival Hall, Bolton Town Hall. Cost: Membership is £27.00 per annum or visitors at £5.00.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.578098,-2.430875,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-floral-art-club'),(61,'Bolton Hobby Craft Knitting Club','Fiona Kernohan','Hobbycraft Bolton','Bolton Gate Retail Park','','Bolton','BL1 2SL','07776 141259','fiona.kernohan@hobbycraft.co.uk','http://www.hobbycraft.co.uk/bolton','<p>If you fancy meeting up and meeting new friends whilst knitting - learning the skills and showing others how to knit then pop along to the informal group that meets every Friday in the HobbyCraft Bolton store. Everyone will be made welcome. Every Friday 2pm. Cost: Free.</p>\r\n','','','',1,150,1,1,53.586063,-2.424932,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-06-06 10:30:30',NULL,NULL,'bolton-hobby-craft-knitting-club'),(62,'Bolton U3A','Ann Waring','St Andrew and St George URC','St George Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2BS','01204 492343','ann.waring@hotmail.co.uk','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=495&page=1','U3A stands for the University of the Third Age, which is a self-help organisation for people no longer in full time employment providing educational, creative and leisure opportunities in a friendly environment. Interest Groups meet at various venues in the town centre in these subjects; archaeology, art appreciation, basic Italian, biology, crafts (cards), creative writing, European studies, film forum, gardening, French, history, literature, local history, mah-jong, play reading, philosophy, poetry for pleasure, recorded music, scrabble, Saturday ramblers, singing for pleasure, solo whist - cards, walkabout, transactional analysis, world’s religions, women’s history. General meeting are held on the 4th Friday of the month, 2pm – 4pm. Annual Subscription; £18.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.581602,-2.432203,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-u3a'),(63,'Horwich Art Society','Christine Murray','Holy Trinity Parish Hall','Church Street','Horwich','Bolton','BL6 6AA','01204 669645','christine.murray520@ntlworld.com','http://www.homepage.ntlworld.com/maddogmcq/myart/has/main.htm','The Society contains a mixture of characters, all different, with varied levels of skills. The common bond is a keen interest and enthusiasm for the many aspects of art -the only criteria to join the society. We are a very friendly group so why not come and have a chat and a \'cuppa\'. Your first visit is free and you will be made very welcome. We hope to see you soon. Every Friday 7pm until 9 pm. Annual cost: £20. Weekly admission members - £1.50.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.599029,-2.539706,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'horwich-art-society'),(64,'Horwich Resource Centre',NULL,'Beaumont Road','Horwich',NULL,'Bolton','BL6 7BG','01204 668157','horwich.hrc@onebillnet.co.uk','http://www.allcommunity.co.uk/horwichresource/','What\'s on: St John Ambulance – Luncheon Clubs – Tea Dance - Keep Fit – Looney Tunes – Childminders – Craft Clubs - Yoga – Pilates – Martial Arts – Line Dancing – Art Classes - Upholstery Classes – Horwich Widows – R.S.P.C.A. - Morris Dancing – Kidz2gether – B.A.N.D.- Embroiderers’ Guild – plus much more. For more details see website.',NULL,'HorwichResource','',1,150,1,1,53.600597,-2.545078,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'horwich-resource-centre'),(65,'Pensioners Link','Anne Deacon','Wigan & Leigh Pensioners Link','Allan Taylor House','27 Charles Street','Leigh','WN7 1DB','01942 261753','anne_counsellor@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.pensionerslink.org.uk','Pensioner Link works with and for the benefit of the over 50’s throughout the borough of Wigan. It currently provides a range of services which support older people and carers of all ages by providing information, advice and signposting on a wide number of issues and works very closely with the Carers Helpline. It hosts Wigan Independent Advice Centre one morning/week for benefits advice, and the Health Trainers use our centre for consultations. We also offer a one-to-one counselling service provided by fully qualified counsellors. Very importantly, Pensioners Link provides a wide range of social activities, which are very well attended by older people and carers. Activities include arts and crafts, exercise and relaxation, holistic therapies, good food club, coffee mornings, tai chi, discussion group, Spanish and IT.',NULL,'penlinkhouse','https://www.facebook.com/leigh.pensionerslink',1,150,1,1,53.497205,-2.513966,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pensioners-link'),(66,'Art to Art','Barbara Nettleton','Sunshine Community','Vauxhall Road','Scholes','Wigan','WN1 3SN','01942 515519 or','bn.arttoart@gmail.com','http://www.arttoartwigan.co.uk/','Activities include: Drawing classes, water colour classes, portrait and open life classes and acrylic and other medium classes. Prices vary from £3.50 to £6 for each class. This building holds other events such as yoga and services such as health trainers for health and diet advice and belly dancing, reading group, jazz octet, friendship club, choir and manga classes for young people. For further information please go to the website provided.',NULL,'ArttoArtWigan','',1,150,1,1,NULL,NULL,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'art-to-art'),(67,'Haigh Hall and Country Park',NULL,'Copperas Lane','Wigan',NULL,'Wigan','WN2 1PE','01942 832895',NULL,'http://www.wlct.org/haigh/haigh-highlights-and-amenities.htm','The Stables is a vibrant Arts and Craft Centre. Craft fayres are held regularly. Other Crafts include stencilling, pottery, embroidery and flower arranging.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.575601,-2.600148,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'haigh-hall-and-country-park'),(68,'Leigh Library',NULL,'Turnpike Centre','Civic Square','Market Street','Leigh','WN7 1EB','01942 404404','Leigh.Library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/leigh-library.htm','Mondays - Writers Group (fortnightly) 5:30pm – 6:45pm. A friendly and supportive creative writing session. Everyone Welcome. Leigh Family History Society 1:30pm – 3:30pm (Local History Desk). Tuesdays - My Guide 10am – 12 noon (In The Library) Internet course for beginners. Get into Reading 11:30pm - 1pm (In The Library), enjoy stories and poems read aloud, Bookchat 7:15pm - 9pm, Adult reading group runs on the 1st Tuesday in the month. Wednesdays - Carpe Diem Sewing Group 10am – 12noon (In The Derby Room). Thursdays - \'Chatterbooks\' - 11am – 12 noon 1st Thursday of the month. (In The Library), Your Bard (Shakespeare Reading Group) 5:30pm – 7pm. 4th Thursday of the month. (In The Derby Room), Poetry Reading Group 7:15pm – 8:30pm 2nd Thursday in month. Fridays - My Guide 10am – 12 noon Internet course for beginners. (In The Library). Saturdays - The Open Book Club 11am - 12noon (monthly). Reading group for adults. Read and discuss our featured book voted for by you. Craft Circle: Whatever your interests - card making, knitting, embroidery or any other crafts - the Craft Circle is the place to meet like-minded people and share tip and ideas. It\'s free and there\'s no need to book, just turn up on the day. We meet on the 1st Friday of the month 1-3pm. For further information telephone Louise on +44 (0)1942 404469.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.496922,-2.518982,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'leigh-library'),(69,'Atherton Library','Marlene Chadwick or Sandra Lord','York Street','Artherton',NULL,'Wigan','M46 9JH','01942 404817','atherton.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/atherton-library.htm','Mondays - Evening Reading Group - 6.30 – 7.30pm every six weeks approx. Refreshments provided. Informal discussion of books read from previous meeting. Knit ‘N’ Natter - 2.00 – 4.00pm. Knitting, crochet and cross stitch. Tuesdays - Book chat - 2.00 – 3.00pm every six weeks approx. Lively chat about new books and bestsellers. Refreshments provided.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.526019,-2.487931,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'atherton-library'),(70,'Platt Bridge Library','Shelia O\'Brien','Platt Field Community First','Rivington Avenue','Platt Field','Wigan','WN2 5NG','01942 487997','plattbridge.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/platt-bridge-community-library.htm','Wednesdays - 1st Wednesday in the month - Bookchat Group, Adult Reading Group 9.30 - 10.30am, 3rd Wednesday in the month - Knitting, Sewing and Crochet 12.30 - 1.30pm',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.52228,-2.595925,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'platt-bridge-library'),(71,'Tyldesley Library',NULL,'Stanley Street','Tyldesley',NULL,'Wigan','M29 8AH','01942 404738','tyldesley.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/tyldesley-library.htm','Tuesdays - Creative Writers 10.30am -12.30pm: Creative writing group, share and discuss work, refreshments included. Bookchat (every 6 weeks) – adult reading group every 6 weeks 2.00pm-3.00pm (ring library for dates ). Thursdays - Evening Reading Group: (every 6 weeks) 6.30pm-8.00pm Discuss a selection of books, every 6 weeks, refreshments included.',NULL,'wlct','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.523419,-2.491547,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'tyldesley-library'),(72,'Wigan Library','Wigan Library','Rita Musa','Wigan Life Centre','The Weind','Wigan','WN1 1NH','01942 404126','wigan.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/wigan-library.htm','English Conversation Wednesdays 4.30pm - 6.00pm and Bookchat for Adults - 1st Wednesday every month 10.30am - 11.30am. Fridays - BBC First Click IT Course 10 - 11.30am. Fridays - Craft Chat 2.30pm - 3.30pm. Saturdays - Knitted Bliss 10.30am - 11.30am.',NULL