reen (between houses 7 and 9)','Dorning Road','Swinton','Salford','M27 5UX','0161 7283061','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/valley-community-centre','Activities and groups include Swinton Childminders (professional childminders only, just call in); Weight support drop in; Beginners computer course; Councillors\' surgery (Second Monday each month); Kurling; Everybody dance (an inclusive session run by SCL Dance Team, small charge applies, contact +44 (0)161 778 0561 to arrange booking); Bike Reapir Club (drop in for 7-16 yr olds); Valley Breakfast Club (during school holidays for children aged 4-11); Morris dancing; Arts and crafts for over 50s (9.30-11.45am); Over 50s lunch (first Thursday of month- £2 for a three course meal, coffee and bingo); Mens Group.',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.50653,-2.332555,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-valley-community-centre'),(84,'Wardley Community Centre','Lesley or Diane','30 Ash Drive','Wardley','Swinton','Salford','M27 3RS','0161 7943334','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/wardley-community-centre','Activities and groups include Art classes (Tuesday 12-3pm); Tai Chi (Monday 1.30-2.30pm); Healthy Hips and Hearts; Pilates; Meditation Classes; Zumba Gold; Parent and Toddler Groups; Henshaws( for partially sighted people); Fitness Class; Band Practice; Legs, Bums and Tums; Belly Dancing; Circuit Training; Kurling; Bible Reading.',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.519404,-2.357621,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wardley-community-centre'),(85,'Energise Centre',NULL,'3 Douglas Green','Charlestown',NULL,'Salford','M6 6ES','0161 2125700','energise@biglifecentres.com','http://www.energisecentre.co.uk/','The Energise Centre provides a range of services to improve and maintain your health and happiness. It\'s also a place for you to come along, meet other people and find out what\'s going on in your local community. Some of the services we offer are: Rowland\'s Pharmacy, General Practice, Drinks & Chat, Counselling service, Computer training suite, Hair Today Gone Tomorrow, Computerised Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, The Creativity Group - \"Drop in to relax using colouring/drawing, simply arty stuff & you don’t need anything, all materials provided!\" £1 donation requested.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.4975,-2.283695,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'energise-centre'),(86,'Adswood Community Centre','Pam and Phil Riley or Tracy Banham','231 Garners Lane','Adswood',NULL,'Stockport','SK3 8QJ','0161 4744754 or','adswoodcc@hotmail.co.uk or tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: Art group (Tuesdays 1-3), Tea Dance (alternate Mondays), Church (Sundays), Zumba starting in January (Thursdays). For further information on groups and activities please call Phil or Pam or the Community Resource Team on the numbers provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.389105,-2.167423,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'adswood-community-centre'),(87,'The Brookdale Club',NULL,'Club House','Bridge Lane','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 3AB','0161 4392782',NULL,'http://www.thebrookdaleclub.com/','The Brookdale Club is a members social Club with many different activities, from Bowling and Bridge to Theatre and Travel. Activities include Andante - If you enjoy singing in harmony, and would like the opportunity to do so on a regular basis, then Andante may well be for you. We are a friendly, mixed choir who meet on Wednesday evenings in the Jubilee Room and aim to put on two performances a year, a Sing-Along Coffee Morning in the spring, and a Christmas concert. Art - The Art Group is a club rather than a class ranging from beginners to professionals and we all enjoy learning from each other. Watercolour is our main media but many members also use acrylics, pastels, pen and wash, and water based oils. Today we have over 70 members meeting twice a week on Tuesday and Wednesday mornings from 9.30 a.m. to 12.30 p.m. Bowling - Outdoor Bowling commences after Easter on Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday afternoons from 1.30pm until approximately 4.30pm. Indoor bowling takes place from September through till Easter on Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday afternoons from 1.30pm and Sunday mornings from 10.00am. Brigde - The weekly programme of events include Rubber and Duplicate Bridge sessions with teams of Four held in the Winter.  Caracamp - The Caracamp Section is a very friendly group of Brookdale members with touring caravans and motor homes. Dancing - This Friendly section meets every Wednesday evening from September until the last week in July for Modern Sequence dancing. Digital Photography - Our meetings are normally held in the Lesser Hall on the third Tuesday of the month, commencing at 7.30pm with an informal Question and Answer session to help all members of the Group with any aspect of their photography. This is followed by a variety of photography topics at 8.00pm. Gardening - The activities are varied, being made up of Coffee Mornings, combined with competitions and social evenings. Linguist - Made up of 5 groups. The Linguists’ Section is managed by a dedicated and enthusiastic committee who arrange a number of social events for all club members during the year.  These range from coffee mornings and tea afternoons to talks, slideshows, dinners and entertainment.  Sometimes the entertainment is provided by the Linguists themselves. Rambling - We organise 2 events per month – one ramble and one stroll. Theatre - Are you a wannabee actor? Brookdale Theatre is always on the lookout for talented actors and actresses to take part in the 5 productions we hold each year with auditions normally held in May/June. We aim to have a varied programme throughout our season (October- May). Travel - We meet socially on the third Friday of most months, with the exception of July and August, mainly for a varied programme of talks on travel related subjects. In addition to our indoor meetings we arrange tours, trips and visits, as suggested by the committee or members themselves, when sufficient numbers are involved to make them viable propositions. Generally these trips run once a month during Spring and Summer. Walrus - The Walrus Section/ Society began its life some 30 plus years ago and was formed so that Members who had ceased an active business life i.e. retired or otherwise, could meet together at the Clubhouse each month to chat together in the Bar Lounge for a budget priced Lunch and enjoy a Speaker as well and Wine - Whilst the Society still holds wine making competitions, it has developed more into a wine and food appreciation Society we hold popular wine tastings at regular intervals plus talks on food, along with a wide range of topics of general interest. Annual party nights, when we have dinner, plus entertainment and our Vice President’s evening when strawberries and cream with wine are served, also accompanied by entertainment are very popular.',NULL,'brookdaleclub','https://www.facebook.com/groups/281290235267551/',1,150,1,1,53.38381,-2.16335,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-brookdale-club'),(88,'Well Being Centre','Charlotte Baxter','Graylaw House','Chestergate',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 1LZ','0161 4747713','charlotte.baxter@stockportmind.org.uk',NULL,'Set in the centre of Stockport, the Well Being Centre is a one stop shop for anyone wanting to access a variety of health and well being services. It’s important to us that we provide what you want, so we have worked hard to make the ce