me','Stockport','SK8 7BG','0161 980829','brenda.scragg@ntlworld.com','http://www.thefrms.co.uk/affprogs/bramhall%202012.htm','The Bramhall Recorded Music Society meets weekly from September to June on Tuesdays from 8.00pm-10pm at the Friends Meeting House 91 Station Road, Cheadle Hulme SK8 7BG. Annual Subscriptions are £7 + £1 for each meeting attended. Programmes are mostly given by members on a theme of their choice. A printed programme is available for Sept - Dec and Jan - June. Occasional social events are arranged. Most of our members are retired. We are a small group c.28 members and we are always looking for new members.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.372816,-2.183013,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-recorded-music-society'),(123,'BAM (Brinnington Arts and Music)','Becky Marsh','Lapwing Centre','Lapwing Lane','Brinnington','Stockport','SK5 8LF','07813 198556','bamdrummers@gmail.com','http://www.bamdrummers.moonfruit.com/','We are a community group for all ages and abilities focussed on making, playing and performing music. We also run dance and arts workshops. This provides our members with confidence, self esteem, wellbeing through creativity and music making. We perform at community events as a band. We currently run a session at the Lapwing Leisure Centre, Brinnington, Stockport, every Wednesday from 5-7pm. The building is totally accessible and all are welcome. The workshop is free but with a suggested \'sub\' of 50p.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bam-Brinnington-Arts-and-Music/342097782502196',1,150,1,1,53.432516,-2.13035,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bam-brinnington-arts-and-music'),(124,'Age UK Bolton',NULL,'72/74 Ashburner Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1TN','01204 382411','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/','Activities and services include Aromatherapy and Reflexology Services - to relieve stress, tension or just to pamper yourself. Café - serving an excellent choice of good quality meals, snacks, drinks in a welcoming and comfortable environment. Community-based Services and Activities - community-based services and activities, including, befriending services; keep fit and other exercise classes; special interest and hobby groups; lunch and leisure clubs etc. to enable and support older people to remain active (physically and mentally) and independent within their own communities. Counselling - confidential counselling services provided by professionally trained and qualified counsellors. Courses and Activities - an attractive and imaginative choice of short courses and activities at our Learning and Resources Centre. Fundraising - help us to raise funds to provide services/activities, with and behalf of older people in Bolton. \"Handyman\" (Practical Support) Service - for good quality, reliable and affordable help with decorating, gardening and small repairs. Information and Advice/Legal Advice Service - free, confidential advice on all issues, including legal matters, affecting older people. Insurance and Other Products - The Age UK Group offers a range of products and services tailor-made for the over 50s. Volunteering Opportunities - find out how you can join our team of first class volunteers. Walking clubs - offering a choice of demanding and less demanding walks. Wheelchair Hire - short-term loans. Will-Making Service - available at a specially negotiated price. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.576827,-2.432148,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-bolton'),(125,'Age UK Learning and Resource Centre Farnworth',NULL,'Cross Street','Farnworth',NULL,'Bolton','BL4 7AG','01204 701525','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/Our-services/Courses--activities/','If you thought life stopped at 50, then think again. A whole new world of opportunity and learning is waiting to be discovered. Just take a look at what’s on offer in our Learning and Resources Centre. Conveniently located at the heart of Farnworth, the Centre, which has its own parking area, is only a few minutes’ walk from the town’s main bus station and shopping area. This modern, comfortable and purpose-built facility, on two-levels, has been designed in partnership with older people, and offers full access, throughout, for people with disabilities. Hundreds of older people use the Centre each week and all are assured of a warm and friendly welcome. There are courses to suit all levels and all tastes, including: computers for ABSOLUTE beginners, intermediate level computer courses, internet for beginners, digital photography and image manipulation, family history workshop. And if computers aren’t your thing, there’s lots more to choose from: painting and drawing, modern languages, an attractive choice of crafts, music keyboard and guitar classes and literature groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.548993,-2.396181,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-learning-and-resource-centre-farnworth'),(126,'Bolton U3A','Ann Waring','St Andrew and St George URC','St George Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2BS','01204 492343','ann.waring@hotmail.co.uk','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=495&page=1','U3A stands for the University of the Third Age, which is a self-help organisation for people no longer in full time employment providing educational, creative and leisure opportunities in a friendly environment. Interest Groups meet at various venues in the town centre in these subjects; archaeology, art appreciation, basic Italian, biology, crafts (cards), creative writing, European studies, film forum, gardening, French, history, literature, local history, mah-jong, play reading, philosophy, poetry for pleasure, recorded music, scrabble, Saturday ramblers, singing for pleasure, solo whist - cards, walkabout, transactional analysis, world’s religions, women’s history. General meeting are held on the 4th Friday of the month, 2pm – 4pm. Annual Subscription; £18.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.581602,-2.432203,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-u3a'),(127,'Halliwell History Society','Margaret Koppens','St Luke\'s Church','Chorley Old Road',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 3BE','01204 597644',NULL,'http://www.halliwell-lhs.co.uk/index.php','We are a Local History Group based in Halliwell, Bolton, who were intent on recording and keeping alive the history of the Halliwell Township. We meet on the last Tuesday of the month at 7.30pm at St Lukes Church. A small entrance charge is made on the door. We have speakers on a variety of subjects, we usually get about 50-60 people at the meetings which are very informal and there is disability access to our venue.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.585928,-2.450332,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'halliwell-history-society'),(128,'Horwich Resource Centre',NULL,'Beaumont Road','Horwich',NULL,'Bolton','BL6 7BG','01204 668157','horwich.hrc@onebillnet.co.uk','http://www.allcommunity.co.uk/horwichresource/','What\'s on: St John Ambulance – Luncheon Clubs – Tea Dance - Keep Fit – Looney Tunes – Childminders – Craft Clubs - Yoga – Pilates – Martial Arts – Line Dancing – Art Classes - Upholstery Classes – Horwich Widows – R.S.P.C.A. - Morris Dancing – Kidz2gether – B.A.N.D.- Embroiderers’ Guild – plus much more. For more details see website.',NULL,'HorwichResource','',1,150,1,1,53.600597,-2.545078,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'horwich-resource-centre'),(129,'Kearsley Park Vets Bowling Club',NULL,'Pavilion','Thomas Moore Close','Kearsley','Bolton','BL4 8ND','01204 574405 or',NULL,NULL,'Promote bowling as a competitive and social recreation for the residents of Kearsley and surrounding area, throughout summer. In winter we have indoor bowling, card games and bingo (Wednesdays) plus dominoes (Tuesdays and Wednesdays). Junior Sunday session, helping to bridge the generation gap. To bowl you need to be a member. Membership £10per year. Cards, bingo and dominoes are free to all Bolton residents',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.539927,-2.379187,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'kearsley-park-vets-bowling-club'),(130,'Older People - Bolton Council',NULL,'Bolton Council','Town Hall','Victoria Square','Bolton','BL1 1RU','01204 338027',NULL,'http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/OlderPeople/Pages/default.aspx','These pages are a gateway to information for older people living in Bolton, to help you find out more about activities and services including information about care homes, day care, meals on wheels and activities.',NULL,'boltoncouncil','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bolton-Council/102011083185130',1,150,1,1,53.578098,-2.430875,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'older-people---bolton-council'),(131,'Westhoughton Old Age Pensioners Association','Jean Green','Winifield Kettle Centre','Washacre','Westhoughton','Bolton','BL5 2NG','01942 815491',NULL,NULL,'Group of older people (mainly women) who meet socially to play bingo and dominoes and a luncheon club. Ring & Ride used for transporting members. Meet Tuesday 6.30-9.00pm. Friday 9.30-2pm (Luncheon club) Saturday 6.30-9.00pm',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.542738,-2.51652,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'westhoughton-old-age-pensioners-association'),(132,'Pensioners Link','Anne Deacon','Wigan & Leigh Pensioners Link','Allan Taylor House','27 Charles Street','Leigh','WN7 1DB','01942 261753','anne_counsellor@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.pensionerslink.org.uk','Pensioner Link works with and for the benefit of the over 50’s throughout the borough of Wigan. It currently provides a range of services which support older people and carers of all ages by providing information, advice and signposting on a wide number of issues and works very closely with the Carers Helpline. It hosts Wigan Independent Advice Centre one morning/week for benefits advice, and the Health Trainers use our centre for consultations. We also offer a one-to-one counselling service provided by fully qualified counsellors. Very importantly, Pensioners Link provides a wide range of social activities, which are very well attended by older people and carers. Activities include arts and crafts, exercise and relaxation, holistic therapies, good food club, coffee mornings, tai chi, discussion group, Spanish and IT.',NULL,'penlinkhouse','https://www.facebook.com/leigh.pensionerslink',1,150,1,1,53.497205,-2.513966,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pensioners-link'),(133,'Leigh and District Camera Club',NULL,'99-101 Railway Road','Leigh',NULL,'Wigan','WN7 4AD','01942 879518','leighcameraclub@virginmedia.com','http://www.leighanddistrictcameraclub.org/index.html','Mondays 7:45pm and Thursdays 7:30pm. Further the art of photography; demonstrations, lectures, competitions internal and external with other clubs. £26 per annum.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.49714,-2.522583,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'leigh-and-district-camera-club'),(134,'Leigh Library',NULL,'Turnpike Centre','Civic Square','Market Street','Leigh','WN7 1EB','01942 404404','Leigh.Library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/leigh-library.htm','Mondays - Writers Group (fortnightly) 5:30pm – 6:45pm. A friendly and supportive creative writing session. Everyone Welcome. Leigh Family History Society 1:30pm – 3:30pm (Local History Desk). Tuesdays - My Guide 10am – 12 noon (In The Library) Internet course for beginners. Get into Reading 11:30pm - 1pm (In The Library), enjoy stories and poems read aloud, Bookchat 7:15pm - 9pm, Adult reading group runs on the 1st Tuesday in the month. Wednesdays - Carpe Diem Sewing Group 10am – 12noon (In The Derby Room). Thursdays - \'Chatterbooks\' - 11am – 12 noon 1st Thursday of the month. (In The Library), Your Bard (Shakespeare Reading Group) 5:30pm – 7pm. 4th Thursday of the month. (In The Derby Room), Poetry Reading Group 7:15pm – 8:30pm 2nd Thursday in month. Fridays - My Guide 10am – 12 noon Internet course for beginners. (In The Library). Saturdays - The Open Book Club 11am - 12noon (monthly). Reading group for adults. Read and discuss our featured book voted for by you. Craft Circle: Whatever your interests - card making, knitting, embroidery or any other crafts - the Craft Circle is the place to meet like-minded people and share tip and ideas. It\'s free and there\'s no need to book, just turn up on the day. We meet on the 1st Friday of the month 1-3pm. For further information telephone Louise on +44 (0)1942 404469.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.496922,-2.518982,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'leigh-library'),(135,'Lamberhead Green Library','Lynne Evans','Abraham Guest Specialist Sports and Art College','Greenhey','Orrell','Wigan','WN5 0DQ','01942 760041','lamberhead.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/lamberhead-green-library.htm','Tuesdays 10am - 12pm and Wednesdays  1 - 3pm - Beginner\'s computer course  -this is an absolute beginners course teaching everything from turning a computer on to operating microsoft word to the internet. It is a five week course. Booking is essential as we are always fully booked. This is free. Thursdays - Adult reading group 2nd Thursday of each month 10.00 - 11.30am. Refreshments provided. Fridays - Family History 11am - 12pm.  Meeting held every month.  For more details please contact the library.',NULL,'wlct','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.541593,-2.686934,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'lamberhead-green-library'),(136,'Age UK Wigan',NULL,'68 Market Street',NULL,NULL,'Wigan','WN1 1HX','01942 241972','enquiries@ageukwiganborough.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/wiganborough/','At the heart of the work of Age UK Wigan Borough are the services provided for older people across the Borough. These are locally determined, as a response to identified needs and the availability of appropriate resources. Services include advocacy - providing information to allow people to make informed choices and decisions. Bright Days Programme - offering a wide range of activities to encourage you to feel good and have fun. Care Homes Admission Service - help, advice and support for you and your family when choosing a care home. Direct Payments - Age UK Wigan Borough has been funded to help people in use of Direct Payments. Handyperson service - helping you maintain independence and improve safety and security in the home. Hospital Information & Support Service - short term support for older people who are admitted to the Royal Albert Edward Infirmary, Wigan. Information & advice - available to people aged 50 and over, their relatives, friends and carers in the Borough of Wigan. Paveways Plus - Information and advice service for people with a disability and their carers. Products and  services - A range of products and services tailor-made for the over 50s. Starting Point - a telephone helpline offering information and support to people aged 50 and over and  Support at Home Services - offering practical and emotional support in order for older people to retain their independence and volunteering - volunteers undertake a wide range of activities in our offices and in the community.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.548295,-2.633729,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-wigan'),(137,'Contact the Elderly','Kathleen Sheridan',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Greater Manchester',NULL,'0800 716543 or ','info@contact-the-elderly.org.uk','http://www.contact-the-elderly.org.uk/','Contact the Elderly is the only national charity solely dedicated to tackling loneliness and social isolation among older people. We aim to do this by organising monthly Sunday afternoon tea parties for small groups of older people (aged 75+) who live alone, and volunteers within their local community, offering a regular and vital friendship link every month. Each older person is collected from their home by a volunteer driver and taken to a volunteer host’s home for the afternoon. The group is warmly welcomed by a different host each month, but the drivers remain the same which means that over the months and years, acquaintances turn into friends and loneliness is replaced by companionship. Our tea parties are a real lifeline of friendship for our older members who have little or no contact with any family or friends. They bring people of all ages together, develop fulfilling friendships and support networks, and give everyone involved something to look forward to each month.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.497848,-2.318776,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'contact-the-elderly'),(138,'Pensioners Centre','Marian Lachford',NULL,'356 Manchester Road','Tydlesley','Wigan','M29 7DY','01942 701165',NULL,NULL,'Activities include a Luncheon Club for people over the age of 60 in need of companionship. It runs on a Wednesday 11.00am to 1.15pm. The cost is £2.60 for a 2 course meal, plus 20p for tea or coffee. Come along for a game of domino\'s or cards, followed by lunch. Astley Pensioners Social Club meet on Tuesdays 6pm - 9pm to chat, have a cup of tea and play bingo. There are some organised group outings. There is a £5.00 subscription charge per year, plus £2.55 for bingo and refreshments.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.499118,-2.460147,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pensioners-centre'),(139,'Sunshine House Community Centre','Barbara Nettleton','Sunshine House','Bradshawgate',NULL,'Wigan','WN1 3SN','01942 748806',NULL,'http://www.arttoartwigan.co.uk','Art to Art (Wigan) CIC is a Community Interest Company and our task is to manage Sunshine House Community Centre  and some of the groups using it. Activities include: Water colour class Tues 7- 9pm, Wed 10am- 12 noon, Thurs 1-3pm, and Fri 