ve and maintain your health and happiness. It\'s also a place for you to come along, meet other people and find out what\'s going on in your local community. Activities and groups include: B fit B Smart – gentle exercises for over 50’s. Energise With Music – music wellbeing drop in group, come & listen or join in. £3 donation. The Salford Community Carers Group - drop in for carers & their families. Legends – Stop Smoking Service Tel: +44 (0)161 2124050. Women of the World – local women’s group meet every Friday, contact Gaynor +44 (0)161 2125700. Skills & Works – Come along & get signed up with Skills & Work to get help with looking for work, training & writing C.V.’s etc',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.502472,-2.277843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'willow-tree-centre'),(160,'Energise Centre',NULL,'3 Douglas Green','Charlestown',NULL,'Salford','M6 6ES','0161 2125700','energise@biglifecentres.com','http://www.energisecentre.co.uk/','The Energise Centre provides a range of services to improve and maintain your health and happiness. It\'s also a place for you to come along, meet other people and find out what\'s going on in your local community. Some of the services we offer are: Rowland\'s Pharmacy, General Practice, Drinks & Chat, Counselling service, Computer training suite, Hair Today Gone Tomorrow, Computerised Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, The Creativity Group - \"Drop in to relax using colouring/drawing, simply arty stuff & you don’t need anything, all materials provided!\" £1 donation requested.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.4975,-2.283695,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'energise-centre'),(161,'Ordsall Community Cafe Project','','172 Tatton Street','Ordsall','','Salford','M5 3PS','0161 8726011','ordsall.cafe@hotmail.co.uk','http://www.ordsallcommunitycafe.co.uk/','<p>The project provides a friendly, inviting cafeteria and a variety of much-needed services and facilities for the local community, and those