 weeks at 7.00pm at Salford Royal Hospital, previously known as Hope Hospital. Contact group for details.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.487545,-2.323424,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'hope-kidney-patient-association-hkpa'),(206,'Ashton, Leigh and Wigan Diabetic Support Group','Ann Cunliffe','St Thomas Church Hall','Warrington Road',NULL,'Ashton-in-Makerfield','WN4 9PL','01942 202956','anncunliffe@sky.com','http://www.wigan.gov.uk/Services/CommunityLiving/CommunityGroups/AshtonLeighAndWiganDiabeticSupportGroup.htm','The Ashton, Leigh and Wigan Diabetic Support Group is for anyone who has cared, or cares for someone, with diabetes. The aim of the group is to help people cope more effectively with the condition. Meetings cost just £1 to attend and usually include a presentation by a guest speaker on some aspect of diabetes. Meetings take place on the 2nd Monday of each month (February to November), 7.30pm to 9.30pm.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.483652,-2.638549,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'ashton,-leigh-and-wigan-diabetic-support-group'),(207,'Think Ahead',NULL,'28 Leigh Street',NULL,NULL,'Wigan','WN1 3BE','01942 824888','info@think-ahead.org.uk','http://www.think-ahead.org.uk/','Think Ahead Community Stroke Group offers help to Stroke Survivors, their families and carers across Wigan and Leigh to improve the quality of their lives by providing friendship, information, advice, support and education, together with opportunities for interaction with other members by organising outings, respite breaks and appropriate social activities.',NULL,'thinkaheadwigan','https://www.facebook.com/ThinkAheadStrokeGroup',1,150,1,1,53.542937,-2.620864,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'think-ahead'),(208,'Active Lifestyles Development Officers',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Salford',NULL,NULL,NULL,'http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/active-lifestyles','If you would like to become physically active and have any of the following health conditions contact the Active Lifestyles Team about getting started: heart attack or stroke, coronary heart disease, high blood pressure, overweight or obese, inactive lifestyle, high cholesterol, diabetes or a family history of heart disease. Our team of friendly and highly qualified exercise professionals can give you specific advice and information about your condition and what exercise may suit you best and will provide you with ongoing support in becoming involved with the many enjoyable and sociable exercise options we offer. Maybe try our Get Active Programme a free six week course of exercise taster sessions including Low level circuits, Tai Chi and Kurling and with the guidance of your Active Lifestyles Officer discover what exercise best suits your goals and needs.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.488465,-2.298297,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'active-lifestyles-development-officers'),(209,'Community Diabetes Team',NULL,'3rd floor','Sentinel House','Albert Street','Eccles','M30 0NJ','0161 2122095','salford.diabetescare@nhs.net','http://www.salforddiabetescare.co.uk','Provides learning about your condition. Patients can refer themselves by contacting the community diabetes team by telephone or by post. Healthcare professionals can refer appropriate people with diabetes by telephone/fax. The Community Diabetes team provides group education sessions for people with type 1 diabetes (DAFNE) and type 2 diabetes (X-Pert).',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.484727,-2.33811,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'community-diabetes-team'),(210,'British Heart Foundation Heart Helpline',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0300 3303311',NULL,'http://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/how-we-help/support/heart-helpline.aspx','When it comes to anything heart-related, we want to make sure that you have all the information, support and guidance you need. We\'re here to help you, whether you\'re calling