.facebook.com/pages/NKF-National-Kidney-Federation/138351706194949?v=info#',1,150,1,1,53.323112,-1.159271,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-national-kidney-federation-helpline'),(215,'X-PERT Programme','Tracey Hancock','Primary Care and Partnerships','3rd Floor Regent House','Heaton Lane','Stockport','SK4 1BS','0161 4265576','tracy.hancock@nhs.net','http://www.xperthealth.org.uk/','The X-PERT programme is a nationally-recognised, structured group education programme for people with diabetes. It is delivered to people with diabetes free of charge, usually through the NHS. Its aim is to provide them with the knowledge, skills and confidence to manage their own condition, thereby reducing the incidence of diabetes-related complications and the impact on the NHS and improving their quality of life, health and well-being. There are two courses run in Stockport. Diabetes X-PERT - this is a 6 week group programme for people with Type 2 diabetes run by NHS Stockport. Patients attend for 6 half days (once a week) and it covers all aspects of their diabetes. There is an emphasis on food, physical activity and weight management. No charge. For patients to enrol they should contact the X-Pert Co-ordinator on +44 (0)161 4265576. Expert Patient Programme - National programme covering 6 weeks for long term chronic conditions, contact +44 (0)161 4269366. Patient self referral. Held at various venues around Stockport. No charge. Both only available to people registered with a Stockport GP.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.409558,-2.168189,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'x-pert-programme'),(216,'The British Kidney Patient Association (BKPA)',NULL,'3 The Windmills','St Mary’s Close','Turk Street','Alton','GU34 1EF','01420 541424',NULL,'http://www.britishkidney-pa.co.uk/','The British Kidney Patient Association is a well established charity working to improve the quality of life for adults and children with kidney disease. We prov