ance you need. We\'re here to help you, whether you\'re calling about yourself or someone you care about. Our cardiac nurses and heart health advisors are on hand to help with any questions or concerns you have about heart health and heart conditions. Lines are open 9am-5pm Monday to Friday.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,NULL,NULL,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'british-heart-foundation-heart-helpline'),(219,'Torkington Community Centre','Tracey Banham or Kadijatu Mansaray','Torkington Road','Hazel Grove',NULL,'Stockport','SK7 4PY','0161 4742200','tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk or kadijatu.mansaray@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: Age UK (Monday and Thursday AM/PM), Slimming World (Monday PM), WRVS Luncheon Club (Wednesday and Friday AM/PM), WRVS Friendship Club (Wednesday PM), Stockport Stroke Support Group (Thursday PM), Dance Group (Friday PM), Gamblers Anonymous (Friday PM), and Weekend Day Centre (Saturday and Sunday AM/PM). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.380553,-2.098036,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'torkington-community-centre'),(220,'Underhill Community Centre','Tracey Banham or Kadijatu Mansaray','Chichester Road','Romiley',NULL,'Stockport','SK6 4BL','0161 4742200','tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk or kadijatu.mansaray@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: Romiley Rise & Shine Group (Monday AM), WRVS Monday Welcome Stroke Club (Monday PM), Holbart Dance Group (Monday and Thursday PM), Slimming World (Tuesday PM), Hatha Yoga (Wednesday AM), Big Umbrella Club (Tuesday AM/PM). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.414999,-2.08993,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'underhill-community-centre'),(221,'Alzheimer\'s Society Stockport and District Branch','Amanda Pluck','292B London Road','Hazel Grove',NULL,'Stockport','SK7 4RD','0161 4834446','amanda.pluck@alzheimers.org.uk','http://www.alzheimers.org.uk/site/custom_scripts/branch.php?branch=true&branchCode=12658','Information and support is available for anyone living with dementia, families and friends, health professionals and other voluntary organisations, through telephone calls, newsletters, fact sheets and signposting to appropriate organisations. Please contact us on +44 (0)161 4834446 or +44 (0)161 4872945 or drop into the office. The Dementia Outreach service provides support and information to family and carers of those with dementia on an individual basis. This can be in their own home or other agreed venue. The person with dementia needs to have a confirmed diagnosis. Support and social groups include: SHARED groups which stands for Support Help and Access to Resources and Education for Dementia (£6). This is a 15 week programme for people with dementia and their carers. SHARED Drop in, luncheon club (£5), cafe\'s, carer\'s group and walk and talk group.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.376765,-2.115886,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'alzheimers-society-stockport-and-district-branch'),(222,'Healthy Eating for People\nWith Kidney Problems leaflet',NULL,'Dietetic Department','Royal Albert Edward Infirmary','Wigan Lane','Wigan','WN1 2NN','01942 822189',NULL,'http://www.wiganleigh.nhs.uk/Library/All_New_PI_Docs/Audio_Leaflets/Dietetics/Eating_Kidney_Problems/Healthy_Eating_with_Kidney_Problems.pdf','Patient information leaflet for healthy eating. Guide from Wrightington, Wigan and Leigh NHS Foundation Trust for people with kidney problems.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.557346,-2.628661,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'healthy-eating-for-people-with-kidney-problems-leaflet'),(223,'Riteweight','Kath Brignall','Nutrition and Dietetic Department','3rd Floor Lever Chambers','Ashburner Street','Bolton','BL1 1SQ','01204 462563','awmt@bolton.nhs.uk','http://www.activebolton.com/page.aspx?Page=11','Rite Weight is a FREE service that provides advice and support for adults who would like to lose or maintain weight. We DON\'T charge a joining fee and there are NO weekly subscriptions. Rite Weight will provide you with the skills to take control of your weight and lead a healthier lifestyle! Find us at your local health and community centres in your local area so you always have advice and support when you need it. Our Service sessions are held on a weekly basis over a 10 week period. The sessions are flexible, practical, informative and moreover provide useful tips to put what you learn into practice. When you have completed the 10 week program we offer further support should you need it. We provide help and information that covers a variety of areas and help you develop the skills you need to take control of your weight. We can also provide you with one-to-one support when you need it. You can attend a one-to-one session if you can\'t attend a Service, are waiting for a Service to start or would just like some extra support. We ask that anyone interested in attending our course, registers their place with us.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.57691,-2.431634,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'riteweight'),(224,'Rosemary Conley',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'01509 620222','info@rosemaryconley.com','http://www.rosemaryconley.com/','NHS GP Referral Scheme - An increasing number of Rosemary Conley Diet and Fitness Clubs franchisees are running referral schemes in conjunction with their local Primary Care Trusts (PCT) and GP surgeries. Rosemary Conley Clubs are ideally suited to form partnerships with PCTs and offer: Dietary advice based on healthy eating recommendations. Optional exercise sessions for all levels of ability at every class. Classes run by qualified instructors. Rosemary Conley classes cater for all levels of fitness and instructors are extremely experienced in supporting their obese members to achieve their weight loss goals. Emphasis is placed on helping individuals to make permanent lifestyle changes. The diet is based on healthy eating principles coupled with a safe and effective exercise session at every class. To find out if a PCT referral scheme already exists in your area please contact your local Rosemary Conley franchisee.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,NULL,NULL,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'rosemary-conley'),(225,'Slimming World',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0844 8978000',NULL,'http://www.slimmingworld.com/','You’re sure of a warm welcome as you step through the doors of our friendly Slimming World Service. Every week, we hope you\'ll share your personal progress with us, and whether you choose to take the direct route to your chosen goal, or the more scenic path, we will give you the help, support and most importantly the motivation you will need to continue until you reach it. Success is a journey not a destination – come with us and enjoy the ride. If you can’t get to a Service, join our Slimming World Online programme.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,NULL,NULL,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'slimming-world'),(226,'Weight Watchers',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0845 3451500','uk.help@weightwatchers.co.uk','http://www.weightwatchers.co.uk/index.aspx','Your food, your life, your weight loss. Our aim hasn’t changed over the years - it is simply to help you lose weight and learn how to keep it off. Because we believe that food is for life, for enjoyment and for good health, we have developed the new ProPoints plan using advanced 