J','01942 870403',NULL,'http://www.wlct.org/Sport-and-Healthy-Living/activelife/howe-bridge-sports-centre.htm','Facilities at this large site include a 25 metre swimming pool and teaching pool offering a wide range of pool activities from swimming lessons to Fun ‘n’ Floats; a large indoor multi-use sports hall; 6 Badminton courts, Aerobic Studio, 3 Squash courts, a fully furbished Profiles Health & Fitness suite offering an extensive range of cardiovascular and resistance machines, a grass football pitch and a meeting / conferencing facilities with a licensed bar.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.51468,-2.506605,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'howe-bridge-sports-centre'),(325,'Hindley Leisure Centre',NULL,'Mornington Road','Hindley',NULL,'Wigan','WN2 4LG','01942 253142',NULL,'http://www.wlct.org/Sport-and-Healthy-Living/activelife/hindley-sports-centre.htm','Facilities at this community focused split-site include large and small swimming pools offering a wide range of pool activities from swimming lessons to Fun ‘n’ Floats, sauna and steam rooms; a multi-use sports hall, squash courts, Badminton and Table tennis, 5-a-side football, Profiles Health & Fitness suite offering an extensive range of cardiovascular and resistance machines and a large function room is also available for hire.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.532777,-2.562685,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'hindley-leisure-centre'),(326,'Pelican Centre',NULL,'Castle Street',NULL,NULL,'Tyldesley','M29 8EG','01942 882722',NULL,'http://www.pelicantyldesley.co.uk/info.php?info_id=1','Facilities at this site includes a 25 metre pool and 2 diving boards providing a wide range of water activities including lane swimming, ladies only, swimming lessons, birthday parties and galas.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.515092,-2.472289,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pelican-centre'),(327,'Fit City Broughton Pool',NULL,'Great Cheetham Street West',NULL,NULL,'Salford','M7 2DN','0161 7922847','fitcitybroughtonpool@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-broughton-pool','Fit City Broughton Pool boasts a health and fitness suite containing the very best in resistance and cardio-vascular exercise equipment. The suite is managed by experienced and qualified staff to help you create a healthier lifestyle. There is also a sauna available for relaxation. A 25 metre swimming pool and separate teaching pool host many local and regional competitions throughout the year. In addition, there is a full programme of adult and children’s swimming lessons. Salford Swim Squad have most of their training sessions based here and the pool also hosts other aquatic clubs and organisations.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.500411,-2.264735,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-broughton-pool'),(328,'Fit City Clarendon',NULL,'Liverpool Street',NULL,NULL,'Salford','M5 4AY','0161 7361494','fitcityclarendon@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-clarendon','Fit City Clarendon provides excellent access and leisure opportunities for all members of the community. At Fit City Clarendon there are fantastic swimming facilities. These comprise of a 25 metre pool that is shallow at both ends and a separate teaching pool. There is a health and fitness suite, a four court multi-purpose sports hall, aerobics studio, squash court and outdoor synthetic pitch. This centre is an Inclusive Fitness Initiative (IFI) accredited centre. This means that special consideration is given to people with disabilities. There are specially designated car parking spaces, easy ground floor access, modified exercise machines and a fully inclusive exercise programme.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.482914,-2.286624,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-clarendon'),(329,'Fit City Eccles',NULL,'Barton Lane','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0DD','0161 7877107','fitcityeccles@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-eccles','Fit City Eccles is a modern facility offering a double storey 85-station gym equipped with the latest range of Pulse Fitness cardiovascular and resistance equipment. There is a comprehensive range of aerobic classes including, circuits, spinning, aerobics, boxercise, chair based exercise classes and tai-chi. There are also aqua-fit classes in the swimming pool. The 25m swimming pool provides a comprehensive programme of swimming activities from general public sessions to lane swimming, and competitive club. The large sports hall provides the opportunity to enjoy a range of traditional sporting activities and coaching classes.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.478871,-2.346207,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-eccles'),(330,'Fit City Worsley',NULL,'Bridgewater Road','Walkden',NULL,'Salford','M28 3AB','0161 7902084','fitcityworsley@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-worsley','On entering the building you will notice a bright and welcoming reception and entrance area. There are three swimming pools that provide a child friendly environment and excellent facilities for public swimming. You will also find a new sauna suite, which is located adjacent to the main swimming pool. A brand new fully re-equipped fitness suite has been provided and this is complimented by a fantastic aerobics/dance studio which is already proving extremely popular.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.510784,-2.415101,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-worsley'),(331,'Irlam and Cadishead Leisure Centre',NULL,'Liverpool Road','Irlam',NULL,'Salford','M44 6RB','0161 7754134','fitcityirlam@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/irlam-and-cadishead-leisure-centre','The \'new look\' facility boasts a four court sports hall, a squash court, dry side changing facilities, an extension to the existing fitness suite, a multi use/aerobic studio, outdoor team changing facilities, improved access for people with disabilities - including a lift to the first floor, an additional pool entrance in the wetside changing rooms for groups/lessons and additional car parking bays. The additional features of the facility allow more family friendly/co-ordinated activities to take place. There is more of an opportunity to cater for every age group (in particular families) in one building - at the same time. There is now the potential to add new sessions to the leisure programme, as well as expand on the existing ones. The sports hall caters for football, basketball, netball, trampolining, gymnastics, aerobic sessions and sports courses… to name but a few.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.450242,-2.415671,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'irlam-and-cadishead-leisure-centre'),(332,'Fit City Pendlebury',NULL,'Cromwell Road','Pendlebury',NULL,'Salford','M27 9SZ','0161 7931750','fitcitypendlebury@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-pendlebury','Close to the centre of Swinton, Fit City Pendlebury has a 25 metre swimming pool which offers a wide range of aquatic activities from public swimming to swimming lessons for all ages and abilities. For the competitive swimmer, Swinton Swimming Club is based at this centre.  The swimming pool is an ideal venue for people with disabilities. There is a regular weekly session for this group, and the pool includes a hoist. It is also served by purpose built changing, toilet and showering facilities, all with easy access. We have an extensive fitness class programme which is delivered in our large sports hall. Classes include circuits, Boxercise, Zumba, Aerobics and many more. Our Fitness Suite has recently undergone a full refurbishment, which included the installation of state of the art Pulse Resistance and Cardio Vascular (CV) equipment. All CV equipment has it\'s own integrated Freeview TV.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.516161,-2.343715,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-pendlebury'),(333,'PARiS (Physical Activity Referral in Stockport)','Michelle Childs',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Stockport',NULL,'0161 4820900','gpreferral@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/lifeleisurestockportgpreferral','Physical Activity Referral in Stockport (PARiS) is the GP Exercise Referral scheme in Stockport, designed to help patients with moderate medical conditions become and stay more physically active, whilst benefiting and or improving their health. A joint partnership between Life Leisure and NHS Stockport, the scheme is delivered by a strong and experienced team of health and exercise professionals, who provide guidance, support and pathways towards health improvement. Activities include health walks, chair based exercise, gym sessions, yoga and swimming as well as specialist sessions for those with COPD and Cardiac conditions. Some of the activities involve a cost which is subsidised and some are free such as the cycling program and health walks. The scheme operates throughout a variety of Life Leisure Facilities and community facilities also.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.406754,-2.158843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'paris-physical-activity-referral-in-stockport'),(334,'Life Leisure Avondale',NULL,'Heathbank Road','Cheadle Heath',NULL,'Stockport','SK3 0UP','0161 4774242','info@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/Avondale','Located on the grounds of Stockport Academy, a few hundred yards from Morrisons, Life Leisure Avondale has facilities for all the family. Facilities include: Fitness suite/gym, swimming pool, weekly programme of aerobics classes, personal training, sports hall, and children\'s classes and activities. In addition to the gym and aerobics classes we offer personal training and a number of specialised fitness courses. The sports hall and activity hall can be hired out for football, badminton and a number of other sports as a block booking or on a casual basis. For more information on all our activities why not drop in for a look around or call a member of our team on +44 (0)161 4774242.',NULL,'lifeleisureUK','https://www.facebook.com/lifeleisure',1,150,1,1,53.399635,-2.184137,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'life-leisure-avondale'),(335,'Life Leisure Cheadle',NULL,'Shiers Drive','Cheadle',NULL,'Stockport','SK8 1JR','0161 4283216','info@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/Cheadle','Just a five minute walk from Cheadle Village and John Lewis, Life Leisure Cheadle has facilities and activities for all the family. Facilities include: state of the art fitness suite, swimming pools (main pool and small pool), aerobics studio with weekly programme of classes, swim changing area, childrens soft play area, childrens classes and activities, Stockport Metro swimming lessons, and Variety fitness sports injury clinic and massage. In addition to general gym and aerobics classes we offer personal training and a number of specialised fitness courses. For more information on all our activities why not drop in for a look around or call a member of the team on +44 (0)161 4283216.',NULL,'lifeleisureUK','https://www.facebook.com/lifeleisure',1,150,1,1,53.386586,-2.209384,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'life-leisure-cheadle'),(336,'Life Leisure Hazel Grove',NULL,'Jackson\'s Lane','Hazel Grove',NULL,'Stockport','SK7 5JW','0161 4395221','info@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/HazelGrove','Ideally situated for local residents and businesses alike, Life Leisure Hazel Grove has facilities and activities for all the family. Facilities include: State of the art fitness suite, swimming pools (main and small pools), aerobics studio with weekly class programme, dedicated spin studio, sports performance zones, swim changing area, creche, children\'s classes and activities, Stockport Metro swimming lessons, JT physiotherapy clinic and massage,  and Essence of Beauty. In addition to general gym and aerobics classes we offer personal training and a number of specialised fitness courses. For more information on all our activities why not drop in for a look around or call a member of the team on +44 (0)161 4395221.',NULL,'lifeleisureUK','https://www.facebook.com/lifeleisure',1,150,1,1,53.369811,-2.13608,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'life-leisure-hazel-grove'),(337,'Grand Central ',NULL,'Grand Central Square','Wellington Road South',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 3TA','0161 4747766','info@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/GrandCentralPools','Located right in the centre of Stockport, next door to the train station, Life Leisure has recently taken over Grand Central Pools as management contractors and over the next few months the centre shall be revamped to the town centres most advanced fitness facility. Newly fitted with the latest fitness equipment it is planned to refurbish a number of areas in the facility over the coming months. Facilities include: state of the art fitness suite, brand new fitness equipment, performance training zone, aerobics studio, 50 metre swimming pool, and health suite. The centre is also home to Stockport Metro and a British Swimming Intensive Training Centre where world class swimmers and Olympic medallists train on a daily basis. The Stockport Metro programme also offers lessons for complete beginners from 6 weeks old. For more information contact the Swimline on +44 (0)161 4290401. For general centre enquiries please call +44 (0)161 4747766.',NULL,'lifeleisureUK','https://www.facebook.com/lifeleisure',1,150,1,1,53.407132,-2.16011,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'grand-central-'),(338,'Bolton CHA Rambling Club','Doreen Pearson',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bolton',NULL,'01204 394649','stridingout@hotmail.co.uk','http://www.boltoncha.org.uk/index.html','The Club is very active and extends a warm welcome to all walkers and lovers of the countryside. We particularly welcome new members of all ages to come along and join us on one of our many walks this summer. We are a local club, based around Bolton, Lancashire, with no affiliations and with members of all ages and from a range of backgrounds. For a modest annual fee you can enjoy all the hidden delights of rural Lancashire and beyond, the best way there is, on foot! Let us introduce you to walks you may not even know and in turn you can offer us your favourites. Bolton CHA Rambling Club is always keen to recruit new members. We organise walks for people of all ages, abilities and backgrounds and in addition we arrange a number of social activities throughout the year.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.584441,-2.428619,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-cha-rambling-club'),(339,'Bolton Ramblers','Pat Hall',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bolton',NULL,'01204 300602','boltonramblers@hotmail.co.uk','http://www.boltonramblers.org.uk/index.html','The group is part of the Manchester and High Peak Area of the Ramblers\' Association. The whole area includes many regions of excellent, scenic walking country and is also within easy access of the Peak District, the Lake District and the Yorkshire Dales National Parks. Currently we have about 550 members and new members are always welcome. We have a varied programme of walks. Coach Rambles are organised for the first Saturday and third Sunday of each month. Shorter Local Footpath Walks using the wealth of footpaths in the Bolton area are organised on the second Sunday of each month. These shorter walks are almost always accessible by public transport and provide a great way to get into walking as well as exploring the countryside in and around Bolton.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.584441,-2.428619,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-ramblers'),(340,'Get Active Bolton','','The Get Active Team, Floor 1 Bolton Arena','Arena Approach','Horwich','Bolton','BL6 6LB','0800 458 4029','getactivebolton@gmail.com','http://www.getactivebolton.co.uk/','<p>Get Active is a community physical activity programme for over 45&#39;s in Bolton and aims to encourage people to increase their levels of physical activity in with the national recommended guidelines of at least 5 x 30 minutes per week. Existing Get Active sessions include: salsa, gym sessions, boxing sessions, keep fit classes, Pilates, yoga, gentle stretch and exercise, swimming, dancing, bowls, tai chi, off road bike and many more...</p>\r\n','','GetActiveBolton','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Get-Active-Bolton/256539264415883',1,150,1,1,53.578966,-2.537925,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-06-19 11:18:50',NULL,NULL,'get-active-bolton'),(341,'Mud to Muscle','Rachael Ford','The Environment Resource Centre','499-511 Bury Road',NULL,'Bolton','BL2 6DH','01204 603754','rford@lancswt.org.uk','http://www.activebolton.com/page.aspx?Page=19','This project is aimed at adults who want to get outdoors, get active and get environmental. By having a go at practical conservation tasks in green spaces of Bolton the team can make improvements to the environment and their local community whilst also benefitting their health. The tasks include practical management to woodland, wetlands and grasslands and are varied and fun. All equipment is provided as well as brews! Our sessions are aimed at all levels of experience and fitness. If you have never done any outdoor practical work before don\'t let this put you off as our supervisors will provide you with all the information and support you need on how to use our tools. All volunteers are welcome - from those who want to move 40 wheelbarrows a day to those who just want to make the brews and have a chat!',NULL,'Lancswildlife','https://www.facebook.com/lancashirewildlifetrust',1,150,1,1,53.580802,-2.385594,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'mud-to-muscle'),(342,'Wigan Rambling and Climbing Club','Jill Shilladay','Wigan Cricket Club','Bull Hey','Parsons Walk','Wigan','WN1 1RU','01257 421926','jill.shilladay@btinternet.com','http://www.wiganwalkers.com/','Walks take place on Sundays throughout the year, and on Tuesday evenings during the summer months. Start times vary. We are just about to publish our programme for the next six months, which should be on the website soon. Walks are graded according to difficulty and anyone who is relatively active should find a walk within their ability. We advise those not used to walking to start with the easier walks to assess their fitness level. We also organise social events in the winter months. These are held at Wigan Cricket Club off Parsons Walk in Wigan and start at 8.15 pm each week. We are always keen to welcome new members. We charge a £10 annual membership fee which entitles members to go on any of the guided walks including those using a coach to reach the start of the walk. There is an additional charge of £10 per person when using the coach. At other times we use our own transport. It is customary to make a nominal contribution to the driver towards fuel costs.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/WiganRamblingAndClimbingClub',1,150,1,1,53.550641,-2.637151,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-rambling-and-climbing-club'),(343,'Get Active Wigan and Leigh',NULL,'Robin Park Indoor Sports Centre','Loire Drive',NULL,'Wigan','WN5 0UL','01942 488481','activeliving@wlct.org','http://www.getactivewiganandleigh.co.uk/','Active Living is part of Wigan Leisure & Culture Trust, and is responsible for helping people to become more physically active to improve their general health, well-being and quality of life. The team provide a wide range of sessions and activities to suit everyone, wherever you are in Wigan Borough. You can find details of all activities and health programmes, along with lots of information on health and well-being, by visiting their website.',NULL,'active_living','https://www.facebook.com/ActiveLiving',1,150,1,1,53.54569,-2.652535,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'get-active-wigan-and-leigh'),(344,'Salford U3A/ Salford Life Long Learning','Carole Bowler','Eccles Gateway','28 Barton Lane','Eccles','Salford','M30 0TU','0161 790 2372/0','carole@bowler.plus.com','http://www.salfordu3alll.colsal.org.uk/','U3A\' stands for The University of the Third Age. The \'Third Age\' is a time of creativity and fulfilment for older people. The \'Third Age\' refers to the periods of time after the First Age of childhood dependence and the Second Age of full time employment and parental responsibility. Salford Life Long Learning is a group of approximately 250 people within the U3A who are seeking to swell their numbers so why not join us. They have a range of groups which do different activities including: memories of Salford, discussion groups, bird watching, drama, gardening, family history, french, Mahjongg, music, poetry (Fri afternoon-please call), opera ballet on video, painting, science and maths, scrabble, walks, Eccles local history, A toast to Salford, Spanish, summer schools, no vices bridge, book club (first Wednesday of the month @ Walkden Gateway), quilting, theatre group and keep fit. Monthly general meetings take place at the Eccles Gateway.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482579,-2.338968,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-u3a-salford-life-long-learning'),(345,'Health Walks','Jo Bennett','Active Lifestyles Development Officer','Salford Watersport Centre','15 The Quays','Salford','M50 3SQ','0161 7780559','jo.bennett@scll.co.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/healthwalks.htm','Salford Community Leisure’s health walk scheme forms part of a national programme to help encourage and support people to become more physically active to improve their health. Health walks are led by trained volunteers and can be from 45 minutes to one hour in length. The health walks aim to promote the message of ‘doing at least 30 minutes of moderate activity on at least five days of the week’.  Nordic walking - A form of summer cross country skiing training, whereby you walk with specifically designed poles, using your upper and lower body at the same time, strengthening your back, legs and arms, and reducing neck and shoulder tension - all this while improving the health of your heart and lungs. Aimed at people who want to get more physically active. If you\'re interested in walking and would like some routes to try by yourself or with friends you can download six route cards for walks in Eccles, Winton and Barton. The routes have been created as part of an independent walking pack, which contains the route cards and information on health, physical activity and walking. Numbers are limited but If you would like to receive a pack please email your name and address to jo.bennett@scll.co.uk and we\'ll pop one in the post.',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.471633,-2.288057,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'health-walks'),(346,'Boothstown Community Centre','Marjorie or Susan','Standfield Drive','Boothstown','Worsley','Salford','M28 1NB','0161 7999425','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/boothstown-community-centre','Activities and groups include Cafe 55 (meals start at 11.30am); Older persons meeting (first Monday of the month); Grow your Own (6 weeks from 13th Feb, Mon 2-4pm); Healthy walking group (Mon 2-4pm); Men\'s Health Group (Mon 3-4.30pm); Writers Group (Mon 7-9pm); Curling; Healthy Hips and Hearts (Tues 2-3.30pm); Weight Watchers (Tues 5-6.30pm, 6.30-8pm); Zumba (Tues 8-9pm); Lunch Club (Wed 12.30-2pm); Over 60s Club (Wed 1.30-3.30pm); Local Histories (Third Wednesday of month 7.15-9.15pm); Ladies Group (last Wednesday of month 7.30-10pm); Art group (Thurs 11.45-1.45pm); Tai Chi (Thurs 2-3pm); Yoga (Thurs 7.15-9.15pm); Transport meeting; Reading Group (Fri 2-3pm).',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.504413,-2.417325,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'boothstown-community-centre'),(347,'PARiS (Physical Activity Referral in Stockport)','Michelle Childs',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Stockport',NULL,'0161 4820900','gpreferral@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/lifeleisurestockportgpreferral','Physical Activity Referral in Stockport (PARiS) is the GP Exercise Referral scheme in Stockport, designed to help patients with moderate medical conditions become and stay more physically active, whilst benefiting and or improving their health. A joint partnership between Life Leisure and NHS Stockport, the scheme is delivered by a strong and experienced team of health and exercise professionals, who provide guidance, support and pathways towards health improvement. Activities include health walks, chair based exercise, gym sessions, yoga and swimming as well as specialist sessions for those with COPD and Cardiac conditions. Some of the activities involve a cost which is subsidised and some are free such as the cycling program and health walks. The scheme operates throughout a variety of Life Leisure Facilities and community facilities also.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.406754,-2.158843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'paris-physical-activity-referral-in-stockport'),(348,'Bramhall U3A','Mike Hollingworth','St Michaels Church Hall','St Michaels Avenue','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 2PG','0161 4392865','enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk','http://www.bramhallu3a.org.uk/','The aim is to share learning and leisure interests with other retired or semi-retired people in the Bramhall area as well as encouraging social interaction between members. Monthly meeting, usually on the 3rd Thursday of the month, at St. Michael\'s Church Hall with a guest speaker. More than 40 groups taking part in creative activities (e.g. art, card making, choir, embroidery), physical activities (e.g. cycling, Pilates swimming, table tennis, walking), learning activities (e.g. archaeology, languages, science) and other leisure activities (e.g. discussion groups, family history, pub quiz). The U3A also organising day\'s outings and theatre visits plus holidays. How to join - contact the membership secretary by emailing enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk or come to one of our monthly meetings. £10 per year per person to join the U3A. There is a charge of £1 to come to the monthly meetings. Some activities take place in the homes of members where there is no charge. There will be a small charge for some activities where a room has to be hired. There are obviously charges for outings, theatre visits and holidays.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.363982,-2.163215,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-u3a'),(349,'Stockport Ramblers','Gwen Bennett',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Stockport',NULL,'07794 715265','gwen_22@hotmail.com','http://www.stockportramblers.org.uk/','We are the Stockport Ramblers. We are the largest of the ten Ramblers groups in the Greater Manchester and High Peak area, and part of the Ramblers, a nationwide charity whose aims are to promote walking for health, pleasure and an appreciation of our wonderful countryside. We offer walks in the Stockport area, but also further afield, such as the Peak District, Southern Pennines, Yorkshire Dales and Snowdonia. We also arrange walking weekends away, to places such as the Lake District, Wales and the Northern Pennines. We have walks to suit all abilities, so if you are new to walking you may choose a shorter and easier walk in the local area, or if you are more experienced you may choose a harder walk in the moorlands or possibly the Mountains of Snowdonia.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.406754,-2.158843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-ramblers'),(350,'Stockport Walking and Outdoor Group','Sue',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Stockport',NULL,'0161 4948220','Stockportwalkingoutdoors@gmail.com','http://www.stockportwalkingoutdoor.org.uk/','Stockport Walking & Outdoor Group is a multi-activity group with individual members aged 18 to 70+ as well as a number of families. New faces are always welcome ... just come along to any of our events. The annual subscription of £5 per person is collected in January each year. Activities include: Sunday walks, cycle rides, family walks, Wednesday walks. Other activities are arranged from time to time and will be published on our website and in the programme. These may include: theatre trips, meals, barbecues, cinema visits, walking, cycling & skiing holidays.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.406754,-2.158843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-walking-and-outdoor-group'),(351,'Hazel Grove Civic Hall','Tracey Banham or Kadijatu Mansaray','London Road','Hazel Grove',NULL,'Stockport','SK7 4DF','0161 4742200','tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk or kadijatu.mansaray@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: Hazel Grove TWG Craft Club (Wednesday PM), Gardening Club Meetings and Showing (