e (Wednesday and Thursday PM) WRVS Luncheon (Thursday AM/PM), Marple Carers (Thursday PM), and Marple Senior Citizens Dance (Saturday PM). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided. For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.396833,-2.060356,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'marple-senior-citizens-centre'),(353,'Adult Learning in Bolton Libraries',NULL,'Central Library','Le Mans Crescent',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1SE','01204 333173 ','libraries@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/AdulteducationatBoltonLibraries.aspx','Activities include: English for Speakers of Other Languages (ESOL) - ESOL classes run at the Central Library in partnership with The Workers Educational Association. ICT Classes - many of our libraries run beginners’ ICT classes in partnership with Bolton Community College. These classes run for four or five weeks (with 10 hours tuition in all). Other classes - we offer a range of other courses for adult learners – for example Tai Chi at Oxford Grove and Local History at Astley Bridge – and there are new ones starting all the time. Do ask at any library for more details and to book your place.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries?fref=ts',1,150,1,1,53.577385,-2.431294,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'adult-learning-in-bolton-libraries'),(354,'Age UK Learning and Resource Centre Farnworth',NULL,'Cross Street','Farnworth',NULL,'Bolton','BL4 7AG','01204 701525','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/Our-services/Courses--activities/','If you thought life stopped at 50, then think again. A whole new world of opportunity and learning is waiting to be discovered. Just take a look at what’s on offer in our Learning and Resources Centre. Conveniently located at the heart of Farnworth, the Centre, which has its own parking area, is only a few minutes’ walk from the town’s main bus station and shopping area. This modern, comfortable and purpose-built facility, on two-levels, has been designed in partnership with older people, and offers full access, throughout, for people with disabilities. Hundreds of older people use the Centre each week and all are assured of a warm and friendly welcome. There are courses to suit all levels and all tastes, including: computers for ABSOLUTE beginners, intermediate level computer courses, internet for beginners, digital photography and image manipulation, family history workshop. And if computers aren’t your thing, there’s lots more to choose from: painting and drawing, modern languages, an attractive choice of crafts, music keyboard and guitar classes and literature groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.548993,-2.396181,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-learning-and-resource-centre-farnworth'),(355,'Bolton College Adult Learning',NULL,'Deane Road Campus','Deane Road',NULL,'Bolton','BL3 5BG','01204 482000','info@boltoncc.ac.uk','http://www.boltoncollege.ac.uk/key-area/5/Adult-Learning','Bolton College offers hundreds of excellent learning opportunities that are ideally suited to the needs of adults returning to education through adult education or community learning ranging from introductory courses and general interest to advanced courses and foundation degrees. Fees vary.',NULL,'BoltonCollege','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonCollege',1,150,1,1,53.57357,-2.44032,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-college-adult-learning'),(356,'Enjoy Learning Bolton','Tom Smith',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bolton',NULL,'01204 811163','tomsmith.belmont@talk21.com','http://www.enjoy-learning.org.uk/','Enjoy Learning is a not for profit organisation that provides courses and events without examinations. Information is on our website. This is being updated over the next few weeks to include our 2012/13 programme and venue changes. We offer courses to anyone over the age of 18 but in reality the majority of people who attend are over 50 and around 60% are 60 and over. The courses and classes recruit well and we are growing year on year (we started in 2006) - we have had over 1000 enrolments this year. Most of our classes are languages, art and craft, history based, with a little music and creative writing included as well. We respond to demands and this determines our programme offer . This year however we have commissioned a report on what we can offer to stroke victims and are running a one day event in Bolton Library around older people and mobile digital devices as part of adult learners week (May 2012). We offer our courses in the north Bolton area at Delph Hill Community Centre Doffcocker, Horwich Resource Centre, St. John\'s Breightmet and Theatre Church. Fees vary.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.584441,-2.428619,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'enjoy-learning-bolton'),(357,'Bolton U3A','Ann Waring','St Andrew and St George URC','St George Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2BS','01204 492343','ann.waring@hotmail.co.uk','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=495&page=1','U3A stands for the University of the Third Age, which is a self-help organisation for people no longer in full time employment providing educational, creative and leisure opportunities in a friendly environment. Interest Groups meet at various venues in the town centre in these subjects; archaeology, art appreciation, basic Italian, biology, crafts (cards), creative writing, European studies, film forum, gardening, French, history, literature, local history, mah-jong, play reading, philosophy, poetry for pleasure, recorded music, scrabble, Saturday ramblers, singing for pleasure, solo whist - cards, walkabout, transactional analysis, world’s religions, women’s history. General meeting are held on the 4th Friday of the month, 2pm – 4pm. Annual Subscription; £18.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.581602,-2.432203,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-u3a'),(358,'Leigh Library',NULL,'Turnpike Centre','Civic Square','Market Street','Leigh','WN7 1EB','01942 404404','Leigh.Library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/leigh-library.htm','Mondays - Writers Group (fortnightly) 5:30pm – 6:45pm. A friendly and supportive creative writing session. Everyone Welcome. Leigh Family History Society 1:30pm – 3:30pm (Local History Desk). Tuesdays - My Guide 10am – 12 noon (In The Library) Internet course for beginners. Get into Reading 11:30pm - 1pm (In The Library), enjoy stories and poems read aloud, Bookchat 7:15pm - 9pm, Adult reading group runs on the 1st Tuesday in the month. Wednesdays - Carpe Diem Sewing Group 10am – 12noon (In The Derby Room). Thursdays - \'Chatterbooks\' - 11am – 12 noon 1st Thursday of the month. (In The Library), Your Bard (Shakespeare Reading Group) 5:30pm – 7pm. 4th Thursday of the month. (In The Derby Room), Poetry Reading Group 7:15pm – 8:30pm 2nd Thursday in month. Fridays - My Guide 10am – 12 noon Internet course for beginners. (In The Library). Saturdays - The Open Book Club 11am - 12noon (monthly). Reading group for adults. Read and discuss our featured book voted for by you. Craft Circle: Whatever your interests - card making, knitting, embroidery or any other crafts - the Craft Circle is the place to meet like-minded people and share tip and ideas. It\'s free and there\'s no need to book, just turn up on the day. We meet on the 1st Friday of the month 1-3pm. For further information telephone Louise on +44 (0)1942 404469.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.496922,-2.518982,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'leigh-library'),(359,'Wigan Library','Wigan Library','Rita Musa','Wigan Life Centre','The Weind','Wigan','WN1 1NH','01942 