reehlc.co.uk/','The Willow Tree Centre in Lower Kersal, Salford, provides a range of services to improve and maintain your health and happiness. It\'s also a place for you to come along, meet other people and find out what\'s going on in your local community. Activities and groups include: B fit B Smart – gentle exercises for over 50’s. Energise With Music – music wellbeing drop in group, come & listen or join in. £3 donation. The Salford Community Carers Group - drop in for carers & their families. Legends – Stop Smoking Service Tel: +44 (0)161 2124050. Women of the World – local women’s group meet every Friday, contact Gaynor +44 (0)161 2125700. Skills & Works – Come along & get signed up with Skills & Work to get help with looking for work, training & writing C.V.’s etc',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.502472,-2.277843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'willow-tree-centre'),(362,'Energise Centre',NULL,'3 Douglas Green','Charlestown',NULL,'Salford','M6 6ES','0161 2125700','energise@biglifecentres.com','http://www.energisecentre.co.uk/','The Energise Centre provides a range of services to improve and maintain your health and happiness. It\'s also a place for you to come along, meet other people and find out what\'s going on in your local community. Some of the services we offer are: Rowland\'s Pharmacy, General Practice, Drinks & Chat, Counselling service, Computer training suite, Hair Today Gone Tomorrow, Computerised Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, The Creativity Group - \"Drop in to relax using colouring/drawing, simply arty stuff & you don’t need anything, all materials provided!\" £1 donation requested.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.4975,-2.283695,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'energise-centre'),(363,'Age UK Stockport',NULL,'Commonweal','56 Wellington Street',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 3AQ','0161 480 1211','info@ageukstockport.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/stockport/','Our services consist of the Practical and Specific Support service team and the Wayfinder Team. The Practical and Specific Support service team deliver a range of services built around each individual\'s needs. Overview of Practical & Support services: Practical support including Handy Help, shopping and pension collection, and digital support; Social activities - find out about the Pop In Centre, volunteering, and other social opportunities; Support for carers - we offer respite services for carers; Support for health & wellbeing including counselling, a health check service and tai chi classes and support for access to care information and support for those considering care options. The Way finder team is the main entry point to the wide range of support, services and activities. The experienced Wayfinder team will assist each person to find their way to what they need. Costs apply to some of the services and activities that Age UK Stockport delivers. For further information, please contact the Age UK Stockport Wayfinder and Community office.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.408751,-2.157029,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-stockport'),(364,'Bramhall U3A','Mike Hollingworth','St Michaels Church Hall','St Michaels Avenue','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 2PG','0161 4392865','enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk','http://www.bramhallu3a.org.uk/','The aim is to share learning and leisure interests with other retired or semi-retired people in the Bramhall area as well as encouraging social interaction between members. Monthly meeting, usually on the 3rd Thursday of the month, at St. Michael\'s Church Hall with a guest speaker. More than 40 groups taking part in creative activities (e.g. art, card making, choir, embroidery), physical activities (e.g. cycling, Pilates swimming, table tennis, walking), learning activities (e.g. archaeology, languages, science) and other leisure activities (e.g. discussion groups, family history, pub quiz). The U3A also organising day\'s outings and theatre visits