/page/737-welcome.aspx','We provide specialised day care and day centre provision for local older Asian people. We provide a wide range of activities, and entertainment, along with useful information. Daily activities and services include: ESOL English classes, ICT with basic English, cookery class, art & craft, massage & holistic therapy, yoga, chair based exercise, swimming sessions, local & abroad trips, advocacy work, home visits (additional support), interpretation and translation service, transport facility, vegetarian and halal meal provision, chiropody service, health checks, information sharing sessions with various topics, eye tests arranged through AERC, indoor games and entertainment. The Service Users Forum, and Asian Carers Forum are our two main groups, developed to empower and support our service users and their carers. To become a member it is £10 per year.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.571009,-2.447911,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'asian-elders-resource-centre'),(367,'Bolton Carers Support','','Bolton Carers Centre','Thicketford House','Thicketford Road','Bolton','BL2 2LW','01204 363056','','http://www.boltoncarersupport.org.uk/','<p>Anyone who looks after a family member who is ill, elderly or who has a disability is welcome to contact Bolton Carers Support. We offer a carers helpline, carers newsletter, carers outings, courses and special events. Please contact us for a free Carers Information Pack.</p>\r\n','','','',1,150,1,1,53.58968,-2.405844,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2014-05-30 11:45:55',NULL,NULL,'bolton-carers-support'),(368,'Thicketford House Community Care Centre',NULL,'Thicketford Road',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL2 2LW','01204 337537',NULL,'http://www.housingcare.org/service/ser-info-6088-carers-assessme.aspx','The centre is a hive of activity – including entertainment, reminiscence sessions, and an art group, to name a few. People can learn computer skills, including e-mailing relatives abroad. We offer an active carers support group, with a dedicated worker. Carers are much in evidence in the centre, and they are an integral part of our community. Local people over the age of 60 drop in to join in the activities, have a cup of tea, a snack or a hot meal for a small charge. For people who want to sit quietly, we have a sensory garden. Older people who live for a short time at Thicketford often join in the activities that are offered. The centre also accommodates Asian Elders day care. We promote independence in older people whilst having a strong belief in maintaining the rights of the individual. We are located in the heart of the community and are part of older peoples lives in our neighbourhood.',NULL,'boltoncouncil','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bolton-Council/102011083185130',1,150,1,1,53.58968,-2.405844,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'thicketford-house-community-care-centre'),(369,'Westhoughton Visiting Service','Jean Jones','Community Learning Centre','Central Drive','Westhoughton','Bolton','BL5 3DS','01942 799374','westhoughtonvisitingservice@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.localdirectory.bolton.gov.uk/ProviderDetails.aspx?ProviderID=842774','Befriending older people, including a sitting-in service for older people with special needs i.e. Dementia. Also offer support for carers and two luncheon clubs Thurstons H.D.U. Bolton, Wigan Road, Westhoughton Mon 12 - 2.30 and Ryelands Court Ryelands, Westhoughton, Bolton, BL5 2PW Thurs 12.00 2.30.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.551492,-2.518905,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'westhoughton-visiting-service'),(370,'Winifred Kettle Community Care Centre','Alison  Leaver','Leigh Road','Westhoughton',NULL,'Bolton','BL5 2NE','01942 634566',NULL,'http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/Communityanddaycentres.aspx','We are open 365 days a year from 8.45am to 5.15pm. On Tuesdays and Fridays the centre has a specialised service for people with Dementia, which can accommodate 12 people, whilst on the remaining days of the week we have 25 places offering personal care, respite for carers and social activities. Snacks, a two-course hot meal and transport to and from the centre are available at a nominal charge. A bathing service is also available and a hairdresser visits once a week. Our aims at Daycare are to provide care to meet the physical, psychological, social and spiritual needs of the vulnerable older people within the communities of Westhoughton, Blackrod and Over Hulton and from outside these areas for specialist services. We are committed to providing a quality service and to achieve this we welcome your feedback through group meetings, having a comments book available and by regular individual reviews. Our aim is to maintain the independence of all our service users wherever possible and to work closely with community groups in our area including such as Age Concern, W.A.S.P.S, W.V.S, W.O.A.P.A, Townswomen’s Guild and Rotary Club, who use our facilities for some of their activities.',NULL,'boltoncouncil','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bolton-Council/102011083185130',1,150,1,1,53.541291,-2.516206,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'winifred-kettle-community-care-centre'),(371,'Wigan and Leigh Carers Centre',NULL,'3-5 Frederick Street','Hindley',NULL,'Wigan','WN2 3BD','01942 705959',NULL,'http://www.wiganandleighcarerscentre.org.uk','The new Wigan and Leigh Carers Centre opened in June 2010 and is a resource for carers of all ages from across the borough. The role of the Carers Centre is to actively support carers of all ages through the provision of information, training and support. In addition it offers an activity programme tailored to the needs of carers, including: (Free service and carers need to register with us) benefit advice, carers information pack, access to leisure activities, complenmentary therapies and short breaks, access to health checks, training and assisting carers back into education and employment.',NULL,'WiganLeighCarer','https://www.facebook.com/wiganleigh.carerscentre',1,150,1,1,53.534593,-2.581549,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-and-leigh-carers-centre'),(372,'Pensioners Link','Anne Deacon','Wigan & Leigh Pensioners Link','Allan Taylor House','27 Charles Street','Leigh','WN7 1DB','01942 261753','anne_counsellor@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.pensionerslink.org.uk','Pensioner Link works with and for the benefit of the over 50’s throughout the borough of Wigan. It currently provides a range of services which support older people and carers of all ages by providing information, advice and signposting on a wide number of issues and works very closely with the Carers Helpline. It hosts Wigan Independent Advice Centre one morning/week for benefits advice, and the Health Trainers use our centre for consultations. We also offer a one-to-one counselling service provided by fully qualified counsellors. Very importantly, Pensioners Link provides a wide range of social activities, which are very well attended by older people and carers. Activities include arts and crafts, exercise and relaxation, holistic therapies, good food club, coffee mornings, tai chi, discussion group, Spanish and IT.',NULL,'penlinkhouse','https://www.facebook.com/leigh.pensionerslink',1,150,1,1,53.497205,-2.513966,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pensioners-link'),(373,'Age UK Salford',NULL,'108 Church Street','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0LH','0161 7887300','administrator@ageconcernsalford.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/salford/','Range of services for older people. Information on housing, financial & care issues. Day care with activities, meals, chiropody, bathing & hairdressing. Drop-in centre. Home services: shopping. Advocacy. Hospital aftercare service. Dementia support service for carers of people with dementia. Buddy service for clients with early onset dementia (under 65). Social inclusion & insurance services.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482985,-2.337389,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-salford'),(374,'The Princess Royal Trust Salford Carers Centre',NULL,'Angel Healthy Living Centre','1 St. Philips Place',NULL,'Salford','M3 6FA','0161 8330217','carers.centre@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/carers.htm','If you look after someone, Salford Carers Centre could help you. If you look after someone who can\'t get by on their own, whether it is your partner, relative, friend or neighbour you\'re considered to be a carer. A carer is someone, of any age, who provides unpaid support to family or friends. This could be caring for a relative, partner or friend who is ill, frail, disabled or has mental health or substance misuse problems. At Salford Carers Centre we can help you access a wide range of services that could help make things easier for you. Carers have different needs and the Centre can assist you with helpful information, practical advice or support in your caring role and concerns such as: health issues, equipment, entitlements, Carers Personal Budgets, or emotional support. Carers may even be juggling paid work with their unpaid caring responsibilities at home. For more information about the advice, information or services we offer please contact the Centre.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.483522,-2.263297,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-princess-royal-trust-salford-carers-centre'),(375,'Age UK Stockport',NULL,'Commonweal','56 Wellington Street',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 3AQ','0161 480 1211','info@ageukstockport.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/stockport/','Our services consist of the Practical and Specific Support service team and the Wayfinder Team. The Practical and Specific Support service team deliver a range of services built around each individual\'s needs. Overview of Practical & Support services: Practical support including Handy Help, shopping and pension collection, and digital support; Social activities - find out about the Pop In Centre, volunteering, and other social opportunities; Support for carers - we offer respite services for carers; Support for health & wellbeing including counselling, a health check service and tai chi classes and support for access to care information and support for those considering care options. The Way finder team is the main entry point to the wide range of support, services and activities. The experienced Wayfinder team will assist each person to find their way to what they need. Costs apply to some of the services and activities that Age UK Stockport delivers. For further information, please contact the Age UK Stockport Wayfinder and Community office.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.408751,-2.157029,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-stockport'),(376,'Stockport Care Schemes','Breda Johnson','South Reddish Clinic','Reddish Road','Reddish','Stockport','SK5 7QU','0161 4778782/07','breda.johnson@stockportcareschemes.org.uk','http://www.stockportcareschemes.org.uk','The aim of our schemes is to introduce volunteers to vulnerable people and hard pressed carers who need a little extra help and support. We provide transport for people with poor mobility so that they may attend medical appointments and some social activities. We arrange visits for the elderly and  help for the housebound.  Befrienders / carers also support various social and activities groups. Anyone can refer themselves to us if they fit the criteria stated here. Services offered: transport, befriending and activity groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.422318,-2.156517,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-care-schemes'),(377,'My Care, My Choice',NULL,'Information & Publicity (Adult Social Care)','Stopford House (4th Floor)','Piccadilly','Stockport','SK1 3XE','0161 217 6029','adult.social.care@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.mycaremychoice.org.uk/','My Care, My Choice is Stockport Council\'s dedicated website which provides information and advice about what adult social care services are available and how to receive them. The \'My Care, My Choice\' website is designed to help people find the information they need as quickly and easily as possible. It also features: a self assessment tool to enable you to determine how much help they (or their friend, neighbour or relative) might need, a calculator that lets you work out how much certain services might cost you and a facility to search for a residential or nursing home in a particular area and for a particular condition.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.407968,-2.15829,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'my-care,-my-choice'),(378,'Marple Senior Citizens Centre','Tracey Banham or Kadijatu Mansaray','Memorial Park','Marple',NULL,'Stockport','SK6 6BA','0161 4742200','tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk or kadijatu.mansaray@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: U3A (Monday AM/PM), Whist Drive (Monday PM), RSPB High Peak (Monday PM), WRVS (Tuesday AM/PM), Marple & District Rambling Club (Tuesday PM) Probus - retired or semi-retired professional or business people club (Wednesday AM/PM), Bingo (Wednesday PM), MSCA Dance (Wednesday and Thursday PM) WRVS Luncheon (Thursday AM/PM), Marple Carers (Thursday PM), and Marple Senior Citizens Dance (Saturday PM). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided. For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.396833,-2.060356,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'marple-senior-citizens-centre'),(379,'MhIST',NULL,'30 Chorley New Road',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 4AP','01204 527200','help@mhist.co.uk ','http://www.mhist.co.uk/','MhIST, the Mental Health Independent Support Team was set up in 1992 with the specific aims of providing a friendly and confidential service to support and voice the interests of mental health service and their carers. The services that MhIST delivers have grown and developed over time and now include: advocacy at the Bolton Royal Hospital, advocacy in the community, advocacy for the elderly, craft social group, counselling and psychotherapy, information and support for individuals, confidence and self esteem building course, mental health \"A-Z\" directory, mindfulness meditation, support for residents in supported accommodation, recovery support groups for depression, self help for self harm, self help for OCD, self help for Bipolar, Independent Mental Health Advocacy (IMHA), advocacy for the travelling community, advocacy for refugees and asylum seekers.',NULL,'MhIST1','https://www.facebook.com/mhist.bolton?sk=wall&filter=12',1,150,1,1,53.582159,-2.44329,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'mhist'),(380,'Age UK Bolton',NULL,'72/74 Ashburner Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1TN','01204 382411','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/','Activities and services include Aromatherapy and Reflexology Services - to relieve stress, tension or just to pamper yourself. Café - serving an excellent choice of good quality meals, snacks, drinks in a welcoming and comfortable environment. Community-based Services and Activities - community-based services and activities, including, befriending services; keep fit and other exercise classes; special interest and hobby groups; lunch and leisure clubs etc. to enable and support older people to remain active (physically and mentally) and independent within their own communities. Counselling - confidential counselling services provided by professionally trained and qualified counsellors. Courses and Activities - an attractive and imaginative choice of short courses and activities at our Learning and Resources Centre. Fundraising - help us to raise funds to provide services/activities, with and behalf of older people in Bolton. \"Handyman\" (Practical Support) Service - for good quality, reliable and affordable help with decorating, gardening and small repairs. Information and Advice/Legal Advice Service - free, confidential advice on all issues, including legal matters, affecting older people. Insurance and Other Products - The Age UK Group offers a range of products and services tailor-made for the over 50s. Volunteering Opportunities - find out how you can join our team of first class volunteers. Walking clubs - offering a choice of demanding and less demanding walks. Wheelchair Hire - short-term loans. Will-Making Service - available at a specially negotiated price. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.576827,-2.432148,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-bolton'),(381,'Apna Asian Women Project','Farhat Shaheen','130 Gibbon Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 5LS','07969 312754','farhat2k@hotmail.com',NULL,'Counselling service for Asian women. We help to make a difference to the local community by providing support, on sensitive issues, that Asian women find difficult to deal with. We have a number of multi-lingual counsellors who speak a variety of languages including Urdu, Gujarati, Kashmiri, Hindi, Punjabi and Sindhi. All our counsellors are qualified and BACP accredited. Opening times: Monday to Friday 10.00am till 4.00pm. Evening and weekends available by appointment only.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.569219,-2.444592,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'apna-asian-women-project'),(382,'BAND (Building A New Direction)',NULL,'The Bolton Hub','Bold Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1LS','01204 546070','admin@band.org.uk','http://www.band.org.uk','BAND is a voluntary mental health organisation. We support 8 drop-in centres in Bolton, and also have a number of projects which help people with mental health issues in some way. A user led group providing help, support and advice to anyone undergoing life problems, including stress, loneliness, depression, anxiety and other mental health needs.',NULL,'BANDBolton','',1,150,1,1,53.57681,-2.428416,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'band-building-a-new-direction'),(383,'Beacon Bolton Counselling Service',NULL,'The Bolton Hub','Bold Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1LS','01204 546100','enquire@beaconcounselling.org','http://www.beaconcounselling.org','We are a confidential counselling service, staffed by trained volunteers. Anyone above the age of 16 is eligible, irrespective of race, religion and beliefs. Daily counselling sessions are available. Contact the number to arrange an appointment.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.57681,-2.428416,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'beacon-bolton-counselling-service'),(384,'Simeon Centre Counselling Service',NULL,'The Victoria Hall','Knowsley Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2AS','01204 387363','counselling@simeoncentre.org.uk','http://www.simeoncentre.org.uk/','Offers the opportunity to talk through feelings in a confidential, peaceful and sensitive environment. Counselling sessions are free and available to anyone above the age of 16. Appointments can be made by contacting the centre.',NULL,'SimeonBolton','https://www.facebook.com/simeonbolton',1,150,1,1,53.580667,-2.430844,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'simeon-centre-counselling-service'),(385,'MhIST',NULL,'30 Chorley New Road',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 4AP','01204 527200','help@mhist.co.uk ','http://www.mhist.co.uk/','MhIST, the Mental Health Independent Support Team was set up in 1992 with the specific aims of providing a friendly and confidential service to support and voice the interests of mental health service and their carers. The services that MhIST delivers have grown and developed over time and now include