raylaw House','Chestergate',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 1LZ','0161 4747713','charlotte.baxter@stockportmind.org.uk',NULL,'Set in the centre of Stockport, the Well Being Centre is a one stop shop for anyone wanting to access a variety of health and well being services. It’s important to us that we provide what you want, so we have worked hard to make the centre the place to be for a varied range of services and resources. Activities and services include: information and advice on local services, self-help library and complementary therapies, counselling and self help groups, music and art workshops, free internet access, volunteering opportunities, monthly newsletters promoting events and activities and much, much more!',NULL,'stockportmind','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMind',1,150,1,1,53.409873,-2.160111,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'well-being-centre'),(394,'Age UK Bolton',NULL,'72/74 Ashburner Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1TN','01204 382411','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/','Activities and services include Aromatherapy and Reflexology Services - to relieve stress, tension or just to pamper yourself. Café - serving an excellent choice of good quality meals, snacks, drinks in a welcoming and comfortable environment. Community-based Services and Activities - community-based services and activities, including, befriending services; keep fit and other exercise classes; special interest and hobby groups; lunch and leisure clubs etc. to enable and support older people to remain active (physically and mentally) and independent within their own communities. Counselling - confidential counselling services provided by professionally trained and qualified counsellors. Courses and Activities - an attractive and imaginative choice of short courses and activities at our Learning and Resources Centre. Fundraising - help us to raise funds to provide services/activities, with and behalf of older people in Bolton. \"