vered to your home may help to keep you independent. Attending a luncheon club gives you the opportunity to socialise and meet with other people outside the home. A variety of nutritionally balanced meals are delivered. The meals can be: hot - delivered by Adult Services staff, between 11.30 am and 1.30pm daily, frozen - delivered by a private Company, weekly, fortnightly or monthly, suit special diets - including diabetic, vegetarian, low salt, low fat and gluten free, fit in with cultural needs - including Asian Vegetarian, Asian Halal, Kosher, Caribbean, West Indian, Middle and Far Eastern and African. There is a small charge for your meal, including sweet. You pay by settling a monthly bill. The current cost of a community meal at home or at a Luncheon Club is: £3.00. The first step is to contact the Older People\'s Helpdesk (using the Contact details tab above) and consider the measures we use to decide if people qualify (eligibility criteria). Not everyone will be entitled to receive meals. You will be asked various questions and if after discussion, you qualify for meals, a member of staff from the community meals team will contact you by phone to discuss the type of meals you require and set the service up.',NULL,'boltoncouncil','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bolton-Council/102011083185130',1,150,1,1,53.578098,-2.430875,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'community-meals-bolton-council'),(412,'Home Instead Senior Care Bolton','David Deller','Office 18 112A-116','Hamill House','Chorley New Road','Bolton','BL1 4DH','01204 498949','david.deller@homeinstead.co.uk','http://www.homeinstead.co.uk/bolton','Home Instead Senior Care provides quality care for people in their own homes. Care is personalised for each individual with a broad range of services available to help people remain independent. These range from companionship, accompanying on trips out, home help, intermediate care, personal care, respite care and specialist Dementia and 