ordhia.htm','Salford Home Improvement Agency can help you if you need repairs, adaptations or improvements to your home, enabling you to stay put in your community in comfort and safety. We can help you if you are over 60, just out of hospital, in receipt of benefits, on a low income, living in dangerous or unhealthy conditions, a lone parent or if you have an illness or disability. Services include small repairs to major improvements for example wiring, heating and insulation, new doors and windows, roof repairs, dampness and timber repairs and level access showers. We will visit you at home to discuss your needs and help you find the right solution. We will help you get quotations, advise on reliable contractors and oversee the whole job from start to end. We will also help you deal with any disruption during the work, or unexpected snags that can arise once the work is completed. If Salford Home Improvement Agency can’t help you, we will do our best to put you in touch with someone who can. Salford Home Improvement Agency can provide you with information on the different types of financial assistance for financing the work.',NULL,'SalfordCouncil','https://www.facebook.com/SalfordCouncil',1,150,1,1,53.513308,-2.341674,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-home-improvement-agency'),(425,'Age UK Stockport',NULL,'Commonweal','56 Wellington Street',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 3AQ','0161 480 1211','info@ageukstockport.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/stockport/','Our services consist of the Practical and Specific Support service team and the Wayfinder Team. The Practical and Specific Support service team deliver a range of services built around each individual\'s needs. Overview of Practical & Support services: Practical support including Handy Help, shopping and pension collection, and digital support; Social activities - find out about the Pop In Centre, volunteering, and other social opportunities; Support for carers - we offer respite services for carers; Support for health & wellbeing including counselling, a health check service and tai chi classes and support for access to care information and support for those considering care options. The Way finder team is the main entry point to the wide range of support, services and activities. The experienced Wayfinder team will assist each person to find their way to what they need. Costs apply to some of the services and activities that Age UK Stockport delivers. For further information, please contact the Age UK Stockport Wayfinder and Community office.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.408751,-2.157029,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-stockport'),(426,'Stockport Care Schemes','Breda Johnson','South Reddish Clinic','Reddish Road','Reddish','Stockport','SK5 7QU','0161 4778782/07','breda.johnson@stockportcareschemes.org.uk','http://www.stockportcareschemes.org.uk','The aim of our schemes is to introduce volunteers to vulnerable people and hard pressed carers who need a little extra help and support. We provide transport for people with poor mobility so that they may attend medical appointments and some social activities. We arrange visits for the elderly and  help for the housebound.  Befrienders / carers also support various social and activities groups. Anyone can refer themselves to us if they fit the criteria stated here. Services offered: transport, befriending and activity groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.422318,-2.156517,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-care-schemes'),(427,'My Care, My Choice',NULL,'Information & Publicity (Adult Social Care)','Stopford House (4th Floor)','Piccadilly','Stockport','SK1 3XE','0161 217 6029','adult.social.care@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.mycaremychoice.org.uk/','My Care, My Choice is Stockport Council\'s dedicated website which provides information and advice about what adult social care services are available and how to receive them. The \'My Car