sterers, tilers, painters and decorators, gardeners, benefit information and advice, laundry services - washing and ironing, hairdressers, dog walking, befriending, personal care, home security, and many others… If you would prefer, someone from Starting Point can visit you at home to discuss your needs in more detail.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.542466,-2.641195,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'starting-point-telephone-helpline-–-age-uk-wigan'),(440,'Pensioners Link','Anne Deacon','Wigan & Leigh Pensioners Link','Allan Taylor House','27 Charles Street','Leigh','WN7 1DB','01942 261753','anne_counsellor@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.pensionerslink.org.uk','Pensioner Link works with and for the benefit of the over 50’s throughout the borough of Wigan. It currently provides a range of services which support older people and carers of all ages by providing information, advice and signposting on a wide number of issues and works very closely with the Carers Helpline. It hosts Wigan Independent Advice Centre one morning/week for benefits advice, and the Health Trainers use our centre for consultations. We also offer a one-to-one counselling service provided by fully qualified counsellors. Very importantly, Pensioners Link provides a wide range of social activities, which are very well attended by older people and carers. Activities include arts and crafts, exercise and relaxation, holistic therapies, good food club, coffee mornings, tai chi, discussion group, Spanish and IT.',NULL,'penlinkhouse','https://www.facebook.com/leigh.pensionerslink',1,150,1,1,53.497205,-2.513966,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pensioners-link'),(441,'Shevington Library','Bill Gaskell','Gathurst Lane','Shevington',NULL,'Wigan','WN6 8HA','01257 252618','shevington.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/shevington-library.htm','Tuesdays - Bookchat – adult reading group (last Tuesday in month 2-3pm). 2nd and 4th Tuesday in mon - Councillor 5.45-6.45pm. Wednesdays - One Stop Shop - Police, councillor, Resident and Tenants Association 1.30-3.30pm.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.566516,-2.695558,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'shevington-library'),(442,'Age UK Salford',NULL,'108 Church Street','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0LH','0161 7887300','administrator@ageconcernsalford.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/salford/','Range of services for older people. Information on housing, financial & care issues. Day care with activities, meals, chiropody, bathing & hairdressing. Drop-in centre. Home services: shopping. Advocacy. Hospital aftercare service. Dementia support service for carers of people with dementia. Buddy service for clients with early onset dementia (under 65). Social inclusion & insurance services.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482985,-2.337389,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-salford'),(443,'Salford One Stop Shop (SHOP)',NULL,'Salford Opportunities Centre','2 Paddington Close','Salford',NULL,'M6 5PL','0161 793 2020 o','housing.advicecentre@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/shop.htm','Housing advice and housing support all in one place. SHOP provides services that prevent homelessness, evictions and repossessions. SHOP can also help people find a home and provide people with the support and skills to keep a home (including managing money, training courses and finding a job).',NULL,'SalfordCouncil','https://www.facebook.com/SalfordCouncil',1,150,1,1,53.486694,-2.284072,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-one-stop-shop-shop'),(444,'Eccles Gateway',NULL,'28 Barton Lane','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0TU','0161 9096528',NULL,'http://www.salford.gov.uk/ecclesgateway.htm','Eccles Gateway offers a wide range of health services including Two GP practices (Telephone: +44(0)161 787 9010); Advice and information area; Adult and children\'s libraries with free PC use and internet access; Audiology department;  Dental training facility; Diabetes; District nurses; Orthoptics; Podiatry; Psychology; Tissue viability.',NULL,'SalfordCouncil','https://www.facebook.com/SalfordCouncil',1,150,1,1,53.482602,-2.339239,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'eccles-gateway'),(445,'Age UK Stockport',NULL,'Commonweal','56 Wellington Street',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 3AQ','0161 480 1211','info@ageukstockport.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/stockport/','Our services consist of the Practical and Specific Support service team and the Wayfinder Team. The Practical and Specific Support service team deliver a range of services built around each individual\'s needs. Overview of Practical & Support services: Practical support including Handy Help, shopping and pension collection, and digital support; Social activities - find out about the Pop In Centre, volunteering, and other social opportunities; Support for carers - we offer respite services for carers; Support for health & wellbeing including counselling, a health check service and tai chi classes and support for access to care information and support for those considering care options. The Way finder team is the main entry point to the wide range of support, services and activities. The experienced Wayfinder team will assist each person to find their way to what they need. Costs apply to some of the services and activities that Age UK Stockport delivers. For further information, please contact the Age UK Stockport Wayfinder and Community office.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.408751,-2.157029,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-stockport'),(446,'My Care, My Choice',NULL,'Information & Publicity (Adult Social Care)','Stopford House (4th Floor)','Piccadilly','Stockport','SK1 3XE','0161 217 6029','adult.social.care@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.mycaremychoice.org.uk/','My Care, My Choice is Stockport Council\'s dedicated website which provides information and advice about what adult social care services are available and how to receive them. The \'My Care, My Choice\' website is designed to help people find the information they need as quickly and easily as possible. It also features: a self assessment tool to enable you to determine how much help they (or their friend, neighbour or relative) might need, a calculator that lets you work out how much certain services might cost you and a facility to search for a residential or nursing home in a particular area and for a particular condition.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.407968,-2.15829,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'my-care,-my-choice'),(447,'FLAG','Pam Coombs, Wayne Morrison, Margaret Newton or Rosie Deveral','Graylaw House','Chestergate',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 1LZ','0161 3741042','info@stockportflag.org.uk','http://www.stockportflag.org.uk/','FLAG is an independent service that puts people in need of practical or emotional help and guidance in touch with those local organisations best able to provide it. We are your link to the health and social care services provided by a consortium of independent voluntary organisations in the area, as well as the services provided by Stockport Council. Whatever you are concerned about talk to FLAG first. If help exists locally, we will find it for you. Our service is free, informed and confidential. We make it easy for you to talk to us, in confidence, about the help and support you need. You can visit the FLAG town centre office, talk to one of the four FLAG advisors working in the community, or call the FLAG helpline. Once we fully understand the help you need we will point you in the right direction.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.409873,-2.160111,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'flag'),(448,'Bolton Community Transport',NULL,'Unit 4 Lecturers Close',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 6DG','01204 393777','bctfs@btconnect.com','http://www.bctfs.co.uk/','Provides transports for people who find it hard to use public transport services. Transport is available for individuals and groups who live in the Borough of Bolton. They have 4 fully accessible minibuses which offer a door to door service and take passengers on outings, excursions, holidays, shopping trips and many other  destinations. Offices open Monday to Friday 9.00am - 5.00pm. Cost varies.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.57171,-2.431239,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-community-transport'),(449,'Bolton Ring and Ride',NULL,'Unit 8 Summerfield Road',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 2NQ','01204 388500','bolton@ringandride.info','http://www.tfgm.com/ringandride/Pages/Depot-Bolton.aspx','Provides accessible transports for people who find it hard to use public transport services. They provide a door to door service and can be booked for short local journeys to access shops, social or leisure activities, work, further education and attend health appointments or places of worship. They also organise day trips and evenings out for members. Open Monday - Saturday 8am - 10.45pm. Sunday 8.15am - 10.10pm. Cost varies.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.564186,-2.414151,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-ring-and-ride'),(450,'Local Link Bolton',NULL,'2 Piccadilly Place','Manchester',NULL,'Manchester','M1 3BG','01204 364566',NULL,'http://www.tfgm.com/buses/local_link/Pages/default.aspx','Local Link is a door-to-door flexible transport service that will pick you up and take you where you want to go. The services can be used by anyone and are available in defined areas. You must book your journey at least one hour in advance, but you can book all your journeys at the same time, up to a week ahead. Local Link uses minibuses or taxis that you share with other passengers. For further information please take a look at the website provided.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.478372,-2.23295,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'local-link-bolton'),(451,'Travel Vouchers',NULL,'Passes and Permits','Transport for Greater Manchester','2 Piccadilly Place','Manchester','M1 3BG','0161 2441050',NULL,'http://www.tfgm.com/journey_planning/Tickets/Pages/tickets_travel_vouchers.aspx','Travel vouchers are for people who are not able to use ordinary buses, trains or Metrolink and who have serious walking difficulties or are registered blind. They can be used to pay for taxis and for travel on accessible bus services such as Ring and Ride and community transport.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.478372,-2.23295,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'travel-vouchers'),(452,'Travel Vouchers',NULL,'Passes and Permits','Transport for Greater Manchester','2 Piccadilly Place','Manchester','M1 3BG','0161 2441050',NULL,'http://www.tfgm.com/journey_planning/Tickets/Pages/tickets_travel_vouchers.aspx','Travel vouchers are for people who are not able to use ordinary buses, trains or Metrolink and who have serious walking difficulties or are registered blind. They can be used to pay for taxis and for travel on accessible bus services such as Ring and Ride and community transport.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.478372,-2.23295,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'travel-vouchers'),(453,'Wigan and District Community Transport','David Jones','Hope Enterprise Centre','Scot Lane',NULL,'Wigan','WN5 0PN','01942 768811','davidjones@wiganct.org.uk','http://www.wiganct.org.uk/','Wigan and District Community Transport runs fully accessible minibuses for use by voluntary and community groups in Wigan and the surrounding area with a new individual service commencing early 2012. Any group and/or individual is eligible to use any of our services, complete with a volunteer driver, and the charges are available prior to booking. A simple booking form is required prior to travel.',NULL,'WiganMinibuses','',1,150,1,1,53.548943,-2.661969,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-and-district-community-transport'),(454,'Ring and Ride (Wigan)','Neil','Unit 1','Richard Street','Ince','Wigan','WN3 4JN','01942 492 252 ','wigan@ringandride.info','http://www.tfgm.com/ringandride/Pages/Depot-Wigan.aspx','Ring & Ride provides a door-to-door accessible minibus service for people of all ages who find it difficult to use ordinary public transport. Registration is required before the service can be used. To register, or to receive more information about services, phone the enquiry line. You must book your journey between 9.30am and 12.45pm the day before you want to travel. If you want a return journey, please remember to book it at the same time. Different charges are applied depending on the eligibility.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.538464,-2.622424,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'ring-and-ride-wigan'),(455,'Shopmobility Wigan Borough',NULL,'The Garry Kay Centre','Spinning Gate',NULL,'Leigh','WN7 4PG','01942 777985','leighoffice@wiganboroughshopmobility.co.uk','http://www.wiganboroughshopmobility.co.uk','The Shopmobility service is open to anyone with any kind of limited mobility, temporary or permanent. Once registered with Shopmobility, you are entitled to use our powered scooters or electric or manual wheelchairs daily Monday to Sunday (excluding bank holidays). You can shop, or socialize, to your hearts content. Childrens Service: Shopmobility has a children\'s service, offering daily use of children\'s powered scooters, electric and manual wheelchairs. This service is available from our Wigan and Leigh offices. Wheelchair Loan Service: If you are a registered client we will loan you a wheelchair for up to eight weeks at a time. Registered clients can also take advantage of the other services we offer. Twelve months membership of Shopmobility Wigan Borough currently costs £15. There is an additional charge of £2 per day for use of equipment. This charge is applicable for the first two visits in any one week (Monday to Saturday). Any further visits in that week will be charged at £1. Visitors pay £5 per day.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Wigan-Borough-Shopmobility/54005839393',1,150,1,1,53.495438,-2.517165,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'shopmobility-wigan-borough'),(456,'Travel Vouchers',NULL,'Passes and Permits','Transport for Greater Manchester','2 Piccadilly Place','Manchester','M1 3BG','0161 2441050',NULL,'http://www.tfgm.com/journey_planning/Tickets/Pages/tickets_travel_vouchers.aspx','Travel vouchers are for people who are not able to use ordinary buses, trains or Metrolink and who have serious walking difficulties or are registered blind. They can be used to pay for taxis and for travel on accessible bus services such as Ring and Ride and community transport.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.478372,-2.23295,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'travel-vouchers'),(457,'Ring and Ride Salford',NULL,'9-10 Orchard Trading Estate','Langley Road South',NULL,'Salford','M6 6SD','0161 7459001 (B','salford@ringandride.info','http://www.tfgm.com/ringandride/Pages/Depot-Salford.aspx','Ring & Ride provides a door-to-door accessible minibus service for people of all ages who find it difficult to use ordinary public transport. Need to register before first use (this is free). Phone the day before to book ride. Cost with bus pass is 80p each way, without bus pass is £1.60 each way.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.497581,-2.286542,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'ring-and-ride-salford'),(458,'Salford Local Link',NULL,'1 Hope Street (off Oldfield Road)','Salford',NULL,'Manchester','M5 4WN','0845 6055505 (B',NULL,'http://www.tfgm.com/buses/local_link/Pages/default.aspx','Local Link is a door-to-door flexible transport service that will pick you up and take you where you want to go. The services can be used by anyone and are available in defined areas. You must book your journey at least one hour in advance, but you can book all your journeys at the same time, up to a week ahead. Local Link uses minibuses or taxis that you share with other passengers. Prices vary.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.478141,-2.268418,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-local-link'),(459,'Shopmobility Stockport','John Leatherbarrow','Level 2','Merseyway Car Park',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 1PD','0161 666 1100','admin@shopmobstockport.freeserve.co.uk','http://www.shopmobilityuk.org/ShopmobilityScheme.asp?SchemeId=S00291','Our service exists to help anyone with mobility problems, whether they are permanent or temporary. Today with shopping malls and pedestrianised areas it is becoming increasingly difficult for people with mobility impairment to access these areas. Shopmobility lends manual wheelchairs, powered wheelchairs and powered scooters, as well as sighted guides, to its disabled members to enable them to shop anywhere and visit leisure and commercial facilities in Stockport. Manual wheelchairs may also be hired long-term and training can be provided to private scooter owners for the Scooter User Proficiency Award. Life membership costs £20. Annual membership costs £10 for 1 year.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Shopmobility-Stockport/302234283197789',1,150,1,1,53.410272,-2.15984,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'shopmobility-stockport'),(460,'Travel Vouchers',NULL,'Passes and Permits','Transport for Greater Manchester','2 Piccadilly Place','Manchester','M1 3BG','0161 2441050',NULL,'http://www.tfgm.com/journey_planning/Tickets/Pages/tickets_travel_vouchers.aspx','Travel vouchers are for people who are not able to use ordinary buses, trains or Metrolink and who have serious walking difficulties or are registered blind. They can be used to pay for taxis and for travel on accessible bus services such as Ring and Ride and community transport.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.478372,-2.23295,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'travel-vouchers'),(461,'Stockport Ring and Ride',NULL,'Kay Street','Manchester',NULL,'Stockport','M11 2DX','0845 6884933 (e','stockport@ringandride.info','http://www.tfgm.com/ringandride/Pages/Depot-Stockport.aspx','The service is door to door and can be used for any journey required within the area you live e.g; doctors/hospital appointments, shopping, visiting, entertainment etc. The cost of the journeys vary, if there is a GMPTE concessionary pass you will pay the concessionary fare as you would on public transport, if there is a GMPTE concessionary plus pass there fare is free, as with any other free pass, if there is no bus pass then you would pay full fare as on public transport, also travel vouchers may be used. In addition to the Ring and Ride service there is also a Cross Boundary service which enables the passenger to travel into neighbouring districts.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.473979,-2.200857,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-ring-and-ride'),(462,'Easygo Community Transport','Chris','Oakhouse','Newby Road Industrial Estate','Hazel Grove','Stockport','SK7 5DA','0161 4193580','info@easygoct.org.uk','http://www.easygoct.wordpress.com/','Easygo has been established for twenty seven years in Stockport providing affordable and accessible travel for its clients, travel could be anything from a trip to the shops or a hospital appointment to a week away on holiday or a visit to a relative, It was started as a need had been shown that some people had various needs and could not get about on normal transport. all our vehicles are fully accessible minibus’s and we specialise in providing transport for the people of Stockport and surrounding areas who are unable to access normal transport, through disability, age, location or infirmity.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Easy-Go-Community-Transport/193678030690017',1,150,1,1,53.378397,-2.129012,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'easygo-community-transport'),(463,'Stockport Care Schemes','Breda Johnson','South Reddish Clinic','Reddish Road','Reddish','Stockport','SK5 7QU','0161 4778782/07','breda.johnson@stockportcareschemes.org.uk','http://www.stockportcareschemes.org.uk','The aim of our schemes is to introduce volunteers to vulnerable people and hard pressed carers who need a little extra help and support. We provide transport for people with poor mobility so that they may attend medical appointments and some social activities. We arrange visits for the elderly and  help for the housebound.  Befrienders / carers also support various social and activities groups. Anyone can refer themselves to us if they fit the criteria stated here. Services offered: transport, befriending and activity groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.422318,-2.156517,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-care-schemes'),(464,'Age UK Bolton',NULL,'72/74 Ashburner Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1TN','01204 382411','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/','Activities and services include Aromatherapy and Reflexology Services - to relieve stress, tension or just to pamper yourself. Café - serving an excellent choice of good quality meals, snacks, drinks in a welcoming and comfortable environment. Community-based Services and Activities - community-based services and activities, including, befriending services; keep fit and other exercise classes; special interest and hobby groups; lunch and leisure clubs etc. to enable and support older people to remain active (physically and mentally) and independent within their own communities. Counselling - confidential counselling services provided by professionally trained and qualified counsellors. Courses and Activities - an attractive and imaginative choice of short courses and activities at our Learning and Resources Centre. Fundraising - help us to raise funds to provide services/activities, with and behalf of older people in Bolton. \"Handyman\" (Practical Support) Service - for good quality, reliable and affordable help with decorating, gardening and small repairs. Information and Advice/Legal Advice Service - free, confidential advice on all issues, including legal matters, affecting older people. Insurance and Other Products - The Age UK Group offers a range of products and services tailor-made for the over 50s. Volunteering Opportunities - find out how you can join our team of first class volunteers. Walking clubs - offering a choice of demanding and less demanding walks. Wheelchair Hire - short-term loans. Will-Making Service - available at a specially negotiated price. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.576827,-2.432148,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-bolton'),(465,'Bolton Volunteer Centre',NULL,'The Bolton Hub','Bold Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1LS','01204 546060','admin@boltonvolunteering.org.uk','http://www.boltoncvs.org.uk','Assists local people to find suitable volunteering opportunities and also support groups working with volunteers.',NULL,'BoltonCVS','https://www.facebook.com/CVSBolton?fref=ts',1,150,1,1,53.57681,-2.428416,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-volunteer-centre'),(466,'Time 2 Communities CIC','Barbara Kerks','The Old Turkish Baths','18 Great Moor Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1NP','0300 099 4950 o','enquiries@time2cic.org','http://www.time2cic.org/','A Bolton based community company providing support, time and resources to local people by local people. We offer: Befriending, advocacy and mentoring by our friendly STAR workers and volunteers aimed at helping you find the resources you need to make the most out of living and working in Bolton. Translation and interpretation services - get help to understand and process essential information. Training and adult education - we can point you towards current and new learning opportunities to improve your working and general interest skills. Bolton Time Bank - join one of the fastest growing and innovative volunteer schemes in the UK, open to individuals and organisations and opportunities to develop your own community initiatives - whether you want to develop a new project or even start your own community business.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.576906,-2.426371,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'time-2-communities-cic'),(467,'Horwich Visiting Service','Pauline Chadwick','Horwich Clinic','Jones Street','Horwich','Bolton','BL6 7AJ','01204 669408',NULL,'horwichvisitingservice.wordpress.com/','Offers friendship to anyone who is elderly, isolated or housebound and who live in Horwich. Accepts referrals from family, GPs, and social workers. We also offer an assisted shopping service. To become a volunteer or to refer someone to the service contact the group.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.601664,-2.54929,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'horwich-visiting-service'),(468,'Mud to Muscle','Rachael Ford','The Environment Resource Centre','499-511 Bury Road',NULL,'Bolton','BL2 6DH','01204 603754','rford@lancswt.org.uk','http://www.activebolton.com/page.aspx?Page=19','This project is aimed at adults who want to get outdoors, get active and get environmental. By having a go at practical conservation tasks in green spaces of Bolton the team can make improvements to the environment and their local community whilst also benefitting their health. The tasks include practical management to woodland, wetlands and grasslands and are varied and fun. All equipment is provided as well as brews! Our sessions are aimed at all levels of experience and fitness. If you have never done any outdoor practical work before don\'t let this put you off as our supervisors will provide you with all the information and support you need on how to use our tools. All volunteers are welcome - from those who want to move 40 wheelbarrows a day to those who just want to make the brews and have a chat!',NULL,'Lancswildlife','https://www.facebook.com/lancashirewildlifetrust',1,150,1,1,53.580802,-2.385594,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'mud-to-muscle'),(469,'Age UK Wigan','','68 Market Street','','','Wigan','WN1 1HX','01942 241972','enquiries@ageukwiganborough.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/wiganborough/','<p>At the heart of the work of Age UK Wigan Borough are the services provided for older people across the Borough. These are locally determined, as a response to identified needs and the availability of appropriate resources. Services include advocacy - providing information to allow people to make informed choices and decisions. Bright Days Programme - offering a wide range of activities to encourage you to feel good and have fun. Care Homes Admission Service - help, advice and support for you and your family when choosing a care home. Direct Payments - Age UK Wigan Borough has been funded to help people in use of Direct Payments. Handyperson service - helping you maintain independence and improve safety and security in the home. Hospital Information &amp; Support Service - short term support for older people who are admitted to the Royal Albert Edward Infirmary, Wigan. Information &amp; advice - available to people aged 50 and over, their relatives, friends and carers in the Borough of Wigan. Paveways Plus - Information and advice service for people with a disability and their carers. Products and services - A range of products and services tailor-made for the over 50s. Starting Point - a telephone helpline offering information and support to people aged 50 and over and Support at Home Services - offering practical and emotional support in order for older people to retain their independence and volunteering - volunteers undertake a wide range of activities in our offices and in the community.</p>\r\n','','','',60,150,1,1,53.548295,-2.633729,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2014-09-04 17:28:06',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-wigan'),(470,'Contact the Elderly','Kathleen Sheridan',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Greater Manchester',NULL,'0800 716543 or ','info@contact-the-elderly.org.uk','http://www.contact-the-elderly.org.uk/','Contact the Elderly is the only national charity solely dedicated to tackling loneliness and social isolation among older people. We aim to do this by organising monthly Sunday afternoon tea parties for small groups of older people (aged 75+) who live alone, and volunteers within their local community, offering a regular and vital friendship link every month. Each older person is collected from their home by a volunteer driver and taken to a volunteer host’s home for the afternoon. The group is warmly welcomed by a different host each month, but the drivers remain the same which means that over the months and years, acquaintances turn into friends and loneliness is replaced by companionship. Our tea parties are a real lifeline of friendship for our older members who have little or no contact with any family or friends. They bring people of all ages together, develop fulfilling friendships and support networks, and give everyone involved something to look forward to each month.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.497848,-2.318776,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'contact-the-elderly'),(471,'Age UK Salford',NULL,'108 Church Street','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0LH','0161 7887300','administrator@ageconcernsalford.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/salford/','Range of services for older people. Information on housing, financial & care issues. Day care with activities, meals, chiropody, bathing & hairdressing. Drop-in centre. Home services: shopping. Advocacy. Hospital aftercare service. Dementia support service for carers of people with dementia. Buddy service for clients with early onset dementia (under 65). Social inclusion & insurance services.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482985,-2.337389,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-salford'),(472,'Unlimited Potential','Marcia Powell','51 Federick Road',NULL,NULL,'Salford','M6 6FP','0161 7430088','info@unlimitedpotential.org.uk','http://www.unlimitedpotential.org.uk','Unlimited Potential provides a range of high-quality, personal services which aim to make a real difference to the lives of people and the communities in which they live. Services include Health Trainers: We support you to plan realistic, achievable goals and how to reach them. Working at your pace and on issues that matter to you, the results have been fantastic so far with over 90% of people achieving at least one of the goals in their action plan. Support is offered in the form of practical advice and information on the various services and support offered locally.  Healthy Communities Collaborative (cancer, Cardiovascular Disease, ): The service aims to promote earlier presentations of cancer/ cardiovascular disease in primary care, to facilitate earlier diagnosis and treatment. It does this by developing teams led by local people to identify and engage priority groups in their communities. They raise awareness, and educate people about recognising and presenting cancer symptoms/ cardiovascular disease. The work is done together with Cancer/ Cardiovascular networks and screening programmes, while supporting primary care in interpretation of best practice.  Time Banking : \"...time to give and take.\" Aims to strengthen communities by drawing people together and by developing mutual friendships and support. Time Banking is open to everyone, of any background, age or ability. Everyone has skills and experience to offer.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.492903,-2.274601,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'unlimited-potential'),(473,'Voluntary Friends for Older People','Cath Riley','Meadowbrook Unit','Stott Lane',NULL,'Salford','M6 8HG','0161 7723893','cath.riley@bstmht.nhs.uk','http://www.gmw.nhs.uk/services-v/voluntaryfriendsforolderpeople.htm','The VFOP service enlists volunteer befrienders to visit and support older residents of Salford who are isolated and lonely in the community. Our volunteers are matched on a one to one basis and are requested to visit clients each week for one hour. Offers a befriending service for people who are isolated, bereaved or who have mild-moderate depression. Can self-refer to the service.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.487206,-2.321155,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'voluntary-friends-for-older-people'),(474,'Age UK Stockport',NULL,'Commonweal','56 Wellington Street',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 3AQ','0161 480 1211','info@ageukstockport.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/stockport/','Our services consist of the Practical and Specific Support service team and the Wayfinder Team. The Practical and Specific Support service team deliver a range of services built around each individual\'s needs. Overview of Practical & Support services: Practical support including Handy Help, shopping and pension collection, and digital support; Social activities - find out about the Pop In Centre, volunteering, and other social opportunities; Support for carers - we offer respite services for carers; Support for health & wellbeing including counselling, a health check service and tai chi classes and support for access to care information and support for those considering care options. The Way finder team is the main entry point to the wide range of support, services and activities. The experienced Wayfinder team will assist each person to find their way to what they need. Costs apply to some of the services and activities that Age UK Stockport delivers. For further information, please contact the Age UK Stockport Wayfinder and Community office.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.408751,-2.157029,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-stockport'),(475,'Stockport Care Schemes','Breda Johnson','South Reddish Clinic','Reddish Road','Reddish','Stockport','SK5 7QU','0161 4778782/07','breda.johnson@stockportcareschemes.org.uk','http://www.stockportcareschemes.org.uk','The aim of our schemes is to introduce volunteers to vulnerable people and hard pressed carers who need a little extra help and support. We provide transport for people with poor mobility so that they may attend medical appointments and some social activities. We arrange visits for the elderly and  help for the housebound.  Befrienders / carers also support various social and activities groups. Anyone can refer themselves to us if they fit the criteria stated here. Services offered: transport, befriending and activity groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.422318,-2.156517,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-care-schemes'),(476,'Contact the Elderly','Kathleen Sheridan',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Greater Manchester',NULL,'0800 716543 or ','info@contact-the-elderly.org.uk','http://www.contact-the-elderly.org.uk/','Contact the Elderly is the only national charity solely dedicated to tackling loneliness and social isolation among older people. We aim to do this by organising monthly Sunday afternoon tea parties for small groups of older people (aged 75+) who live alone, and volunteers within their local community, offering a regular and vital friendship link every month. Each older person is collected from their home by a volunteer driver and taken to a volunteer host’s home for the afternoon. The group is warmly welcomed by a different host each month, but the drivers remain the same which means that over the months and years, acquaintances turn into friends and loneliness is replaced by companionship. Our tea parties are a real lifeline of friendship for our older members who have little or no contact with any family or friends. They bring people of all ages together, develop fulfilling friendships and support networks, and give everyone involved something to look forward to each month.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.497848,-2.318776,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'contact-the-elderly'),(477,'Well Being Centre','Charlotte Baxter','Graylaw House','Chestergate',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 1LZ','0161 4747713','charlotte.baxter@stockportmind.org.uk',NULL,'Set in the centre of Stockport, the Well Being Centre is a one stop shop for anyone wanting to access a variety of health and well being services. It’s important to us that we provide what you want, so we have worked hard to make the centre the place to be for a varied range of services and resources. Activities and services include: information and advice on local services, self-help library and complementary therapies, counselling and self help groups, music and art workshops, free internet access, volunteering opportunities, monthly newsletters promoting events and activities and much, much more!',NULL,'stockportmind','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMind',1,150,1,1,53.409873,-2.160111,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'well-being-centre'),(478,'Diabetes UK - Isle of Wight','Chairman -   Richard Newnham','The Red Cross House','Hunnycross Way','','Newport','PO30 5ZD','01983  290168','ricnewnham@onwight.net','http://isle-of-wight.diabetesukgroup.org/home/iow---home.asp','<p>Historically, the majority of&nbsp;diabetes care on the IOW was at the Diabetes Centre at St Marys Hospital.<br />\r\nThe Diabetes UK - Isle of Wight Voluntary Group was well supported, raising much needed funds for both the Diabetes Centre and Diabetes UK.&nbsp;&nbsp; Monthly meetings at The Red Cross House were well attended, always an interesting programme of speakers providing much valuable information.&nbsp; Meetings also giving the opportunity to meet one&#39;s fellow peers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More recently, most diabetes care on the IOW is now with the PCT (GP&#39;s, Health Centre&#39;s, Medical Centre&#39;s, Surgery&#39;s etc). This, inadvertently seems to&nbsp;have resulted in&nbsp; less support of the Diabetes UK - Isle of Wight Voluntary Group.&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe trend&nbsp;has changed,&nbsp;&nbsp;meetings&nbsp;are well&nbsp;supported by a growing audience, resulting in much interesting discussion.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Monthly meetings&nbsp;continue at The Red Cross House.....and.....<br />\r\nDiabetes Support Groups across the Island, all working together - United we Stand. People&nbsp;free to attend any meeting/group as and when convenient.<br />\r\nSandown is the first of such, formed in August 2010 (now standalone),&nbsp; Carisbrooke November 2010, Wootton Bridge May 2011, St Helens/Bembridge June 2011 and Ventnor 2012.</p>\r\n','Monday, July 14th  Liz Whittingstall, Senior Diabetes Specialist Nurse  - Tablets, Insulin, Food, Hypos and more! -  August  No meeting - Summer Hols.  Monday, September 8th  Dr Ali Al-Bahrani, Consul','','',1,150,1,1,50.6992203,-1.30216810000002,'eng','2014-07-10 09:33:47','2014-09-04 17:28:32',NULL,NULL,'diabetes-uk-isle-of-wight'),(479,'Alzheimer\'s Cafe','','St John\'s Church Hall','Cnr of Terrace Road and Drake Road ','','Nodehill ','PO30 1EQ','220200 ','Alzheimercafe@btconnect.com','','<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:217pt\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"width: 217pt; height: 60pt\">For people living with dementia, their families and friends, carers and those with an interest in dementia.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n','Last Thursday monthly, 6-8.30pm','','',1,150,1,1,50.69565,-1.29616120000003,'eng','2014-07-10 09:55:19','2014-09-04 17:29:28',NULL,NULL,'alzheimer-s-caf'),(480,'Bingo','','Downside Community and Learning Centre ','Isobel Centre','Furrlongs Campus Furrlongs ','Newport',' PO30 2AX','01983 524340','','','<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width:109px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"height:130px; width:109px\">entranc