dfrey ','Congregational Church','98 Pyle Street','','Newport','PO30 1UH','01983 529626','ivor@glynhinton.entadsl.com','http://www.nhsrf.org.uk/branchesdata.php?brnm=90','<p><strong>If you are retired or coming up to retirement from the NHS and living in this area, you and your partner will be made very welcome at our branch.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Fellowship exists to maintain friendships and to provide opportunities to make new friends through a range of social and leisure activities.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou will be given a warm welcome whether you worked in a hospital or in the community and whatever your job.</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>We are a small friendly club who meet once a month (except for January and August) to enjoy each other&rsquo;s company and listen to a speaker </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>We also arrange to meet together for lunch and go on outings on the island during the year </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>We welcome new members at any of our meetings or guests who may wish to visit a few times before they decide if they want to join </strong></p>\r\n','Monthly 1st Tuesday - 2.30 - 4.30pm (except Jan, Aug and Dec)','','',60,150,1,1,50.698611,-1.29804260000003,'eng','2014-07-11 14:35:24','2014-09-03 15:11:51',NULL,NULL,'national-health-service-retirement-fellowship'),(528,'Newport (I.W.) Scrabble Club','Noel Turner','Riverside Centre','The Quay','','Newport','PO30 2QR','01983 614426','','http://newportiwsc.org.uk/','<p>Did you know that, according to J.W. Spears&#39; own newsletter, there are more competitive Scrabble players per head of population on the Isle of Wight, than anywhere else in the UK?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, congratulations! You are lucky enough to want to pursue your favourite hobby in what is probably the best place in the country. There are major cities which have struggled to form Scrabble Clubs, whilst the Island has two of the largest clubs around.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In practice, this means that we can offer you a whole range of possible opponents, from people who enjoy the game simply because they like word-games and enjoy the company, right up to one lady, Penny Downer, (pictured right, taking part in the National Championships, in a photograph that was published in &quot;The Times&quot;) who the top U.S. player, Matt Graham (runner-up in the 1997 World Championships) described, simply, as &quot;awesome&quot;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Newport (I.W.) Scrabble Club meets every Tuesday evening, at 7.15pm ready for a 7.30 start, at the Riverside Centre, Newport Quay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ryde (I.W.) Scrabble Club meets every Monday evening, at 7.15pm ready for a 7.30 start, at the Community Centre, George Street, Ryde.</p>\r\n','every Tuesday evening, at 7.15pm ready for a 7.30 start','','',1,150,1,1,50.7024596,-1.2905508000000099,'eng','2014-07-11 14:38:28','2014-07-11 14:38:28',NULL,NULL,'newport-i-w-scrabble-club'),(529,'Newport Afternoon Womens Guild','Mrs I Clark','The Parish Centre','Town Lane','','Newport','PO30 1JU','01893 520914','','','<p>The Isle of Wight Federation meets bi-monthly on the 4th Monday 10.15am at the Broadway Centre, Sandown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Federation, as well as supporting the eleven Island Guilds, hosts annually an Arts &amp; Crafts Exhibition, an inter-guild Quiz, both a Luncheon and a Christmas Concert. The Federation organises many enjoyable holidays and outings for both members, friends and husbands, and there is always a waiting list as these are so popular.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The fastest growing guild on the Island, Lake Morning, has decided to continue not only with their personal recruitment events but to raise awareness of TG in general at several of the annual Island shows again this year.</p>\r\n',' 1st Mon of the month -  14.00 - 16.30','','',1,150,0,1,50.6989214,-1.29285549999997,'eng','2014-07-11 15:14:44','2014-09-04 17:13:28',NULL,NULL,'newport-afternoon-womens-guild'),(530,'Townswomen\'s Guild, Newport Evening','Mrs M Wheeldon','The Parish Centre','Town Lane','','Newport','PO30 1JU','01983 240 988','','','<p>The Isle of Wight Federation meets bi-monthly on the 4th Monday 10.15am at the Broadway Centre, Sandown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Federation, as well as supporting the eleven Island Guilds, hosts annually an Arts &amp; Crafts Exhibition, an inter-guild Quiz, both a Luncheon and a Christmas Concert. The Federation organises many enjoyable holidays and outings for both members, friends and husbands, and there is always a waiting list as these are so popular.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The fastest growing guild on the Island, Lake Morning, has decided to continue not only with their personal recruitment events but to raise awareness of TG in general at several of the annual Island shows again this year.</p>\r\n','3rd Mon 19.15 exc Aug ','','',1,150,0,1,50.6989214,-1.29285549999997,'eng','2014-07-11 15:26:16','2014-09-04 17:13:11',NULL,NULL,'townswomen-s-guild-newport-evening'),(531,'University of the 3rd Age','Sue Casey, Secretary','The Quay','','','Newport','PO30 2QR','01983 614 095','','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=665','<p style=\"margin-left:0.5em\">The Isle of Wight U3A started in 1992. We now have nearly 400 members and are still growing! (Charity No. 1048548)</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0.5em\">Despite the term &#39;University&#39; there are no exams or degrees. It simply a desire to learn for its own sake and to share the company of others. Our members are mainly people who are retired or not in full time employment. We mainly meet in&nbsp;<a href=\"http://u3asitec.org.uk/live/code/u3asite.php?site=665&amp;page=2\">groups</a>, and these are very varied ranging from languages, literature, bridge, dancing, art, history, IT, plus many more. The groups are run and organised by members.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0.5em\">We also hold quarterly open meetings at the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.google.co.uk/maps/place/Riverside+Centre+Ltd/@50.70246,-1.290551,17z/data=!3m1!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0xe838e14c6c180e1b\">Riverside Centre</a>, Newport. Visitors are welcome to come and listen to interesting speakers, meet members and enjoy free refreshments. Once a year we have an &#39;Open Day&#39; which is open to all. Group leaders run stalls so that they can share with everyone what goes on within their own groups.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0.5em\">We publish a quarterly&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.rogerskid.org.uk/iwu3a/news_flip/index.html\">newsletter</a>&nbsp;for all our members. This gives lots of information about our groups and keeps everyone informed. The annual membership fee is &pound;12 single or &pound;20 per couple. This gives access to as many groups as you wish (provided they have places).</p>\r\n','Various','','',1,150,1,1,50.7024596,-1.2905508000000099,'eng','2014-07-11 15:29:49','2014-09-03 15:15:36',NULL,NULL,'university-of-the-3rd-age'),(532,'Tai Chi Chaun','','Riverside Centre','The Quay','','ne','PO30 2QR','07891836295','tomasntraceysegrue@btinternet.com','','<p>Natural Balance, anyone, any age and any ability.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact: 01983 616953 / 07891836295</p>\r\n','Friday 10-11am','','',1,150,1,1,50.7024596,-1.2905508000000099,'eng','2014-07-11 15:35:15','2014-07-11 15:35:15',NULL,NULL,'tai-chi-chaun'),(533,'Badminton Club','Clayton Sheath ','Wroxall Community Centre, Station Road','','','Wroxall','PO38 3DP','856461','','','','Tues 10.30-12','','',1,150,1,1,50.6164776,-1.2213967000000099,'eng','2014-08-07 09:36:53','2014-08-07 09:36:53',NULL,NULL,'badminton-club'),(534,'Women\'s Institute','','Shorwell Parish Hall','','','Shorwell','PO30 3JR','524716','','','','2nd Monday of the month. 7.30pm.','','',1,150,0,1,50.6406755,-1.35504939999998,'eng','2014-08-07 10:06:21','2014-09-04 17:12:50',NULL,NULL,'women-s-institute'),(535,'Brighstone Women\'s Institute','Angela Russell ','Wilberforce Hall','','','Brighstone','PO30 4AX','740403','','','','Every 2nd Tuesday at 7.30pm','','',1,150,0,1,50.6436989,-1.39568299999996,'eng','2014-08-07 10: