e Street','','','Ryde','PO33 2JF','01983 812774','','','<p>Chatters Caf&eacute; &ndash; Monday to Friday 10.00 &ndash; 2.00 p.m. This caf&eacute; has cheap, subsidized food. Friend&nbsp;to Friend Club on Tuesdays from 2.30 p.m. Contact Gwen tel.565588 or Joyce tel.564890 or contact their office tel.812774 Scrabble Club &ndash; Monday 7.00 &ndash; 10.00 p.m Bridge Club ( Island Bridge Club)&nbsp; contact Bud Abbott on tel.616786 Art Class held Monday&rsquo;s a.m. and p.m. (Oils and Acrylics)&nbsp; tel.812774</p>\r\n','Various','','',1,150,1,1,50.729454,-1.16150489999995,'eng','2014-08-10 23:55:13','2014-09-03 15:10:16',NULL,NULL,'george-street-centre'),(677,'Gobles Centre - activities','Call the warden','The Gobles','Lower Wood Street','','Ryde','PO33 2HJ','01983 614592','','','<p>Weekly social activities include singalong - memory lane, musical entertaiment, keep fit, bingo</p>\r\n','','','',65,150,1,1,50.7284755,-1.1542680999999702,'eng','2014-08-10 23:57:08','2014-09-04 16:49:04',NULL,NULL,'gobles-centre'),(678,'Harold Lewis Day Centre - tea/coffee/lunch ','Mrs Larkin','36 High Street ','','','Bembridge','PO35 5SE','01983 874455','','','<p>Tea/Coffee and Lunch avaialable.</p>\r\n','Tues and Thurs: 9-2pm','','',1,150,1,1,50.6898968,-1.0898680999999901,'eng','2014-08-11 00:08:30','2014-09-04 16:47:35',NULL,NULL,'harold-lewis-day-centre'),(679,'Haylands Health Walk','Richard Dent Volunteer Coordinator IOW NHS Trust','United reform church','junction of Upton Rd and Corbetts Rd','Haylands','Ryde','PO33 3LE','822099 ext 6246','richard.dent@iow.nhs.uk','http://www.rydebaptist.org/chatterscafe.htm','<p>Intermediate walks</p>\r\n','every last Tuesday of the month at 10.30am   ','','',1,150,1,1,50.7200392,-1.17293480000001,'eng','2014-08-11 00:11:44','2014-09-04 16:47:03',NULL,NULL,'haylands-health-walk'),(680,'Health Walks','Louise Grey','Meet at The Pavillion, East Cowes.','Vectis Road','','East Cowes','PO32 6HN','01983 538003','','','<p>All walks lead by trained volunteer and are fairly level. You can walk at your own pace.</p>\r\n','Wed: 10am','','',1,150,1,1,50.7493504,-1.28359150000006,'eng','2014-08-11 00:13:49','2014-09-04 16:46:34',NULL,NULL,'health-walks-7'),(681,'Holy Trinity Church - hot lunch','','Dover Street','','','Ryde','PO33 2BN','','','','<p>Hot lunch.</p>\r\n','Daily 12-3pm','','',1,150,1,1,50.7278178,-1.15782200000001,'eng','2014-08-11 00:15:19','2014-09-04 16:46:11',NULL,NULL,'holy-trinity-church'),(682,'Housing Benefit and Council Tax','','North Medina Community Development Trust','1 Ferry Road','','East Cowes','PO32 6RA','','','','','9.30-12.30pm','','',1,150,1,1,50.7575168,-1.2896197999999701,'eng','2014-08-11 00:17:28','2014-09-04 16:45:43',NULL,NULL,'housing-benefit-and-council-tax-1'),(683,'Independent Arts Singabout','','All Saints Church Hall','Queens Road','','Ryde','PO33 3BG','01983 822437','','http://independentarts.org.uk/singabout_1/','<p>Singing for Well Being.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SingAbout is a fun and social music therapy run by Independent Arts on the Isle of Wight, which can help to maintain memory and improve mood and wellbeing. It can also improve breathing, movement, speech and confidence. It&#39;s fun and free and an opportunity to get out and meet people.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SingAbout is based on the &lsquo;Singing for the Brain&rsquo; therapy, which was developed specifically for people with Alzheimer&rsquo;s and other dementia sufferers, as well as people whose brain functions are affected perhaps by a stroke or injury. &#39;Singing for the Brain&rsquo; is a trademarked therapy which has gained much recognition through studies undertaken with patients. It is recognised by the NHS as the most effective form of complementary therapy for this group and it works by stimulating, improving and maintaining the brain&rsquo;s neurological pathways.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our SingAbout sessions, led by experienced practitioners, have a wider benefit to both carers and participants by providing group activity and encouraging social interaction. The sessions require group participation, and sometimes songs will be sung in rounds. Many of the songs require gentle hand actions or chair-based movements. Some are specifically chosen to invoke memories; some are previously unknown so participants are encouraged to memorise the words.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>No musical background is necessary so come along and try it!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Weekly on a Monday from 2 -4 p.m','','',1,150,1,1,50.727324,-1.16922210000007,'eng','2014-08-11 00:20:30','2014-09-04 16:45:17',NULL,NULL,'independent-arts-singabout-1'),(684,'Island Flower Club','Kate Newcombe','Wootton Bridge Community Centre','Brannon Way ','Wootton Bridge ','Wootton','PO33 4NW','01983 564369','sue.gibbons@hotmail.com','http://www.nafas.org.uk/flower_club/Island+Flower+Club+(Ryde).html','','2nd Wed of each month at 2pm. ','','',1,150,1,1,50.7243677,-1.2311995,'eng','2014-08-11 00:23:07','2014-09-04 16:44:18',NULL,NULL,'island-flower-club'),(685,'Line Dancing','Derek George ','Bembridge Village Hall','High Street','','Bembridge','PO35','01983 873228','','','<p>Tea/Coffee and biscuits available</p>\r\n','Mon and Fri 10-11.30','','',1,150,1,1,50.6793881,-1.10002529999997,'eng','2014-08-11 00:25:34','2014-09-04 16:43:54',NULL,NULL,'line-dancing-2'),(686,'Mature Moves','Diana Smith','Bembridge Village Hall','High Street','','Bembridge','PO35','01983 567032','','','<p>Keep Fit class for the over 60s.</p>\r\n','Tues (not 1st Tues of the month) 2:30pm. ','','',65,150,1,1,50.6793881,-1.10002529999997,'eng','2014-08-11 00:27:05','2014-09-04 16:43:34',NULL,NULL,'mature-moves'),(687,'Line Dancing','Shirl and Dave','Wootton Community Centre','Brannon Way','','Wootton','PO33 4NW','01983 880149','','','','Mon: 2-3.30 (Beginners) 7.45-9.15 (easy Intermediates) Tues: 2-3.30, 7.45-9.15 (improvers) ','','',1,150,1,1,50.7243677,-1.2311995,'eng','2014-08-11 00:29:26','2014-09-04 16:43:11',NULL,NULL,'line-dancing-3'),(688,'Mature Move