2','','','<p>Senior citizens are very welcome. Tea/coffee and friendship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Free</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tea/Coffee and friendship. Free</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Senior Circle meets every Wednesday at the Church at 2:30pm for an hour or so. There are regularly about 35 people who attend each week. Throughout the year there are various trips planned. In the summer there are trips out to Rhylstone Gardens for cream teas and there are various celebration meals at Christmas etc. During the Wednesday meetings there is opportunity to meet people and make friends. Very often we will have quizzes together; speakers who talk to us about various topics and a time of getting to know each other over a cup of tea or coffee. We have great fun together and would like to welcome anyone to join us.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n','every Wednesday 2.30 - 4.00 p.m. ','','',65,150,1,1,50.725123,-1.16074630000003,'eng','2014-08-11 00:43:23','2014-09-04 16:11:16',NULL,NULL,'ryde-elim-church-senior-circle'),(694,'Ryde Health Walk','Richard Dent Volunteer Coordinator IOW NHS Trust','meet outside LA Bowl, Ryde esplanade, Ryde','Esplanade Pavilion','Esplanade','Ryde','PO33 2EL','822099 ext 6246','richard.dent@iow.nhs.uk','http://www.walkingforhealth.org.uk/walkfinder/south-east/isle-wight-health-walks','<p><strong>Come along to a regular Health Walk and...&quot;Walk your way to health&quot;</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nLed every week by experienced Walks Leaders, all short walks are fairly level and you can walk at your own pace.</p>\r\n','every Tuesday at 10.30am ','','',1,150,1,1,50.7320967,-1.15634249999994,'eng','2014-08-11 10:55:42','2014-09-04 16:09:49',NULL,NULL,'ryde-health-walk'),(695,'Ryde Library','','101 George Street ','','','Ryde','PO33 2JE','01983 562170','','http://www.iwight.com/Council/OtherServices/Ryde-Library/Introduction-to-Ryde-Library','<p><strong>Various activities: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The library provides a safe and welcoming space in the heart of Ryde.&nbsp; As well as providing the usual library facilities we also host Ryde Help Centre, and have regular Citizens Advice sessions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The library is&nbsp;in the process of recruiting people for a new Friends&#39;&nbsp;Group which will help raise money for the library as well as helping us to provide regular events of all kinds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please have a look at our other web pages for more information about what we do. We look forward to seeing you soon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Service Description:</strong>&nbsp;Children&#39;s and adults&#39; books, large print books, talking books on CD, DVDs, compact discs, reference collection, newspapers, photocopying, fax service, free internet access, free computer access. Ryde Library also has a gallery space for art exhibitions, and holds weekly Rhymetimes.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRyde Library is also the home of the Ryde Help Centre</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Services available at this library:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Books</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>DVDs*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CDs*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Energy Saving Monitors&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Talking Books on Cassette/CD*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Large Print&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer facilities&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Free Internet access</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Free online language courses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Over 500 free online courses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>e-magazines</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Free access to Find My Past&nbsp; family history website</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Online reference resources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Word processing&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scanning facilities&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Printing*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Colour/B&amp;W photocopying service*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fax service*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference Collection&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Local Studies Collection&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Newspapers&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Garden Refuse Sacks*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bus Pass Applications&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Teenage Area&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Children&rsquo;s Area&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Rhyme Time</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Story Time</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Gallery</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Help Centre</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Regular Events</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Knit and Natter&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This new group will meet once every 4 weeks at Ryde Library from 5.30pm to 7pm on a Wednesday evening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bring your knitting - we&#39;ll provide the refreshments - and make new friends.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suitable for all ages and abilities, this group is free of charge and there&#39;s no need to book. Please note that this is not a tuition group.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"line-height:1.6em\">Free Health Walks and Book Talks</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join us on the last Friday of the month for a walk from Ryde Library&nbsp;followed by a book chat and refreshments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This event is free but numbers are limited, so please call in to the library or phone us using the number on the contact tab above to book a place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reading Groups</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reading groups meet once a month. Please ask at the&nbsp;help desk&nbsp;or call us using the number on the contact tab above for further details.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Poetry Group</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ryde Library&rsquo;s poetry group is held on the first Monday of the month from 5pm &ndash; 6pm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you would like to join the group, please contact the library using the number on the contact tab above, or pop in to leave your details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Museum Display</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Come and study the case of artefacts and visual display, which has been provided by the Island Museum Service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Find my Past</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ryde Library has free access to ancestry website, &lsquo;Find My Past&rsquo;. Search for your ancestors in census records and use parish records to find births, marriages and deaths dating back to 1538!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPop in to the library for more information or give us a ring.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gallery space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Gallery on the library&#39;s upper floor is free to book for your art or photography exhibition. Please ask in the library for details of available dates, and for booking conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you enjoy art, come and look at a selection of paintings or photographs displayed each month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Book Sale</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our recently expanded section of withdrawn library books and other stock (CDs, DVD&rsquo;s, talking books) for sale are to be found towards the centre of the adult lending library, and feature in the library on a permanent basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Teen Book Group</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ryde Library has started a new monthly book group for 13-17 year olds.&nbsp; There&#39;s no fee, and you don&#39;t even need to be a library member!&nbsp; 2nd Tuesday of every month, 3.30pm - 4.30pm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact Diane at Ryde library for more details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LEGO Club</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LEGO Club takes place on the 2nd and 4th Tuesday of each month,&nbsp;for&nbsp;children aged 5+.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The club&nbsp;runs 3.30pm - 4.30pm in the children&#39;s library. There will be free refreshments available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s totally free of charge, and you don&#39;t need to book a place. Come along for as long as you like!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Koko the Library Bear</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Are you going on holiday? Whether you&rsquo;re camping in Devon, or backpacking in Australia, Koko the bear would love to go with you!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTake Koko on your holiday and bring him back to the library along with a photo and some information about your trip. It&rsquo;s a great chance to get your child talking about what they&rsquo;ve seen, and what books they enjoyed while they were away.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn&nbsp;the children&rsquo;s library we have a folder with all of Koko&rsquo;s adventures inside, and he is ready to go on holiday again!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSpeak to a member of staff if you would like to book a date to take Koko away with you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rhyme time for under 5s</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rhyme time is an informal session of rhymes and songs for babies and toddlers, using bells and rattles, and making lots of noise!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe &lsquo;Rhyme Time&rsquo; session, which takes place every Monday (except bank holidays), runs from 10am &ndash; 11am.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFrom 10am &ndash; 10.30am, parents are able to arrive and settle their children, whilst catching up with other parents and children alike (there will be toys and books to play with). The rhymes then begin at 10.30am for half an hour, run by a member of staff, ending the session at 11am.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe session takes place in the children&rsquo;s library and there are lovely toys, rattles and puppets for the children to enjoy. There&rsquo;s no need to book; just come along and join in! Children should be supervised by an adult at all times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Children&#39;s Storytime</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A regular half-hour storytime for younger children, (ideally between 3 &ndash; 8 years) from 11am - 11.30am every Saturday.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt&rsquo;s free to come along, and you don&rsquo;t need to book in advance. Children should be supervised by an adult at all times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Become a Storytime Superstar with our reward system! Every time you come to Storytime, receive a star on the chart. When you&#39;ve collected 4 stars, you can take home a free weekly children&#39;s DVD rental!</p>\r\n','Opening Times: Monday 9.00am - 5.30pm, Tuesday 9.00am - 5.30pm, Wednesday 10.30am - 7.00pm, Thursday CLOSED, Friday 9.00am - 5.30pm, Saturday 9.00am - 5.00pm, Sunday CLOSED','','',1,150,1,1,50.7281859,-1.1614849999999701,'eng','2014-08-11 11:07:17','2015-10-28 09:33:19',NULL,0,'ryde-library'),(696,'Ryde Library Health walk ','Richard Dent Volunteer Coordinator IOW NHS Trust','101 George Street','','','Ryde','PO33 2JE','822099 ext 6246','richard.dent@iow.nhs.uk','','<p>Short walks for beginners 1 hr maximum</p>\r\n','Friday once  per month. Meet at 10.30 ','','',1,150,1,1,50.7281859,-1.1614849999999701,'eng','2014-08-11 11:10:17','2014-09-04 16:09:26',NULL,NULL,'ryde-library-health-walk'),(697,'Ryde Table Tennis Club','Carl Prean or Mrs Rourke ','Table Tennis Centre','Smallbrook Stadium','Ashley','Ryde','PO33 4BH','562747 / 563018','','','<p>All welcome. &pound;2 a session</p>\r\n','Monday, Wednesday and Friday between 7.00 p.m and 9.30 p.m','','',1,150,1,1,50.7094246,-1.16368910000006,'eng','2014-08-11 11:57:11','2014-09-04 16:08:58',NULL,NULL,'ryde-table-tennis-club'),(698,'Senior Circle','','Elim Church','48 Albert Street','','Ryde','PO33 2SB','','','http://www.rydeelim.com/seniorcircle.htm','<p>Tea/Coffee and friendship. Free</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Senior Circle meets every Wednesday at the Church at 2:30pm for an hour or so. There are regularly about 35 people who attend each week. Throughout the year there are various trips planned. In the summer there are trips out to Rhylstone Gardens for cream teas and there are various celebration meals at Christmas etc. During the Wednesday meetings there is opportunity to meet people and make friends. Very often we will have quizzes together; speakers who talk to us about various topics and a time of getting to know each other over a cup of tea or coffee. We have great fun together and would like to welcome anyone to join us.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n','Every Wed 2.30-4','','',65,150,1,1,50.725123,-1.16074630000003,'eng','2014-08-11 12:06:28','2014-09-04 16:08:35',NULL,NULL,'senior-circle'),(699,'Short Mat Bowls','','Wootton Bridge Community Centre','Brannon Way','Wooton Bridge','Ryde','PO33 4NW','01983 884820','','','','Tues 10-1 and Fri 2-5','','',1,150,1,1,50.7243677,-1.2311995,'eng','2014-08-11 12:14:13','2014-09-04 16:07:16',NULL,NULL,'short-mat-bowls-3'),(700,'St Mary\'s Catholic Church','','High Street','','','Ryde','PO33 2RE','01983 812127','','','<p>Coffee served.</p>\r\n','Mon, Wed and Fri 11-2','','',1,150,1,1,50.7270184,-1.16295100000002,'eng','2014-08-11 12:24:29','2014-09-04 16:06:48',NULL,NULL,'st-mary-s-catholic-church'),(701,'St Michael\'s Church','','Upton Road','','','Ryde','PO33 3DX','','','','<p>Lunch Club and Senior Citizens Club.</p>\r\n','Lunch Club: alternate Thurs-book in advance. Senior Citizens Club on a Mon p.m. ','','',65,150,1,1,50.7206623,-1.16950980000001,'eng','2014-08-11 12:40:27','2014-09-04 16:05:58',NULL,NULL,'st-michael-s-church'),(702,'The Daisy Chain Club','Chris, Island Community Care','Fortis House','Cothey Way','','Ryde','PO33 1QT','01983 813000','','','<p>Meet new people, do new things and get involved in the community.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong><em>The Daisy Chain Experience</em></strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><strong><em>&lsquo;Linking People Together&rsquo;&quot;</em></strong></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Daisy Chain is a unique and award winning innovation for the clients and service users of Wight Home Care.&nbsp; Using a 7 seat wheelchair access vehicle, trips and outings are undertaken on a regular basis across the Island involving lunches, teas, shopping trips, sightseeing, picnics and much more. The members decide where they want to go and what they want to do and the Daisy Chain makes it happen!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Staffed by well trained and qualified care workers, clients can safely join in, make new friends, meet others, see and do things....have fun!&nbsp; Lots of outings planned already and more to come.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s what one national organisation have to say about us:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.thinklocalactpersonal.org.uk/Browse/commissioning/blueprint/case-study/?cid=8843&amp;sectorid=175\" target=\"_blank\">thinklocalactpersonal.org.uk</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Membership of the Daisy Chain is open to any of Wight Home Care&rsquo;s service users and dependent only on a small administrative charge to offset overhead costs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To find out more, call us on&nbsp;(01983) 813000&nbsp;and we&rsquo;ll arrange to come and meet you to explain how to join.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cost:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Annual: &pound;25</p>\r\n\r\n<p>First Trip: &pound;20</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Individual Trips: 24.00</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other Packages available</p>\r\n','','','',1,150,1,1,50.7133111,-1.1452918,'eng','2014-08-11 12:43:44','2014-09-04 16:05:08',NULL,NULL,'the-daisy-chain-club'),(703,'The Rainbow Wight Singers','Mrs Rorke','Ryde Parish Church Hall ','Queen\'s Road','','Ryde','PO33 3BG','01983 563018 ','','','<p>This is a singing group, anyone is welcome and you don&rsquo;t have to be able to sing!! The group sing all sorts, from hymns to pop to classical.</p>\r\n','Every Wednesday between 1.30 p.m. â€“ 4.00 p.m','','',1,150,1,1,50.727324,-1.16922210000007,'eng','2014-08-11 12:45:29','2014-09-04 16:02:59',NULL,NULL,'the-rainbow-wight-singers'),(704,'Townswoman\'s Guild','For afternoon Meetings: Mrs Halstead 872232   For evening meetings: Mrs Barker 873928  For Vectis meetings: Mrs J Caplan 872656','Ryde Baptist Church','The George Street Centre','George Street','Ryde','PO33 2JF','01983 872232','','http://www.townswomen.org.uk/page.asp?node=198&action=view_document&tid=7569&sec=Federation_Focus&page=1','<p>For afternoon Meetings: Mrs Halstead 872232&nbsp;&nbsp; For evening meetings: Mrs Barker 873928&nbsp; For Vectis meetings: Mrs J Caplan 872656</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are approximately 700 Guilds&nbsp;in England, Scotland, Wales, Northern Ireland, the Isle of Man and the Isle of Wight&nbsp;which meet at regular monthly meetings held in the morning, afternoon or evening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Their annual programmes include speakers, demonstrations and social activities.&nbsp;A list of some individual Guilds&#39; programme of events and their own web sites are given in the section Events, Guild Focus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Townswomen also get involved in many sports and leisure activities, from line dancing to public speaking, from drama to arts and craf