LL,'bridge-club-2'),(721,'Scrabble Club','Ian Caws','The Community Centre','George Street','','Ryde','PO33 2JF','01983 565484','iancaws@msn.com','http://newportiwsc.org.uk/iwscrab.html','<p>The Island&#39;s Scrabble Clubs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Island possesses two Scrabble Clubs, now known as Newport (Isle of Wight) Scrabble Club, and Ryde (Isle of Wight) Scrabble Club. As will be seen from the history, both Clubs, in their present form, sprang, originally, from the same source. Large numbers of players attend both Clubs, and both Clubs have had to find solutions to the same sorts of problems when deciding on their playing formats, so it should not be surprising that both are very similar. Both meet at 7.15pm for a 7.30pm start, the Ryde Club on a Monday evening, and the Newport Club on a Tuesday. Both play three games of Scrabble until 10pm. Both contain two main groups; an &quot;A&quot; group, playing &quot;Matchplay&quot; Scrabble using tournament rules taken from the ABSP, and a &quot;B&quot; group playing less competitive Scrabble for beginners, or simply for the more socially-minded.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Teams from both clubs take part in the Southern Counties&rsquo; League.</p>\r\n','every Monday evening, at 7.15pm ready for a 7.30 start','','',1,150,1,1,50.729454,-1.16150489999995,'eng','2014-08-11 17:36:20','2014-09-04 14:16:59',NULL,NULL,'scrabble-club'),(722,'Bembridge Afternoon TownsWomen  Guild','Mrs H Ransome','Bembridge Village Hall','High Street','','Bembridge','PO35 5XN','01983 874241','','','<p>The Isle of Wight Federation meets bi-monthly on the 4th Monday 10.15am at the Broadway Centre, Sandown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Federation, as well as supporting the eleven Island Guilds, hosts annually an Arts &amp; Crafts Exhibition, an inter-guild Quiz, both a Luncheon and a Christmas Concert. The Federation organises many enjoyable holidays and outings for both members, friends and husbands, and there is always a waiting list as these are so popular