INSERT INTO `services_revs` VALUES (1,27,'Bank Street Writers and another','Rod Riesco','Bank Street Unitarian Chapel','Crown Street','','Bolton','BL1 2RU','01204 692110','bswscribe@gmail.com','https://sites.google.com/site/bankstreetwriters/','<p>We are a group of writers who meet once a month in the centre of Bolton, Lancashire (UK) for readings, discussions, workshops and visits. Our regular meeting place is the historic Bank Street Unitarian Chapel in Crown Street, just off Deansgate. Members&#39; interests include poetry, fiction, scriptwriting, factual writing - in fact, almost everything you can do with the written word! Newcomers are always welcome at our informal meetings. There&#39;s no commitment to join - but if you do, you&#39;ll also receive our regular newsletter and be able to have a say in how we develop our range of activities.</p>\r\n','','','',1,150,1,1,53.580283,-2.427096,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2015-03-04 15:27:29',NULL,0,'bank-street-writers',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(2,28,'Blackrod Library book groups',NULL,'Church Street','Blackrod',NULL,'Bolton','BL6 5EQ','01204 332380','blackrod.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/BlackrodLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity; you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels.  We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader.  Monday book group: This group meets on the first Monday of the month from 2.00pm until 3.00pm. Thursday book group: This group meets on the third Thursday of the month from 6.00pm to 7.00pm.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.593887,-2.584373,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'blackrod-library-book-groups',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(3,29,'Bolton U3A','Ann Waring','St Andrew and St George URC','St George Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2BS','01204 492343','ann.waring@hotmail.co.uk','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=495&page=1','U3A stands for the University of the Third Age, which is a self-help organisation for people no longer in full time employment providing educational, creative and leisure opportunities in a friendly environment. Interest Groups meet at various venues in the town centre in these subjects; archaeology, art appreciation, basic Italian, biology, crafts (cards), creative writing, European studies, film forum, gardening, French, history, literature, local history, mah-jong, play reading, philosophy, poetry for pleasure, recorded music, scrabble, Saturday ramblers, singing for pleasure, solo whist - cards, walkabout, transactional analysis, world’s religions, women’s history. General meeting are held on the 4th Friday of the month, 2pm – 4pm. Annual Subscription; £18.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.581602,-2.432203,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(4,30,'Bromley Cross Library Book Group',NULL,'The Crescent','Bromley Cross',NULL,'Bolton','BL7 9JU','01204 332354','bromley.cross.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/BromleyCrossLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity: you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels. We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader. This group meets on the first Thursday of the month from 11.00am to 12.00 noon. Contact the library for details.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.616931,-2.418892,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bromley-cross-library-book-group',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(5,31,'Central Library book groups',NULL,'Central Library','Le Mans Crescent',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1SE','01204 333173','central.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/CentralLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity: you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels. We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader. Thursday book group: This group meets on the third Thursday of the month from 6.15pm until 7.15pm, in the central library\'s fiction area. Graphic Novel book group: The Central Library has its own graphic novel group. We\'ve got a pretty good collection of graphic novels, and we\'re working to make it even better. The group meets every four weeks on Saturday from 3.30pm - 4.30pm.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.577385,-2.431294,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'central-library-book-groups',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(6,32,'Enjoy Learning Bolton','Tom Smith',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bolton',NULL,'01204 811163','tomsmith.belmont@talk21.com','http://www.enjoy-learning.org.uk/','Enjoy Learning is a not for profit organisation that provides courses and events without examinations. Information is on our website. This is being updated over the next few weeks to include our 2012/13 programme and venue changes. We offer courses to anyone over the age of 18 but in reality the majority of people who attend are over 50 and around 60% are 60 and over. The courses and classes recruit well and we are growing year on year (we started in 2006) - we have had over 1000 enrolments this year. Most of our classes are languages, art and craft, history based, with a little music and creative writing included as well. We respond to demands and this determines our programme offer . This year however we have commissioned a report on what we can offer to stroke victims and are running a one day event in Bolton Library around older people and mobile digital devices as part of adult learners week (May 2012). We offer our courses in the north Bolton area at Delph Hill Community Centre Doffcocker, Horwich Resource Centre, St. John\'s Breightmet and Theatre Church. Fees vary.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.584441,-2.428619,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'enjoy-learning-bolton',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(7,33,'Harwood Library book groups',NULL,'Gate Fold',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL2 3HN','01204 332340','harwood.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/Harwoodlibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity; you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels.  We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader. Tuesday book group: This group meet on the second Tuesday of the month between 11am and 1pm. Thursday book group: This group meet on the second Thursday of the month between 6.15 and 7.15pm.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.600725,-2.389849,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'harwood-library-book-groups',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(8,34,'High Street Library book group',NULL,'High Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 6SZ','01204 332358','high.street.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/HighStreetLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity; you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels.  We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns reading the same book and leave their comments for the next reader. This group meets on the third Tuesday of the month from 2.30pm until 3.30pm.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.561233,-2.367136,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'high-street-library-book-group',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(9,35,'Library Link',NULL,'Central Library','Le Mans Crescent',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1SE','01204 338755','libraries@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/Specialneedsfacilities.aspx','Bolton libraries provide a free delivery service to Bolton residents who are unable to visit libraries and do not have friends or relatives who are able to collect books for them. Staff and volunteers deliver books to your home at the same time every two weeks.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries',1,150,1,1,53.577385,-2.431294,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'library-link',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(10,36,'Westhoughton Library book group',NULL,'Library Street','Westhoughton',NULL,'Bolton','BL5 3AT','01942 634640','westhoughton.library@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/WesthoughtonLibrary.aspx','Reading can be a solitary pursuit, but joining a book group can make it a social activity; you can share your thoughts about a book, meet new people, and discover books you might not have picked up otherwise. We\'ve got a few different book groups in our libraries, including one devoted to graphic novels.  We\'ve also got a few book chains, where people take turns readin