dult reading group (last Tuesday in month 2-3pm). 2nd and 4th Tuesday in mon - Councillor 5.45-6.45pm. Wednesdays - One Stop Shop - Police, councillor, Resident and Tenants Association 1.30-3.30pm.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.566516,-2.695558,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'shevington-library',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(14,40,'Salford U3A/ Salford Life Long Learning','Carole Bowler','Eccles Gateway','28 Barton Lane','Eccles','Salford','M30 0TU','0161 790 2372/0','carole@bowler.plus.com','http://www.salfordu3alll.colsal.org.uk/','U3A\' stands for The University of the Third Age. The \'Third Age\' is a time of creativity and fulfilment for older people. The \'Third Age\' refers to the periods of time after the First Age of childhood dependence and the Second Age of full time employment and parental responsibility. Salford Life Long Learning is a group of approximately 250 people within the U3A who are seeking to swell their numbers so why not join us. They have a range of groups which do different activities including: memories of Salford, discussion groups, bird watching, drama, gardening, family history, french, Mahjongg, music, poetry (Fri afternoon-please call), opera ballet on video, painting, science and maths, scrabble, walks, Eccles local history, A toast to Salford, Spanish, summer schools, no vices bridge, book club (first Wednesday of the month @ Walkden Gateway), quilting, theatre group and keep fit. Monthly general meetings take place at the Eccles Gateway.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482579,-2.338968,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-u3a-salford-life-long-learning',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(15,41,'Cadishead Library Book Group',NULL,'126 Liverpool Road','Cadishead',NULL,'Salford','M44 5AN','0161 7753457','cadishead.library@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/cadisheadlibrary.htm','The reading group at Cadishead Library meets on the seco