28 Barton Lane','Eccles','Salford','M30 0TU',NULL,'EcclesLibraryWriters@gmail.com','http://www.salford.gov.uk/ecclescr.htm','Our self-supporting group meets at Eccles Gateway to write, read and discuss our work. but always welcome enquiries.Opening times alternate Fridays from 10.00am to 12.00pm. Self referral; Contact via email; From 18 years; Both males and females.',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.482579,-2.338968,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'eccles-library-writers-group',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(22,48,'Boothstown Community Centre','Marjorie or Susan','Standfield Drive','Boothstown','Worsley','Salford','M28 1NB','0161 7999425','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/boothstowncc.htm','Activities and groups include Cafe 55 (meals start at 11.30am); Older persons meeting (first Monday of the month); Grow your Own (6 weeks from 13th Feb, Mon 2-4pm); Healthy walking group (Mon 2-4pm); Men\'s Health Group (Mon 3-4.30pm); Writers Group (Mon 7-9pm); Curling; Healthy Hips and Hearts (Tues 2-3.30pm); Weight Watchers (Tues 5-6.30pm, 6.30-8pm); Zumba (Tues 8-9pm); Lunch Club (Wed 12.30-2pm); Over 60s Club (Wed 1.30-3.30pm); Local Histories (Third Wednesday of month 7.15-9.15pm); Ladies Group (last Wednesday of month 7.30-10pm); Art group (Thurs 11.45-1.45pm); Tai Chi (Thurs 2-3pm); Yoga (Thurs 7.15-9.15pm); Transport meeting; Reading Group (Fri 2-3pm).',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.504413,-2.417325,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'boothstown-community-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(23,49,'Ordsall Community Cafe Project','','172 Tatton Street','Ordsall','','Salford','M5 3PS','0161 8726011','ordsall.cafe@hotmail.co.uk','http://www.ordsallcommunitycafe.co.uk/','<p>The project provides a friendly, inviting cafeteria and a variety of much-needed services and facilities for the local community, and those further away who find them beneficial. Our services and relaxed atmosphere are enjoyed by men and woman, babies and teenagers, old and young from all races and backgrounds - come and join them! Has classes for basic computer skills, bingo, cafeteria, community teas, gentle exercise classes, guitar lessons, hair salon, IT suite and internet access, skills and work, writers group, volunteering.</p>\r\n','','','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Ordsall-Cafe-Project-Ltd/6541793001',1,150,1,1,53.475492,-2.275304,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-06-19 11:12:30',NULL,NULL,'ordsall-community-café-project',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(24,50,'Classic Fiction Reading Group',NULL,'Bramhall Library','Bramhall Lane South','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 2DU','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/bramhalllibrary/','Enjoy reading? Read a book that you just had to talk about? Love talking about books? Whatever your reading taste we have a reading group for you. Our groups are informal and relaxed. Discover new authors and titles, widen your reading choice and meet other readers in a friendly, relaxed and informal setting. Suitable for all ages. Thu, 17 Nov 2011 to Thu, 20 Dec 2012, 18:45 - 19:45. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.359998,-2.164852,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'classic-fiction-reading-group',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(25,51,'Creative Writing for Pleasure',NULL,'Cheadle Library','Ashfield Road','Cheadle','Stockport','SK8 1BB','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/chelibinfo/','Writing for Pleasure (WFP) is for people who want to write, who derive pleasure from words and ideas, and who love reading. WFP is a writers\' workshop where you can meet other writers, tackle writing activities with others, and share feedback. Everyone is welcome to attend. Suitable for all ages. Thu, 03 Nov 2011 to Thu, 06 Dec 2012, 18:00 - 19:45. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.393393,-2.212908,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'creative-writing-for-pleasure',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(26,52,'Heald Green Library Reading Group',NULL,'Heald Green Library','Finney Lane','Heald Green','Stockport','SK8 3JB','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/heglibinfo/','Enjoy reading? Read a book that you just had to talk about? Love talking about books? Whatever your reading taste we have a reading group for you. Our groups are informal and relaxed. Discover new authors and titles, widen your reading choice and meet other readers in a friendly, relaxed and informal setting. Suitable for all ages. Tue, 01 Nov 2011 to Tue, 04 Dec 2012, 14:30 - 15:30. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.370202,-2.228756,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'heald-green-library-reading-group',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(27,53,'Heatons Library Reading Group',NULL,'Heaton Library','Thornfield Road','Heaton Moor','Stockport','SK4 3LD','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/hetlibinfo/','Enjoy reading? Read a book that you just had to talk about? Love talking about books? Whatever your reading taste we have a reading group for you. Our groups are informal and relaxed. Discover new authors and titles, widen your reading choice and meet other readers in a friendly, relaxed and informal setting. Suitable for all ages. Wed, 16 Nov 2011 to Wed, 19 Dec 2012, 18:30 - 19:30. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.416687,-2.19071,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'heatons-library-reading-group',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(28,54,'Marple Bookworms','Sharon Goddard','Marple Library','Memorial Park','Marple','Stockport','SK6 6BA','0161 217 6009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/libraryonline/libraryevents/marplebookworms','Marple Bookworms is a small group of adult readers who meet on the last Monday of every month at Marple Library. Our books are provided for us free of charge from Stockport\'s excellent library service. Our meetings are informal and relaxed, allowing everybody the opportunity to contribute. Discussion is always interesting and often lively! We often share a poem as well which is related to the book we have read; we also share \"other\" reads of the month. Anyone is welcome to join. This group meets every month, on the Last Monday, between Mon, 30 Jan, 2012 - Mon, 26 Nov, 2012 at 6.45pm - 7.45pm.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.396624,-2.061927,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'marple-bookworms',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(29,55,'Marple Writers Workshop','Sylvia Christie','Marple Library','Memorial Park','Marple','Stockport','SK6 6BA','0161 4271665','sylviachristie@googlemail.com','http://www.marple-uk.com/community/writers.htm','Currently there are about twenty members whose ages range from seventeen to seventy plus. Meetings are friendly and informal and new members are always welcome. We sometimes invite visiting speakers - these have included poets, novelists, playwrights and a publisher. Most evenings though we organise our own creative writing activities. We do not feel the need to have a formal committee so individuals and small teams of members volunteer to organise events and to run workshops which inspire the group to write at home as well as in the sessions themselves. No one is ever required to share their writing unless they are happy to do so. Abilities range from interested beginners to winners of national short story and poetry competitions. Current membership fees are £5 twice a year at Easter and in September and new attendees are invited to spend several free evenings with us before they join officially. We meet on Tuesday evenings at 7.15 for a 7.30 start in the upstairs room of Marple library.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.396624,-2.061927,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'marple-writers-workshop',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(30,56,'Non-Fiction Reading Group',NULL,'Greatermoor Library','Gladstone Street','Greatmoor','Stockport','SK2 7QF','0161 2176009',NULL,'http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/yourlibrary/yourlocallibrary/grelibinfo/','Enjoy reading? Read a book that you just had to talk about? Love talking about books? Whatever your reading taste we have a reading group for you. Our groups are informal and relaxed. Discover new authors and titles, widen your reading choice and meet other readers in a friendly, relaxed and informal setting. Suitable for all ages. Sat, 19 Nov 2011 to Sat, 15 Dec 2012, 14:15 - 15:15. Free to join.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.388433,-2.133072,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'non-fiction-reading-group',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(31,57,'The Mobile and Home Library Service',NULL,'Pheonix House','Bird Hall Lane','Cheadle Heath','Stockport','SK3 0RA','0161 4745600','homelibraryservice@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/leisureculture/libraries/morelibraryservices/mhls/','The aim of the Mobile and Home Library Service is to provide a service to members of the Stockport community who are unable to access their local library due to disability, ill health, mobility problems or caring commitments. Community Library Bus - provides a full range of library services on the premises of residential homes and sheltered accommodation. The Home Library Service - this free service is available for people living in the Stockport area who find it difficult to visit a library.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.391528,-2.184703,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-mobile-and-home-library-service',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(32,58,'Asian Elders Resource Centre',NULL,'61 Northfield Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 5JH','01204 651123','eamil@aercbolton.co.uk','http://www.aercbolton.co.uk/page/737-welcome.aspx','We provide specialised day care and day centre provision for local older Asian people. We provide a wide range of activities, and entertainment, along with useful information. Daily activities and services include: ESOL English classes, ICT with basic English, cookery class, art & craft, massage & holistic therapy, yoga, chair based exercise, swimming sessions, local & abroad trips, advocacy work, home visits (additional support), interpretation and translation service, transport facility, vegetarian and halal meal provision, chiropody service, health checks, information sharing sessions with various topics, eye tests arranged through AERC, indoor games and entertainment. The Service Users Forum, and Asian Carers Forum are our two main groups, developed to empower and support our service users and their carers. To become a member it is £10 per year.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.571009,-2.447911,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'asian-elders-resource-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(33,59,'Bolton Art Circle','George Hull','Highfield Hall','Highfield Road','Farnworth','Bolton','BL4 0AW','01204 841172','geoleshull@talktalk.net','http://www.boltonartcircle.org/','We provide facilities for artists to practice, exhibit, promote and sell their works. We arrange demonstrations and workshops, as well as informal, and formal exhibitions. We run Art Fairs at the Last Drop Village Hotel and outdoor exhibitions in Bolton Town Centre precincts. A library of books and videos are available for members. We also provide a library of books and videos for the use of our members. Meet Monday, Wednesday 2 - 4pm and Thursday 7 - 9pm for 50 weeks of the year.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.546753,-2.421173,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-art-circle',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(34,60,'Bolton Floral Art Club',NULL,'Festival Hall','Bolton Town Hall',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1RU','01204 882301','bolton@flowersnorthwest.net','http://www.flowersnorthwest.net/club/Bolton-Floral-Art-Group','We have demonstrators who design approx six arrangements which are raffled at the end of the evening. Tea and coffee is available afterwards. We have various stalls which change as the seasons progress. Each year we organise trips to gardens and the NAFAS National Show for our members. We are always pleased to welcome new members you will find us a friendly and helpful club. Meet on a Wednesday at 7:30pm in the Festival Hall, Bolton Town Hall. Cost: Membership is £27.00 per annum or visitors at £5.00.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.578098,-2.430875,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-floral-art-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(35,61,'Bolton Hobby Craft Knitting Club','Fiona Kernohan','Hobbycraft Bolton','Bolton Gate Retail Park','','Bolton','BL1 2SL','07776 141259','fiona.kernohan@hobbycraft.co.uk','http://www.hobbycraft.co.uk/bolton','<p>If you fancy meeting up and meeting new friends whilst knitting - learning the skills and showing others how to knit then pop along to the informal group that meets every Friday in the HobbyCraft Bolton store. Everyone will be made welcome. Every Friday 2pm. Cost: Free.</p>\r\n','','','',1,150,1,1,53.586063,-2.424932,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-06-06 10:30:30',NULL,NULL,'bolton-hobby-craft-knitting-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(36,62,'Bolton U3A','Ann Waring','St Andrew and St George URC','St George Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2BS','01204 492343','ann.waring@hotmail.co.uk','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=495&page=1','U3A stands for the University of the Third Age, which is a self-help organisation for people no longer in full time employment providing educational, creative and leisure opportunities in a friendly environment. Interest Groups meet at various venues in the town centre in these subjects; archaeology, art appreciation, basic Italian, biology, crafts (cards), creative writing, European studies, film forum, gardening, French, history, literature, local history, mah-jong, play reading, philosophy, poetry for pleasure, recorded music, scrabble, Saturday ramblers, singing for pleasure, solo whist - cards, walkabout, transactional analysis, world’s religions, women’s history. General meeting are held on the 4th Friday of the month, 2pm – 4pm. Annual Subscription; £18.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.581602,-2.432203,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(37,63,'Horwich Art Society','Christine Murray','Holy Trinity Parish Hall','Church Street','Horwich','Bolton','BL6 6AA','01204 669645','christine.murray520@ntlworld.com','http://www.homepage.ntlworld.com/maddogmcq/myart/has/main.htm','The Society contains a mixture of characters, all different, with varied levels of skills. The common bond is a keen interest and enthusiasm for the many aspects of art -the only criteria to join the society. We are a very friendly group so why not come and have a chat and a \'cuppa\'. Your first visit is free and you will be made very welcome. We hope to see you soon. Every Friday 7pm until 9 pm. Annual cost: £20. Weekly admission members - £1.50.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.599029,-2.539706,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'horwich-art-society',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(38,64,'Horwich