 who meet on Wednesday evenings in the Jubilee Room and aim to put on two performances a year, a Sing-Along Coffee Morning in the spring, and a Christmas concert. Art - The Art Group is a club rather than a class ranging from beginners to professionals and we all enjoy learning from each other. Watercolour is our main media but many members also use acrylics, pastels, pen and wash, and water based oils. Today we have over 70 members meeting twice a week on Tuesday and Wednesday mornings from 9.30 a.m. to 12.30 p.m. Bowling - Outdoor Bowling commences after Easter on Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday afternoons from 1.30pm until approximately 4.30pm. Indoor bowling takes place from September through till Easter on Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday afternoons from 1.30pm and Sunday mornings from 10.00am. Brigde - The weekly programme of events include Rubber and Duplicate Bridge sessions with teams of Four held in the Winter.  Caracamp - The Caracamp Section is a very friendly group of Brookdale members with touring caravans and motor homes. Dancing - This Friendly section meets every Wednesday evening from September until the last week in July for Modern Sequence dancing. Digital Photography - Our meetings are normally held in the Lesser Hall on the third Tuesday of the month, commencing at 7.30pm with an informal Question and Answer session to help all members of the Group with any aspect of their photography. This is followed by a variety of photography topics at 8.00pm. Gardening - The activities are varied, being made up of Coffee Mornings, combined with competitions and social evenings. Linguist - Made up of 5 groups. The Linguists’ Section is managed by a dedicated and enthusiastic committee who arrange a number of social events for all club members during the year.  These range from coffee mornings and tea afternoons to talks, slideshows, dinners and entertainment.  Sometimes the entertainment is provided by the Linguists themselves. Rambling - We organise 2 events per month – one ramble and one stroll. Theatre - Are you a wannabee actor? Brookdale Theatre is always on the lookout for talented actors and actresses to take part in the 5 productions we hold each year with auditions normally held in May/June. We aim to have a varied programme throughout our season (October- May). Travel - We meet socially on the third Friday of most months, with the exception of July and August, mainly for a varied programme of talks on travel related subjects. In addition to our indoor meetings we arrange tours, trips and visits, as suggested by the committee or members themselves, when sufficient numbers are involved to make them viable propositions. Generally these trips run once a month during Spring and Summer. Walrus - The Walrus Section/ Society began its life some 30 plus years ago and was formed so that Members who had ceased an active business life i.e. retired or otherwise, could meet together at the Clubhouse each month to chat together in the Bar Lounge for a budget priced Lunch and enjoy a Speaker as well and Wine - Whilst the Society still holds wine making competitions, it has developed more into a wine and food appreciation Society we hold popular wine tastings at regular intervals plus talks on food, along with a wide range of topics of general interest. Annual party nights, when we have dinner, plus entertainment and our Vice President’s evening when strawberries and cream with wine are served, also accompanied by entertainment are very popular.',NULL,'brookdaleclub','https://www.facebook.com/groups/281290235267551/',1,150,1,1,53.38381,-2.16335,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-brookdale-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(62,88,'Well Being Centre','Charlotte Baxter','Graylaw House','Chestergate',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 1LZ','0161 4747713','charlotte.baxter@stockportmind.org.uk',NULL,'Set in the centre of Stockport, the Well Being Centre is a one stop shop for anyone wanting to access 