ursday PM), Beeches Art Painting (Friday PM), NWR (bands) (Friday PM), Coffee Morning Social (Saturday AM)Lets Dance -ballroom dancing (Saturday PM) Line Dancing (Saturday PM), Credit Union Saving (Tuesday AM), Stockport Homes Surgery (Tuesday AM and Saturday AM), Councillors Surgery (Saturday AM), Stockport Homes (Oldham Road) Advice (Thursday AM), Table Top Sale Fundraising (Monthly on Saturday), Brass Band Management (Quartely on Thursday) and Co-op Members Social (Monthly on Thursday). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.429003,-2.094142,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'woodley-civic-hall',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(69,95,'Bramhall U3A','Mike Hollingworth','St Michaels Church Hall','St Michaels Avenue','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 2PG','0161 4392865','enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk','http://www.bramhallu3a.org.uk/','The aim is to share learning and leisure interests with other retired or semi-retired people in the Bramhall area as well as encouraging social interaction between members. Monthly meeting, usually on the 3rd Thursday of the month, at St. Michael\'s Church Hall with a guest speaker. More than 40 groups taking part in creative activities (e.g. art, card making, choir, embroidery), physical activities (e.g. cycling, Pilates swimming, table tennis, walking), learning activities (e.g. archaeology, languages, science) and other leisure activities (e.g. discussion groups, family history, pub quiz). The U3A also organising day\'s outings and theatre visits plus holidays. How to join - contact the membership secretary by emailing enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk or come to one of our monthly meetings. £10 per year per person to join the U3A. There is a charge of £1 to come to the monthly meetings. Some activities take place in the homes of members where there is no charge. There will be a small charge for some activities where a room has to be hired. There are obviously charges for outings, theatre visits and holidays.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.363982,-2.163215,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(70,96,'Stockport Art on Prescription','Alexandra Jackaman','Stockport Art Gallery','Wellington Road South',NULL,'Stockport','SK3 8AB','0161 4265085','alexandra.jackaman@nhs.net','http://stockportccg.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/01/3-Arts-on-Prescription.pdf','Arts On Prescription (AOP) operates in Stockport providing taught drawing and painting classes to promote positive mental health and wellbeing. Course runs for 20 weeks. Free of charge. Classes held at Stockport Art Gallery. Courses run on Tuesdays or Thursdays 10am - 12 noon. Using art to lift mood, provide relaxation, opportunities to reduce social isolation, inspiration and mental stimulation. Learn new skills and develop art in supportive environment. Taught by professional artists and supported by community mental health worker. For people experiencing mild to moderate mental health needs, such as anxiety, depression, coping with stress, bereavement, managing long term health conditions, carers, coping with changes to life circumstances, such as retirement and redundancy. All levels of artistic ability welcome including complete beginners. For Stockport residents only over age of 16. After application received, put on waiting list. Will be invited to meet with AOP co-ordinator for informal chat / assessment when reached top of waiting list and undergoing recruitment process for new course intake. To refer contact Lifestyles Services on +44 (0)161 426 5085. Can self refer or ask GP or health professional to make referral. For further information contact Arts on Prescription Co-ordinator, Alexandra Jackaman.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.408145,-2.161173,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-art-on-prescription',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(71,97,'Bramhall Art Society','Cheryl Lawn','Bramhall Village Club','2 Melbourne Road','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 1LR','0161 4837819','cheryl.lawn@talktalk.net',NULL,'Annual exhibition held each April, dates vary each year. At Bramhall Village Club, Lumb Lane. No regular tutor. Occasional demos, work shops, life classes, approx. 40 members - there may be a waiting list. Wheel chair access. Cost: membership to Village Club, membership to Art Society.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.35704,-2.159207,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-art-society',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(72,98,'High Lane Lacemakers','Janet Banks','High Lane Village Hall, off Windlehurst Road','High Lane',NULL,'Stockport','SK6 8AB','01663 764659','Janet.Banks729@btinternet.com',NULL,'Aims are to pass on the art of lacemaking to others to ensure that the art does not become extinct. The group meets from September to the end of May. Meetings are on Tuesday evenings from 7.30pm to 9.30pm.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.367358,-2.078649,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'high-lane-lacemakers',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(73,99,'Stockport Afternoon Flower Club','Chris Leigh','Woodley Civic Hall','Hyde Road','Woodley','Stockport','SK6 1QG','0161 3510267','chrisleigh@btinternet.com','http://www.nafas.org.uk/flower_club/Stockport+Afternoon+Flower+Club.html','Stockport Afternoon Flower club meets on the last Monday of the month at Woodley Civic Hall (not August or December). The meeting takes the form of a flower arranging demonstration by a qualified floral designer. Demonstrations start at 2pm and finish around 4. We also host social events and some trips. Membership is currently £39 per year which covers admission for all meetings. Visitors are welcome at an admission cost of £5 per meeting. Membership is open to all. We have a cross section of gender, race and ability and a range of ages although most of us are well over 21 - or should that be 61?',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.42474,-2.103464,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-afternoon-flower-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(74,100,'Age UK Learning and Resource Centre Farnworth',NULL,'Cross Street','Farnworth',NULL,'Bolton','BL4 7AG','01204 701525','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/Our-services/Courses--activities/','If you thought life stopped at 50, then think again. A whole new world of opportunity and learning is waiting to be discovered. Just take a look at what’s on offer in our Learning and Resources Centre. Conveniently located at the heart of Farnworth, the Centre, which has its own parking area, is only a few minutes’ walk from the town’s main bus station and shopping area. This modern, comfortable and purpose-built facility, on two-levels, has been designed in partnership with older people, and offers full access, throughout, for people with disabilities. Hundreds of older people use the Centre each week and all are assured of a warm and friendly welcome. There are courses to suit all levels and all tastes, including: computers for ABSOLUTE beginners, intermediate level computer courses, internet for beginners, digital photography and image manipulation, family history workshop. And if computers aren’t your thing, there’s lots more to choose from: painting and drawing, modern languages, an attractive choice of crafts, music keyboard and guitar classes and literature groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.548993,-2.396181,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-learning-and-resource-centre-farnworth',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(75,101,'Bolton Catholic Musical and Choral  Society','Neville Grady','Bolton Parish Church','Parish Hall','Silverwell Street','Bolton','BL1 1PS','01204 856977','secretary@bcmcs.co.uk','http://www.bcmcs.co.uk','BCMCS is an amateur operatic and choral society comprising of a Youth Theatre, Choral, and Musical sections all of which give public performances throughout the year. We welcome anyone who is interested in performing in musical theatre or choral work, or working front of house or backstage.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/groups/bcmcs/',1,150,1,1,53.578747,-2.424876,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-catholic-musical-and-choral--society',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(76,102,'Bolton Little Theatre',NULL,'Hanover Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 4TG','01204 469468','boltonlittletheatre@gmail.com','http://blt.site88.net/','Bolton Little Theatre is run entirely by volunteers. We welcome new members to come along on Monday Night at 7.30 (when a play is not on) to our Club night. This will give you an opportunity to talk to some of the department heads and see what goes on behind the scenes. There are many opportunities whatever your talents; experience is not necessary as enthusiasm is all that is needed! Set building or building of scenery takes place on Monday, Wednesday and Friday mornings from 9.30 to 12.00 and on Monday evenings from 7.30 to 9pm. Volunteers can come to any or all of these sessions. The volunteers take on the roles of House Manager, bar sales, coffee sales ticket sales (box office) and programme sales. If you have an administration talent you may want to help in the theatre office where we catalogue the archives. Also each production needs a Production Secretary to assist the director with admin. If you have a yearning to tread the boards and have no experience you can take on a small part and develop your skills and attend workshops such as those at the Little Theatre Guild conferences or courses such as those at the Lowry. Membership is £12 per season. We have limited disabled access.',NULL,'TheatreBolton','https://www.facebook.com/theatrebolton?ref=stream&hc_location=timeline',1,150,1,1,53.57745,-2.435689,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-little-theatre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(77,103,'Bolton U3A','Ann Waring','St Andrew and St George URC','St George Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2BS','01204 492343','ann.waring@hotmail.co.uk','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=495&page=1','U3A stands for the University of the Third Age, which is a self-help organisation for people no longer in full time employment providing educational, creative and leisure opportunities in a friendly environment. Interest Groups meet at various venues in the town centre in these subjects; archaeology, art appreciation, basic Italian, biology, crafts (cards), creative writing, European studies, film forum, gardening, French, history, literature, local history, mah-jong, play reading, philosophy, poetry for pleasure, recorded music, scrabble, Saturday ramblers, singing for pleasure, solo whist - cards, walkabout, transactional analysis, world’s religions, women’s history. General meeting are held on the 4th Friday of the month, 2pm – 4pm. Annual Subscription; £18.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.581602,-2.432203,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(78,104,'Enjoy Learning Bolton','Tom Smith',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bolton',NULL,'01204 811163','tomsmith.belmont@talk21.com','http://www.enjoy-learning.org.uk/','Enjoy Learning is a not for profit organisation that provides courses and events without examinations. Information is on our website. This is being updated over the next few weeks to include our 2012/13 programme and venue changes. We offer courses to anyone over the age of 18 but in reality the majority of people who attend are over 50 and around 60% are 60 and over. The courses and classes recruit well and we are growing year on year (we started in 2006) - we have had over 1000 enrolments this year. Most of our classes are languages, art and craft, history based, with a little music and creative writing included as well. We respond to demands and this determines our programme offer . This year however we have commissioned a report on what we can offer to stroke victims and are running a one day event in Bolton Library around older people and mobile digital devices as part of adult learners week (May 2012). We offer our courses in the north Bolton area at Delph Hill Community Centre Doffcocker, Horwich Resource Centre, St. John\'s Breightmet and Theatre Church. Fees vary.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.584441,-2.428619,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'enjoy-learning-bolton',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(79,105,'Farnworth Little Theatre',NULL,'Cross Street','Farnworth',NULL,'Bolton','BL4 7AJ','01204 701525','membership@farnworthlittletheatre.co.uk','http://www.farnworthlittletheatre.co.uk/','We are totally self-supporting, financing the running and upkeep of the theatre through box office takings, membership fees, charitable donations and regular fund-raising events. The theatre is run by volunteers and therefore offers many opportunities for people of all ages to get involved in a range of activities, from acting to wardrobe, lighting and sound to publicity and set-building. Why not come and meet us on one of our club nights – Thursdays from 8pm? Join us for a drink in the bar and find out more about how our Little Theatre is run.',NULL,'FLTofficial','https://www.facebook.com/FarnworthLittleTheatre',1,150,1,1,53.549402,-2.396829,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'farnworth-little-theatre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(80,106,'Sunshine House Community Centre','Barbara Nettleton','Sunshine House','Bradshawgate',NULL,'Wigan','WN1 3SN','01942 748806',NULL,'http://www.arttoartwigan.co.uk','Art to Art (Wigan) CIC is a Community Interest Company and our task is to manage Sunshine House Community Centre  and some of the groups using it. Activities include: Water colour class Tues 7- 9pm, Wed 10am- 12 noon, Thurs 1-3pm, and Fri 10am- 12noon. Water Colour with artist Tony Barrow. £3. Mixed media class 10am- 12 noon Saturdays. Oil painting class 6-8pm Thursdays. Oil Painting with artist Tony Barrow. £3. Acrylic painting class Monday 1-3pm (beginners). Acrylic and other mediums with artist Tony Barrow. £3. Portrait class Thursday 6:30-8:30pm. Jazz group performance- Mispent youth Friday 2:30pm- 4pm. Choir group Monday 6:15pm- 7:45pm. Over 60s club Friday 12:30- 2:30pm. Come and play bingo, dominos or just have a chat and a cup of tea. Alzeimers reading group Friday 10am- 12 noon. Computer courses Thursday 10am- 12 noon. All abilities. Pop in if you have a computer query, our tutor can meet your specific needs. Dance moves 11:00 am - 12:30 pm Tuesdays. 50+? Why not try dancing? Mobility, fitness and creativity for all to enjoy! This is a class for anyone who wants to dance regardless of experience. Aimed at people aged 50+. Come along and join us. £1',NULL,'ArttoArtWigan','',1,150,1,1,NULL,NULL,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'sunshine-house-community-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(81,107,'Turnpike Community Theatre','Neil Gredeki','West Leigh Village Club','West Leigh Lane','Leigh','Wigan','WN7 5JE','01942 679933',NULL,'https://en-gb.facebook.com/turnpikecommunitytheatre','A theatre group open to all members of the local community. The Turnpike Theatre group produces two theatrical productions each year. There is an open door policy and all members of the community are invited to attend and participate. Fancy trying your hand on the stage? If this isn\'t your thing, then you can work backstage, set making or design costumes. The group is open to all adults over the age of 16, whatever your ability. There is a cost of £20.00 per production or £10.00 for students, unemployed or OAP\'s.',NULL,'turnpiketheatre','https://en-gb.facebook.com/turnpikecommunitytheatre',1,150,1,1,53.51077,-2.525992,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'turnpike-community-theatre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(82,108,'Wigan Choral Society','Sara Moreton','Whitley Methodist Church','93 Spencer Road',NULL,'Wigan','WN1 2QR','01942 830766',NULL,'http://www.wiganchoral.org.uk','Wigan Choral Society rehearses at Whitley Methodist Church on Monday evenings between 7.30pm and 9.30pm and new singers are always welcome (particularly tenors!). Non-singers willing to help with staging, doorkeeping, ticket sales and suchlike are also welcome.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.560362,-2.63904,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-choral-society',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(83,109,'Wigan Piertown Chorus Barbershop Choir','Ray Naylor','Swinley Labour Club','Coppull Lane',NULL,'Wigan','WN1 2LQ','01942 726932 or','angeandraynaylor@blueyonder.co.uk','http://www.piertownchorus.com/','A male barbershop harmony choir who meet in Wigan. The Wigan Pier Town Chorus is a group of individuals who meet to sing together in four part harmony in the \'Barbershop\' style or \'Barbershop Harmony\' as it is widely known. Meet every Wednesday 8:00pm to 10:00 (free)\nThey currently meet to practice once a week at the Swinley in Wigan and also perform together at concerts or \'sing-outs\', at various locations to carry on the \'Barbershop\' tradition.',NULL,'PiertownChorus','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Friends-of-Pier-Town-Chorus/164731876914293',1,150,1,1,53.553981,-2.625605,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-piertown-chorus-barbershop-choir',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(84,110,'Anvil Street Drummers','Chris or Janet','St Mary & St John\'s Church Hall','Standishgate',NULL,'Wigan','WN1 1XL','01942 517702/07','chris.perry@tesco.net or jbrookes@anvilstreetdrummers.co.uk','http://www.anvilstreetdrummers.co.uk','We are a community drumming band, with members ranging from 10 years old to very old!  We play maracatu rhythms on drums called alfaias, and samba rhythms on drums called surdo\'s and other brazilian instruments. \"When work\'s got you stressed, here\'s a solution that\'s best, try something new, play MARACATU!\" Meet 6:30 pm - 9:00 pm on Wednesdays.',NULL,'AnvilDrummers','https://www.facebook.com/anvilstreetdrummers/info',1,150,1,1,53.549772,-2.628962,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'anvil-street-drummers',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(85,111,'Salford U3A/ Salford Life Long Learning','Carole Bowler','Eccles Gateway','28 Barton Lane','Eccles','Salford','M30 0TU','0161 790 2372/0','carole@bowler.plus.com','http://www.salfordu3alll.colsal.org.uk/','U3A\' stands for The University of the Third Age. The \'Third Age\' is a time of creativity and fulfilment for older people. The \'Third Age\' refers to the periods of time after the First Age of childhood dependence and the Second Age of full time employment and parental responsibility. Salford Life Long Learning is a group of approximately 250 people within the U3A who are seeking to swell their numbers so why not join us. They have a range of groups which do different activities including: memories of Salford, discussion groups, bird watching, drama, gardening, family history, french, Mahjongg, music, poetry (Fri afternoon-please call), opera ballet on video, painting, science and maths, scrabble, walks, Eccles local history, A toast to Salford, Spanish, summer schools, no vices bridge, book club (first Wednesday of the month @ Walkden Gateway), quilting, theatre group and keep fit. Monthly general meetings take place at the Eccles Gateway.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482579,-2.338968,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-u3a-salford-life-long-learning',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(86,112,'Beesley Green Community Centre','Gordon, Dale or Diana','Greenleach Lane','Worsley',NULL,'Salford','M28 2QW','0161 7906124','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/bees