ree-run by Health Improvement Team); Monthly Quiz; Keep fit for over 50s (Thursday 1.30-2.30); Art class (Thursday 3-5pm); Red tiger karate club; Monthly Friday Luncheon club (for people living alone); Musical Theatre.',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.446817,-2.419114,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'irlam-community-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(89,115,'Wardley Community Centre','Lesley or Diane','30 Ash Drive','Wardley','Swinton','Salford','M27 3RS','0161 7943334','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/wardley-community-centre','Activities and groups include Art classes (Tuesday 12-3pm); Tai Chi (Monday 1.30-2.30pm); Healthy Hips and Hearts; Pilates; Meditation Classes; Zumba Gold; Parent and Toddler Groups; Henshaws( for partially sighted people); Fitness Class; Band Practice; Legs, Bums and Tums; Belly Dancing; Circuit Training; Kurling; Bible Reading.',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.519404,-2.357621,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wardley-community-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(90,116,'Westwood Park Community','Bev or Cameron','Grasmere Crescent','Winton',NULL,'Eccles','M30 8DN','0161 789223 or ','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/westwood-park-community-centre','Activities and groups include Fitness for Fun (Mon 1-3pm); Zumba (7.30-8.30pm); Stroke Association-referral (Tues and Thurs 10.30-12.30pm); Senior Line Dancing (Tues 8-9.30pm); Healthy Lifestyles (Wed 10.15-12.15pm); Over 50s Butty and Bingo- Fortnightly (Wed 1.45-3.15pm); Dancing - Disabled Adults (Thurs 1-2pm); Church meetings (Thurs 7.30-9pm); Golden Oldies (Fri 2.45-4.15pm); Lowry String (7-9pm); Church (Sun 10am-12noon).',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.492607,-2.369314,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'westwood-park-community',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(91,117,'Willow Tree Centre',NULL,'94 Littleton Road','Salford',NULL,'Greater Manchester','M7 3SE','0161 2125700','willowtree@thebiglifecompany.com','http://www.willowtreehlc.co.uk/','The Willow Tree Centre in Lower Kersal, Salford, provides a range of services to improve and maintain your health and happiness. It\'s also a place for you to come along, meet other people and find out what\'s going on in your local community. Activities and groups include: B fit B Smart – gentle exercises for over 50’s. Energise With Music – music wellbeing drop in group, come & listen or join in. £3 donation. The Salford Community Carers Group - drop in for carers & their families. Legends – Stop Smoking Service Tel: +44 (0)161 2124050. Women of the World – local women’s group meet every Friday, contact Gaynor +44 (0)161 2125700. Skills & Works – Come along & get signed up with Skills & Work to get help with looking for work, training & writing C.V.’s etc',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.502472,-2.277843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'willow-tree-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(92,118,'Energise Centre',NULL,'3 Douglas Green','Charlestown',NULL,'Salford','M6 6ES','0161 2125700','energise@biglifecentres.com','http://www.energisecentre.co.uk/','The Energise Centre provides a range of services to improve and maintain your health and happiness. It\'s also a place for you to come along, meet other people and find out what\'s going on in your local community. Some of the services we offer are: Rowland\'s Pharmacy, General Practice, Drinks & Chat, Counselling service, Computer training suite, Hair Today Gone Tomorrow, Computerised Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, The Creativity Group - \"Drop in to relax using colouring/drawing, simply arty stuff & you don’t need anything, all materials provided!\" £1 donation requested.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.4975,-2.283695,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'energise-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(93,119,'The Brookdale Club',NULL,'Club House','Bridge Lane','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 3AB','0161 4392782',NULL,'http://www.thebrookdaleclub.com/','The Brookdale Club is a members social Club with many different activities, from Bowling and Bridge to Theatre and Travel. Activities include Andante - If you enjoy singing in harmony, and would like the opportunity to do so on a regular basis, then Andante may well be for you. We are a friendly, mixed choir who meet on Wednesday evenings in the Jubilee Room and aim to put on two performances a year, a Sing-Along Coffee Morning in the spring, and a Christmas concert. Art - The Art Group is a club rather than a class ranging from beginners to professionals and we all enjoy learning from each other. Watercolour is our main media but many members also use acrylics, pastels, pen and wash, and water based oils. Today we have over 70 members meeting twice a week on Tuesday and Wednesday mornings from 9.30 a.m. to 12.30 p.m. Bowling - Outdoor Bowling commences after Easter on Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday afternoons from 1.30pm until approximately 4.30pm. Indoor bowling takes place from September through till Easter on Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday afternoons from 1.30pm and Sunday mornings from 10.00am. Brigde - The weekly programme of events include Rubber and Duplicate Bridge sessions with teams of Four held in the Winter.  Caracamp - The Caracamp Section is a very friendly group of Brookdale members with touring caravans and motor homes. Dancing - This Friendly section meets every Wednesday evening from September until the last week in July for Modern Sequence dancing. Digital Photography - Our meetings are normally held in the Lesser Hall on the third Tuesday of the month, commencing at 7.30pm with an informal Question and Answer session to help all members of the Group with any aspect of their photography. This is followed by a variety of photography topics at 8.00pm. Gardening - The activities are varied, being made up of Coffee Mornings, combined with competitions and social evenings. Linguist - Made up of 5 groups. The Linguists’ Section is managed by a dedicated and enthusiastic committee who arrange a number of social events for all club members during the year.  These range from coffee mornings and tea afternoons to talks, slideshows, dinners and entertainment.  Sometimes the entertainment is provided by the Linguists themselves. Rambling - We organise 2 events per month – one ramble and one stroll. Theatre - Are you a wannabee actor? Brookdale Theatre is always on the lookout for talented actors and actresses to take part in the 5 productions we hold each year with auditions normally held in May/June. We aim to have a varied programme throughout our season (October- May). Travel - We meet socially on the third Friday of most months, with the exception of July and August, mainly for a varied programme of talks on travel related subjects. In addition to our indoor meetings we arrange tours, trips and visits, as suggested by the committee or members themselves, when sufficient numbers are involved to make them viable propositions. Generally these trips run once a month during Spring and Summer. Walrus - The Walrus Section/ Society began its life some 30 plus years ago and was formed so that Members who had ceased an active business life i.e. retired or otherwise, could meet together at the Clubhouse each month to chat together in the Bar Lounge for a budget priced Lunch and enjoy a Speaker as well and Wine - Whilst the Society still holds wine making competitions, it has developed more into a wine and food appreciation Society we hold popular wine tastings at regular intervals plus talks on food, along with a wide range of topics of general interest. Annual party nights, when we have dinner, plus entertainment and our Vice President’s evening when strawberries and cream with wine are served, also accompanied by entertainment are very popular.',NULL,'brookdaleclub','https://www.facebook.com/groups/281290235267551/',1,150,1,1,53.38381,-2.16335,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-brookdale-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(94,120,'Hazel Grove Civic Hall','Tracey Banham or Kadijatu Mansaray','London Road','Hazel Grove',NULL,'Stockport','SK7 4DF','0161 4742200','tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk or kadijatu.mansaray@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: Hazel Grove TWG Craft Club (Wednesday PM), Gardening Club Meetings and Showing (Tuesday PM), Gardening Club Committee Meetings (Wednesday PM), North Cheshire Family History Meetings (Tuesday PM), H.G.C.A. Social Section Coffee Morning (Thursday AM), H.G.C.A. Social Section Tea Dance (Wednesday AM), H.G.C.A. Social Section Social Dance (Saturday PM), H .G. Brass Band Band Practice (Thursday PM), Poynton Youth Brass Band Meeting (Wednesday PM), Knitting Club Meeting (Thursday PM), H.G. Royal British Legion Meeting (Wednesday PM), High Peak Woodturners Meetings and Demonstration (Friday PM), Stockport Philatelic Society Meetings (Friday PM), Stockport Walking and Outdoor Group Meeting (Wednesday PM), H. G. Dance Group Sequence Dancing (Friday AM), Craft Club (Saturday AM), Yoga Training (Wednesday AM), Bunkai Karate Training (Wednesday PM), Bunkai Karate Karate Training (Monday PM), Grove School of Dance - dance lessons (Tuesday AM/PM and Thursday AM/PM), K. D. Dancing - sequence dancing (Thursday PM), H.G. Ward Committee Meeting (Tuesday PM) Hula Hoop Classes - dance lessons (Wed morn 9.45 am to 11am), and Sunshine Circle - meetings and chat (Wednesday AM). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.379632,-2.120795,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'hazel-grove-civic-hall',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(95,121,'Heaton Chapel Community Centre','Tracey Banham or Kadijatu Mansaray','Broadstone Road','Heaton Chapel',NULL,'Stockport','SK4 5JD','0161 4742200','tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk or kadijatu.mansaray@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: Playgroup - term time (Mon-Fri AM/PM), Snooker - October-April (Mon -Thurs PM), Cards (Monday/Saturday PM), Slimming Club (Tuesday PM), Bosnia Society (Tuesday PM), Whist (Thursday PM), Band practice (Thursday PM), and Stockport Recorded Music Club (Friday PM). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.431212,-2.169261,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'heaton-chapel-community-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(96,122,'Bramhall Recorded Music Society','Brenda Scragg','Quarker Meeting House','96 Station Road','Cheadle Hulme','Stockport','SK8 7BG','0161 980829','brenda.scragg@ntlworld.com','http://www.thefrms.co.uk/affprogs/bramhall%202012.htm','The Bramhall Recorded Music Society meets weekly from September to June on Tuesdays from 8.00pm-10pm at the Friends Meeting House 91 Station Road, Cheadle Hulme SK8 7BG. Annual Subscriptions are £7 + £1 for each meeting attended. Programmes are mostly given by members on a theme of their choice. A printed programme is available for Sept - Dec and Jan - June. Occasional social events are arranged. Most of our members are retired. We are a small group c.28 members and we are always looking for new members.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.372816,-2.183013,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-recorded-music-society',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(97,123,'BAM (Brinnington Arts and Music)','Becky Marsh','Lapwing Centre','Lapwing Lane','Brinnington','Stockport','SK5 8LF','07813 198556','bamdrummers@gmail.com','http://www.bamdrummers.moonfruit.com/','We are a community group for all ages and abilities focussed on making, playing and performing music. We also run dance and arts workshops. This provides our members with confidence, self esteem, wellbeing through creativity and music making. We perform at community events as a band. We currently run a session at the Lapwing Leisure Centre, Brinnington, Stockport, every Wednesday from 5-7pm. The building is totally accessible and all are welcome. The workshop is free but with a suggested \'sub\' of 50p.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bam-Brinnington-Arts-and-Music/342097782502196',1,150,1,1,53.432516,-2.13035,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bam-brinnington-arts-and-music',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(98,124,'Age UK Bolton',NULL,'72/74 Ashburner Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1TN','01204 382411','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/','Activities and services include Aromatherapy and Reflexology Services - to relieve stress, tension or just to pamper yourself. Café - serving an excellent choice of good quality meals, snacks, drinks in a welcoming and comfortable environment. Community-based Services and Activities - community-based services and activities, including, befriending services; keep fit and other exercise classes; special interest and hobby groups; lunch and leisure clubs etc. to enable and support older people to remain active (physically and mentally) and independent within their own communities. Counselling - confidential counselling services provided by professionally trained and qualified counsellors. Courses and Activities - an attractive and imaginative choice of short courses and activities at our Learning and Resources Centre. Fundraising - help us to raise funds to provide services/activities, with and behalf of older people in Bolton. \"Handyman\" (Practical Support) Service - for good quality, reliable and affordable help with decorating, gardening and small repairs. Information and Advice/Legal Advice Service - free, confidential advice on all issues, including legal matters, affecting older people. Insurance and Other Products - The Age UK Group offers a range of products and services tailor-made for the over 50s. Volunteering Opportunities - find out how you can join our team of first class volunteers. Walking clubs - offering a choice of demanding and less demanding walks. Wheelchair Hire - short-term loans. Will-Making Service - available at a specially negotiated price. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.576827,-2.432148,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-bolton',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(99,125,'Age UK Learning and Resource Centre Farnworth',NULL,'Cross Street','Farnworth',NULL,'Bolton','BL4 7AG','01204 701525','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/Our-services/Courses--activities/','If you thought life stopped at 50, then think again. A whole new world of opportunity and learning is waiting to be discovered. Just take a look at what’s on offer in our Learning and Resources Centre. Conveniently located at the heart of Farnworth, the Centre, which has its own parking area, is only a few minutes’ walk from the town’s main bus station and shopping area. This modern, comfortable and purpose-built facility, on two-levels, has been designed in partnership with older people, and offers full access, throughout, for people with disabilities. Hundreds of older people use the Centre each week and all are assured of a warm and friendly welcome. There are courses to suit all levels and all tastes, including: computers for ABSOLUTE beginners, intermediate level computer courses, internet for beginners, digital photography and image manipulation, family history workshop. And if computers aren’t your thing, there’s lots more to choose from: painting and drawing, modern languages, an attractive choice of crafts, music keyboard and guitar classes and literature groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.548993,-2.396181,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-learning-and-resource-centre-farnworth',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(100,126,'Bolton U3A','Ann Waring','St Andrew and St George URC','St George Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2BS','01204 492343','ann.waring@hotmail.co.uk','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=495&page=1','U3A stands for the University of the Third Age, which is a self-help organisation for people no longer in full time employment providing educational, creative and leisure opportunities in a friendly environment. Interest Groups meet at various venues in the town centre in these subjects; archaeology, art appreciation, basic Italian, biology, crafts (cards), creative writing, European studies, film forum, gardening, French, history, literature, local history, mah-jong, play reading, philosophy, poetry for pleasure, recorded music, scrabble, Saturday ramblers, singing for pleasure, solo whist - cards, walkabout, transactional analysis, world’s religions, women’s history. General meeting are held on the 4th Friday of the month, 2pm – 4pm. Annual Subscription; £18.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.581602,-2.432203,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:00'),(101,127,'Halliwell History Society','Margaret Koppens','St Luke\'s Church','Chorley Old Road',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 3BE','01204 597644',NULL,'http://www.halliwell-lhs.co.uk/index.php','We are a Local History Group based in Halliwell, Bolton, who were intent on recording and keeping alive the history of the Halliwell Township. We meet on the last Tuesday of t