information to allow people to make informed choices and decisions. Bright Days Programme - offering a wide range of activities to encourage you to feel good and have fun. Care Homes Admission Service - help, advice and support for you and your family when choosing a care home. Direct Payments - Age UK Wigan Borough has been funded to help people in use of Direct Payments. Handyperson service - helping you maintain independence and improve safety and security in the home. Hospital Information & Support Service - short term support for older people who are admitted to the Royal Albert Edward Infirmary, Wigan. Information & advice - available to people aged 50 and over, their relatives, friends and carers in the Borough of Wigan. Paveways Plus - Information and advice service for people with a disability and their carers. Products and  services - A range of products and services tailor-made for the over 50s. Starting Point - a telephone helpline offering information and support to people aged 50 and over and  Support at Home Services - offering practical and emotional support in order for older people to retain their independence and volunteering - volunteers undertake a wide range of activities in our offices and in the community.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.548295,-2.633729,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-wigan',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(111,137,'Contact the Elderly','Kathleen Sheridan',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Greater Manchester',NULL,'0800 716543 or ','info@contact-the-elderly.org.uk','http://www.contact-the-elderly.org.uk/','Contact the Elderly is the only national charity solely dedicated to tackling loneliness and social isolation among older people. We aim to do this by organising monthly Sunday afternoon tea parties for small groups of older people (aged 75+) who live alone, and volunteers within their local community, offering a regular and vital friendship link every month. Each older person is collected from their home by a volunteer driver and taken to a volunteer host’s home for the afternoon. The group is warmly welcomed by a different host each month, but the drivers remain the same which means that over the months and years, acquaintances turn into friends and loneliness is replaced by companionship. Our tea parties are a real lifeline of friendship for our older members who have little or no contact with any family or friends. They bring people of all ages together, develop fulfilling friendships and support networks, and give everyone involved something to look forward to each month.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.497848,-2.318776,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'contact-the-elderly',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(112,138,'Pensioners Centre','Marian Lachford',NULL,'356 Manchester Road','Tydlesley','Wigan','M29 7DY','01942 701165',NULL,NULL,'Activities include a Luncheon Club for people over the age of 60 in need of companionship. It runs on a Wednesday 11.00am to 1.15pm. The cost is £2.60 for a 2 course meal, plus 20p for tea or coffee. Come along for a game of domino\'s or cards, followed by lunch. Astley Pensioners Social Club meet on Tuesdays 6pm - 9pm to chat, have a cup of tea and play bingo. There are some organised group outings. There is a £5.00 subscription charge per year, plus £2.55 for bingo and refreshments.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.499118,-2.460147,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pensioners-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(113,139,'Sunshine House Community Centre','Barbara Nettleton','Sunshine House','Bradshawgate',NULL,'Wigan','WN1 3SN','01942 748806',NULL,'http://www.arttoartwigan.co.uk','Art to Art (Wigan) CIC is a Community Interest Company and our task is to manage Sunshine House Community Centre  and some of the groups using it. Activities include: Water colour class Tues 7- 9pm, Wed 10am- 12 noon, Thurs 1-3pm, and Fri 10am- 12noon. Water Colour with artist Tony Barrow. £3. Mixed media