LL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482985,-2.337389,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-salford',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(119,145,'Salford U3A/ Salford Life Long Learning','Carole Bowler','Eccles Gateway','28 Barton Lane','Eccles','Salford','M30 0TU','0161 790 2372/0','carole@bowler.plus.com','http://www.salfordu3alll.colsal.org.uk/','U3A\' stands for The University of the Third Age. The \'Third Age\' is a time of creativity and fulfilment for older people. The \'Third Age\' refers to the periods of time after the First Age of childhood dependence and the Second Age of full time employment and parental responsibility. Salford Life Long Learning is a group of approximately 250 people within the U3A who are seeking to swell their numbers so why not join us. They have a range of groups which do different activities including: memories of Salford, discussion groups, bird watching, drama, gardening, family history, french, Mahjongg, music, poetry (Fri afternoon-please call), opera ballet on video, painting, science and maths, scrabble, walks, Eccles local history, A toast to Salford, Spanish, summer schools, no vices bridge, book club (first Wednesday of the month @ Walkden Gateway), quilting, theatre group and keep fit. Monthly general meetings take place at the Eccles Gateway.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482579,-2.338968,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-u3a-salford-life-long-learning',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(120,146,'Start in Salford','Danny Morrell','Brunswick House','62 Broad Street',NULL,'Salford','M6 5BZ','0161 351 6000','danny.morrell@startinsalford.org.uk','http://www.startinsalford.org.uk','Start is a unique city-wide arts project. The project provides arts training and opportunities for people of all ages at risk of social exclusion and mental ill health living in the Salford area. START has a studio art base and photographic darkroom facilities which provides members with the opportunity to work in a range of artistic disciplines alongside professional artists. START runs studio based workshops, outreach projects and residencies, an educational and cultural programme, an exhibition programme and regularly has guest artists and other arts/community groups using its facilities. Opportunities are provided to work in a variety of different media from drawing, painting, sculpture, ceramics, mosaic, textiles and printmaking to photography, video, creative writing, drama and music. Members can access these facilities and activities free of charge. Start over Fifty is a friendly and supportive community project offering a creative start for people over fifty. We use easily accessible community venues all over Salford and our tutors will encourage you every step of the way.You can get involved in a variety of creative activities such as drawing, painting, digital photography, creative writing and, to keep active, Tai Chi, Belly dancing and more... We run our sessions for a year in each new venue – come along to a free taster session and if you like it, stay on. A new block of sessions begins every three months. Sessions are once a week, for two hours, and a small weekly fee gets you all the materials and equipment you need. Professional artists and tutors will encourage and support you whether you have years of experience or none at all. New starters are always welcome. Some of the local venues used for these sessions are: Walkden Gateway, Walkden Guild Hall, St James\' Church Hall, Queen Alexandra Close in Ordsall, Tower Blocks in Eccles, Ranulph Court,',NULL,'StartinSalford','https://www.facebook.com/StartinSalford',1,150,1,1,53.491074,-2.282798,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'start-in-salford',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(121,147,'Beesley Green Community Centre','Gordon, Dale or Diana','Greenleach Lane','Worsley',NULL,'Salford','M28 2QW','0161 7906124','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifes