itate earlier diagnosis and treatment. It does this by developing teams led by local people to identify and engage priority groups in their communities. They raise awareness, and educate people about recognising and presenting cancer symptoms/ cardiovascular disease. The work is done together with Cancer/ Cardiovascular networks and screening programmes, while supporting primary care in interpretation of best practice.  Time Banking : \"...time to give and take.\" Aims to strengthen communities by drawing people together and by developing mutual friendships and support. Time Banking is open to everyone, of any background, age or ability. Everyone has skills and experience to offer.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.492903,-2.274601,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'unlimited-potential',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(127,153,'Irlam Community Centre','Pat or Joan','Locklands Lane, off Ferry Hill Road','Irlam',NULL,'Salford','M44 6RB','0161 7762832','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/irlam-community-centre','Activities and groups include Zumba; Legs bums and tums; Line dancing (beginners welcome); Age 19+ yoga; Councillors surgery (second and fourth Tuesday of the month ); Tai Chi; Weight Watchers; A New You (free-run by Health Improvement Team); Monthly Quiz; Keep fit for over 50s (Thursday 1.30-2.30); Art class (Thursday 3-5pm); Red tiger karate club; Monthly Friday Luncheon club (for people living alone); Musical Theatre.',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.446817,-2.419114,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'irlam-community-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(128,154,'Rainbow Rooms Community Centre','Tracy or Sharon','259 Liverpool Road','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0QN','0161 7898091','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/rainbow-rooms-commun