lford.gov.uk/eccleslibrary.htm','Coffee morning first Friday of the month. 10.30-12. No need to book. Donations of 50p asked for tea and coffee.',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.482602,-2.339239,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'eccles-library-',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(138,164,'Irlam Library ',NULL,'Hurst Fold','Liverpool Road','Irlam','Salford','M44 6FD','0161 7753566','irlam.library@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/irlamlibrary.htm','Coffee Morning every Friday. 10.30-12.30, no need to book. Donations of 50p asked for tea and coffee.\n',NULL,'Libraries_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.450242,-2.415671,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'irlam-library-',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(139,165,'The Brookdale Club',NULL,'Club House','Bridge Lane','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 3AB','0161 4392782',NULL,'http://www.thebrookdaleclub.com/','The Brookdale Club is a members social Club with many different activities, from Bowling and Bridge to Theatre and Travel. Activities include Andante - If you enjoy singing in harmony, and would like the opportunity to do so on a regular basis, then Andante may well be for you. We are a friendly, mixed choir who meet on Wednesday evenings in the Jubilee Room and aim to put on two performances a year, a Sing-Along Coffee Morning in the spring, and a Christmas concert. Art - The Art Group is a club rather than a class ranging from beginners to professionals and we all enjoy learning from each other. Watercolour is our main media but many members also use acrylics, pastels, pen and wash, and water based oils. Today we have over 70 members meeting twice a week on Tuesday and Wednesday mornings from 9.30 a.m. to 12.30 p.m. Bowling - Outdoor Bowling commences after Easter on Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday afternoons from 1.30pm until approximately 4.30pm. Indoor bowling takes place from September through till Easter on Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday afternoons from 1.30pm and Sunday mornings from 10.00am. Brigde - The weekly programme of events include Rubber and Duplicate Bridge sessions with teams of Four held in the Winter.  Caracamp - The Caracamp Section is a very friendly group of Brookdale members with touring caravans and motor homes. Dancing - This Friendly section meets every Wednesday evening from September until the last week in July for Modern Sequence dancing. Digital Photography - Our meetings are normally held in the Lesser Hall on the third Tuesday of the month, commencing at 7.30pm with an informal Question and Answer session to help all members of the Group with any aspect of their photography. This is followed by a variety of photography topics at 8.00pm. Gardening - The activities are varied, being made up of Coffee Mornings, combined with competitions and social evenings. Linguist - Made up of 5 groups. The Linguists’ Section is managed by a dedicated and enthusiastic committee who arrange a number of social events for all club members during the year.  These range from coffee mornings and tea afternoons to talks, slideshows, dinners and entertainment.  Sometimes the entertainment is provided by the Linguists themselves. Rambling - We organise 2 events per month – one ramble and one stroll. Theatre - Are you a wannabee actor? Brookdale Theatre is always on the lookout for talented actors and actresses to take part in the 5 productions we hold each year with auditions normally held in May/June. We aim to have a varied programme throughout our season (October- May). Travel - We meet socially on the third Friday of most months, with the exception of July and August, mainly for a varied programme of talks on travel related subjects. In addition to our indoor meetings we arrange tours, trips and visits, as suggested by the committee or members themselves, when sufficient numbers are involved to make them viable propositions. Generally these trips run once a month during Spring and Summer. Walrus - The Walrus Section/ Society began its life some 30 plus years ago and was formed so that Members who had ceased an active business life i.e. retired or otherwise, could meet together at the Clubhouse each month to chat together in the Bar Lounge for a budget priced Lunch and enjoy a Speaker as well and Wine - Whilst the Society still holds wine making competitions, it has developed more into a wine and food appreciation Society we hold popular wine tastings at regular intervals plus talks on food, along with a wide range of topics of general interest. Annual party nights, when we have dinner, plus entertainment and our Vice President’s evening when strawberries and cream with wine are served, also accompanied by entertainment are very popular.',NULL,'brookdaleclub','https://www.facebook.com/groups/281290235267551/',1,150,1,1,53.38381,-2.16335,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-brookdale-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(140,166,'Bramhall U3A','Mike Hollingworth','St Michaels Church Hall','St Michaels Avenue','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 2PG','0161 4392865','enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk','http://www.bramhallu3a.org.uk/','The aim is to share learning and leisure interests with other retired or semi-retired people in the Bramhall area as well as encouraging social interaction between members. Monthly meeting, usually on the 3rd Thursday of the month, at St. Michael\'s Church Hall with a guest speaker. More than 40 groups taking part in creative activities (e.g. art, card making, choir, embroidery), physical activities (e.g. cycling, Pilates swimming, table tennis, walking), learning activities (e.g. archaeology, languages, science) and other leisure activities (e.g. discussion groups, family history, pub quiz). The U3A also organising day\'s outings and theatre visits plus holidays. How to join - contact the membership secretary by emailing enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk or come to one of our monthly meetings. £10 per year per person to join the U3A. There is a charge of £1 to come to the monthly meetings. Some activities take place in the homes of members where there is no charge. There will be a small charge for some activities where a room has to be hired. There are obviously charges for outings, theatre visits and holidays.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.363982,-2.163215,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(141,167,'Bramhall Photographic Society','Gordon or Barbara Johnson','Bramhall Village Club','Limb Lane','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 1LR','01663 734996','burtonjoh@tiscali.co.uk','http://www.bramhallphoto.weebly.com/','Bramhall photographic society aims to promote enjoyment of amateur photography. We meet on Monday evenings 7.45 to 10pm upstairs at the Bramhall Village Club. We have a mixture of competitions, speakers and technical evenings. Annual fee £24.00 and 50p per meeting.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.35704,-2.159207,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-photographic-society',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(142,168,'Stockport Care Schemes','Breda Johnson','South Reddish Clinic','Reddish Road','Reddish','Stockport','SK5 7QU','0161 4778782/07','breda.johnson@stockportcareschemes.org.uk','http://www.stockportcareschemes.org.uk','The aim of our schemes is to introduce volunteers to vulnerable people and hard pressed carers who need a little extra help and support. We provide transport for people with poor mobility so that they may attend medical appointments and some social activities. We arrange visits for the elderly and  help for the housebound.  Befrienders / carers also support various social and activities groups. Anyone can refer themselves to us if they fit the criteria stated here. Services offered: transport, befriending and activity groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.422318,-2.156517,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-care-schemes',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(143,169,'Stockport Older Peoples Forum','Lucie Newsam','The Hatworks','Wellington Mill','Wellington Road South','Stockport','SK3 0EU','0161 480 1211','lucie.newsam@ageukstockport.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/stockport/events/older-peoples-forum/','Health and Social Care, Older People. Stockport Older People’s Forum provides an exciting opportunity for residents of Stockport to have their say on issues that directly relate to them locally as they grow older. Individuals and groups come together to raise awareness of older people’s issues, working to affect and promote positive change in the Borough and to help make sure age is on everyone’s agenda! YOU can get involved in lots of different ways, as little or as much as you like to ensure older people’s voices are heard and to discuss, express and develop views on a wide range of social issues, needs and services. You can join the Forum as an individual or be a representative of your community group – to input into the Forum the issues that arise within your social group; distribute information, gather views from your group members, neighbours, and peers. You can also be part of a task group – these can vary according to the need that exists focusing around various areas such as, transport, health, disability, intergenerational work, diversity, communications and could involve attending relevant conferences, consultations and meetings. In return you will receive regular updates from the Forum through a newsletter, opportunities to be involved in large scale consultations, the chance to join in campaigns and bring your issues to the forefront! Be part of a local network bringing together local residents with agencies to provide solutions to local concerns. The Forum welcomes any new members who would be interested in 