welcome ... just come along to any of our events. The annual subscription of £5 per person is collected in January each year. Activities include: Sunday walks, cycle rides, family walks, Wednesday walks. Other activities are arranged from time to time and will be published on our website and in the programme. These may include: theatre trips, meals, barbecues, cinema visits, walking, cycling & skiing holidays.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.406754,-2.158843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-walking-and-outdoor-group',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(164,190,'Contact the Elderly','Kathleen Sheridan',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Greater Manchester',NULL,'0800 716543 or ','info@contact-the-elderly.org.uk','http://www.contact-the-elderly.org.uk/','Contact the Elderly is the only national charity solely dedicated to tackling loneliness and social isolation among older people. We aim to do this by organising monthly Sunday afternoon tea parties for small groups of older people (aged 75+) who live alone, and volunteers within their local community, offering a regular and vital friendship link every month. Each older person is collected from their home by a volunteer driver and taken to a volunteer host’s home for the afternoon. The group is warmly welcomed by a different host each month, but the drivers remain the same which means that over the months and years, acquaintances turn into friends and loneliness is replaced by companionship. Our tea parties are a real lifeline of friendship for our older members who have little or no contact with any family or friends. They bring people of all ages together, develop fulfilling friendships and support networks, and give everyone involved something to look forward to each month.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.497848,-2.318776,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'contact-the-elderly',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(165,191,'Bolton Cardiac Support Service','Mr David Houghton ','Friends Meeting House','Silverwell Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1PP','01204 300661',NULL,'http://www.boltoncardiacsupportService.org','The Bolton Cardiac Support Service (BCSG) meets at the Friends Meeting House every third Wednesday to offer friendship and support to people who are experiencing or recovering from some form of coronary (heart) illness such as angina, heart attack, heart surgery or ischemic heart disease. (The welcome also extends to their \"carer\" - spouse, partner, family member or friend). Our monthly meetings cover subjects such as diet, medication, exercise and more. Each month we have a speaker (cardiologist, doctor, pharmacist, cardiac rehabilitation specialist, etc.) who gives a brief presentation which is then followed by a question and answer period. We also occasionally have some non-medical topics and social meetings. So, if you think the BCSG might be of help to you, then why not come along and join us. You have nothing to lose but perhaps a lot to gain!',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.57894,-2.424902,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-cardiac-support-service',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(166,192,'Bolton Stop Smoking Service',NULL,'Crompton Health Centre','Crompton Way',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 8UP','01204 462345','stopsmoking@bolton.nhs.uk','http://www.stopsmokingbolton.co.uk/index.aspx','Did you know that you are much more likely to quit successfully if you use the Bolton NHS Stop Smoking Service than with will power alone? Free of charge services are available right on your doorstep where you can find practical support to help you stop smoking. You’ll find details of your Local Stop Smoking Centres on the website provided.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.597432,-2.41518,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-stop-smoking-service',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(167,193,'Bolton Voluntary Service Diabetes UK','','The Holiday Inn','Bolton Centre','1 Higher Bridge Street','Bolton','BL1 2EW','01204 655 555','','http://bolton.diabetesukgroup.org/home/home.asp','<p>Diabetes UK, the charity for people with diabetes, has a network of over 350 voluntary Services throughout the UK. The Bolton Service is one of these Services and supports people in the local area and covers the Bolton and Bury areas of Lancashire. The Service aims to provide support, help, companionship, education and information for people living with diabetes. We welcome everyone affected by diabetes, whether newly diagnosed or longer term, along with carers, friends and family. We have speakers on a variety of relevant topics and social events, too. There is always the opportunity to talk to other members of the Service, ask questions and share experiences. All meetings are on Wednesdays at: 7.30pm at Holiday Inn, Bolton Town Centre, unless otherwise stated.</p>\r\n','','','',1,150,1,1,53.582646,-2.4292,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-06-06 13:28:04',NULL,NULL,'bolton-voluntary-service-diabetes-uk',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(168,194,'Bolton West Stroke Service','Bob and Ann Prideaux or Brenda Nixon\n','Horwich Resource Centre','Beaumont Road','Horwich','Bolton','BL6 7BG','01942 793 266 o','robert.prideaux@ntlworld.com or mrsbrendanixon@yahoo.co.uk ','http://www.stroke.org.uk/support/bolton-west-stroke-Service','Meet 1pm - 3pm on the first and third Thursdays of each month. Club activities include social, exercise, craft, peer support and outings.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.600478,-2.54518,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-west-stroke-service',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(169,195,'Expert Patient Programme','Judith Brown','Expert Patient Programme Co-ordinator','District Nurses Department','Waters meeting Road','Bolton','BL1 8TU','01204 463009','judith.brown@bolton.nhs.uk','http://www.expertpatients.co.uk/','The Expert Patients Programme is an initiative by the NHS to get patients more actively involved, and to support them in dealing with the day to day problems they face. It includes providing local courses and recruiting volunteer tutors with long-term conditions to run future courses. The course is based on a tried and tested model for chronic disease self-management courses, which are led by people who themselves are living with a chronic condition. The free service is open to participants who live with one or more long-term health conditions in Bolton. The referral pathway is followed by patients completing a EPP application form to enrol them on the 6 week course then patients are sent a EPP information pack or a EPP referral form just for health professionals to complete.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/EPPCIC',1,150,1,1,53.591029,-2.425134,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'expert-patient-programme',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(170,196,'Parkinson\'s Disease Society Bolton','Jean Donagain','Jubilee Centre','Darley Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 3DX','01942 730176',NULL,'http://www.parkinsons.org.uk/local-to-you/find-local-branches/north-west/bolton.aspx','We have a busy Service which covers Bolton and surrounding areas (members do not have to be Bolton residents). We have two monthly meetings - one in the evening at the Jubilee Centre, Darley St. Bolton and one at the Leverhulme Centre, Long Lane, Bolton. The meetings are a way for members to get together and enjoy entertainment or a speaker. There is no charge for membership but we ask people to join our national body - Parkinson\'s UK - at a cost of £4.00. People who attend the Leverhulme meeting pay £1.00 towards room rental and refreshments. The branch has trips and outings and a \"buddy Service\" network where smaller Services meet together to socialise. The branch sponsors a series  of exercise Services each week at the Leverhulme gym and the Arena at the Reebok stadium in Horwich. Our membership is made up of people with Parkinson\'s and people who care for them. - also people who have formerly been carers. Our carers\' support Service meets monthly in Bolton Town Centre.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.589198,-2.440418,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'parkinsons-disease-society-bolton',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(171,197,'The British Kidney Patient Association (BKPA)',NULL,'3 The Windmills','St Mary’s Close','Turk Street','Alton','GU34 1EF','01420 541424',NULL,'http://www.britishkidney-pa.co.uk/','The British Kidney Patient Association is a well established charity working to improve the quality of life for adults and children with kidney disease. We provide support, information and financial assistance to patients and families at any stage of life,  when dialysis or transplantation is underway, and kidney disease is having a serious impact upon daily life. Everything we do is focussed on improving life for kidney patients. What often sets us apart from other charities is the level of financial support that we can give to patients, families and kidney units during times of financial difficulty.',NULL,'The_BKPA','https://www.facebook.com/groups/TheBKPA/',1,150,1,1,51.1475,-0.973908,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-british-kidney-patient-association-bkpa',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(172,198,'The National Kidney Federation Helpline','Pauline or Julie','The Point','Coach Road','Shireoaks, Worksop','Notts','S81 8BW','0845 601 02 09','helpline@kidney.org.uk','http://www.kidney.org.uk/','The NKF is the national Kidney Patient charity in the United Kingdom. The Federation’s aim throughout the UK is to promote both the best renal medical practice and treatment, and the health of persons suffering from Chronic Kidney Disease (CKD) or Established Renal Failure (ERF). The NKF also supports the related needs of those relatives and friends who care for kidney patients. The NKF Helpline provides assistance to patients, carers, family, friends and medical professionals. Seek advice, obtain literature, get help, all from the one Helpline number (details below). It is open for calls from 9am to 5pm, Monday to Friday.',NULL,'NKF_UK','https://www.facebook.com/pages/NKF-National-Kidney-Federation/138351706194949?v=info#',1,150,1,1,53.323112,-1.159271,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-national-kidney-federation-helpline',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(173,199,'Self Management Workshops and Courses - Arthritis Care',NULL,'Woodlands Conference Centre','Southport Road',NULL,'Chorley','PR7 1QR','01924 882156','NorthEngland@arthritiscare.org.uk','http://www.arthritiscare.org.uk/InyourArea/NorthEngland/Workshopscourses','Arthritis Care offers free workshops and courses to help people with arthritis learn how to cope with their condition and get the most out of life. We also provide courses to people with other long-term conditions, and run workshops to develop other people’s understanding of arthritis. If you have a long-term condition and are looking for ways to cope, this course could be for you. You may have been recently diagnosed, you may have been living with your condition for some time, or someone close to you may be affected. If you feel in need of help, Challenging Your Condition is suitable for any point in your adult life.',NULL,'arthritis_care','https://www.facebook.com/ArthritisCareUK?ref=ts',1,150,1,1,53.6555,-2.64787,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'self-management-workshops-and-courses---arthritis-care',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(174,200,'British Heart Foundation Heart Helpline',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0300 3303311',NULL,'http://www.bhf.org.uk/heart-health/how-we-help/support/heart-helpline.aspx','When it comes to anything heart-related, we want to make sure that you have all the information, support and guidance you need. We\'re here to help you, whether you\'re calling about yourself or someone you care about. Our cardiac nurses and heart health advisors are on hand to help with any questions or concerns you have about heart health and heart conditions. Lines are open 9am-5pm Monday to Friday.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,NULL,NULL,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'british-heart-foundation-heart-helpline',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(175,201,'Hope Kidney Patient Association (HKPA)','Kath Barlow','Salford Royal NHS Foundation Trust','Salford Royal','Stott Lane','Salford','M6 8HD','01204 381266 or','info.hopekpa@gmail.com','http://www.srft.nhs.uk/about-us/depts/renal-services/patient-organisations/hope-kidney-patients-association/','Hope Kidney Patient Association (HKPA) is a Registered Charity run by kidney patients for kidney patients, their carers, relatives, friends and other interested parties. Only someone who has experienced kidney disease can understand the problems and anxieties associated with the illness. It is often easier for a patient and his or her family to talk to another patient about their difficulties. A patients\' association can provide additional support to complement the NHS provision. HKPA represents the interests of kidney patients who are treated within the West Sector of the Greater Manchester Kidney Care Network (Bolton, Bury, Oldham, Rochdale, Trafford, Wigan & district). Membership is free and open to patients, carers and anyone with a direct interest in the subject of renal disease. The KPA also represents patients\' interests at meetings with medical and managerial staff at the hospital and can offer help and advice on matters of concern to the patient and/or their carer. It can provide information on any problems associated with kidney disease and information on the nature of the disease itself. Meet every 6 weeks at 7.00pm at Salford Royal Hospital, previously known as Hope Hospital. Contact group for details.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.487545,-2.323424,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'hope-kidney-patient-association-hkpa',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(176,202,'