ble tennis, 5-a-side football, Profiles Health & Fitness suite offering an extensive range of cardiovascular and resistance machines and a large function room is also available for hire.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.532777,-2.562685,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'hindley-leisure-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(244,270,'Wigan Hospice Bowling Club',NULL,'North Ashton Village Club','Bolton Street',NULL,'Ashton-in-Makerfield','WN4 0QE','01942 205612',NULL,NULL,'This bowling club meets at the North Ashton Village Club Monday nights 7-9pm. Please note that the bowling season is from March-September. The fee is approx £40 per annum.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.496931,-2.666186,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-hospice-bowling-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(245,271,'Pensioners Link','Anne Deacon','Wigan & Leigh Pensioners Link','Allan Taylor House','27 Charles Street','Leigh','WN7 1DB','01942 261753','anne_counsellor@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.pensionerslink.org.uk','Pensioner Link works with and for the benefit of the over 50’s throughout the borough of Wigan. It currently provides a range of services which support older people and carers of all ages by providing information, advice and signposting on a wide number of issues and works very closely with the Carers Helpline. It hosts Wigan Independent Advice Centre one morning/week for benefits advice, and the Health Trainers use our centre for consultations. We also offer a one-to-one counselling service provided by fully qualified counsellors. Very importantly, Pensioners Link provides a wide range of social activities, which are very well attended by older people and carers. Activities include arts and crafts, exercise and relaxation, holistic therapies, good food club, coffee mornings, tai chi, discussion group, Spanish and IT.',NULL,'penlinkhouse','https://www.facebook.com/leigh.pensionerslink',1,150,1,1,53.497205,-2.513966,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pensioners-link',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(246,272,'Fourways',NULL,'Fourways Assessment Unit','Cleworth Hall Lane','Tyldesley','Wigan','M29 8WS','01942 486930','fourways@wigan.gov.uk','http://www.wigan.gov.uk/Services/HealthSocialCare/DayServices/Fourways/','Our rehabilitation programmes are designed to help recover as far as possible, people\'s former abilities following an impairment. Each person has different needs and our programmes reflect this. In some cases a residential placement lasting up to a maximum of 2 years may be required, in other cases a day service placement may be more appropriate. Our occupational therapist and support staff will work with you towards the goals, you have jointly decided. You will have the opportunity to practice skills you may have lost and also find ways to cope with the difficulties you are facing. Depending on individual circumstances, programmes may include topics such as: improving mobility, domestic activities, personal care, accessing community facilities, speech and language skills, household finance, and social skills.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.513885,-2.447508,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fourways',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(247,273,'Active Lifestyles Development Officers',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Salford',NULL,NULL,NULL,'http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/active-lifestyles','If you would like to become physically active and have any of the following health conditions contact the Active Lifestyles Team about getting started: heart attack or stroke, coronary heart disease, high blood pressure, overweight or obese, inactive lifestyle, high cholesterol, diabetes or a family history of heart disease. Our team of friendly and highly qualified exercise professionals can give you specific advice and information about your condition and what exercise may suit you best and will provide you with ongoing support in becoming involved with the many enjoyable and sociable exercise options we offer. Maybe try our Get Active Programme a free six week course of exercise taster sessions including Low level circuits, Tai Chi and Kurling and with the guidance of your Active Lifestyles Officer discover what exercise best suits your goals and needs.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.488465,-2.298297,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'active-lifestyles-development-officers',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(248,274,'Healthy Hips and Hearts',NULL,'Salford Community Leisure Ltd','Salford Watersports Centre','15 The Quays','Salford','M50 3SQ','0161 7780373','louise.sword@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/active-lifestyles/healthy-at-heart','Healthy hips and hearts is a programme of class based exercise sessions that targets older people. The sessions includes chair based exercise, Tai Chi and also the Healthy hips and hearts choir. All these sessions operate in a community or care home setting. Success of this scheme is not only measured by the physiological benefits of the exercise sessions, but also the social interaction of the group, which results in improved mental well-being. The benefits on the Healthy hips and heart scheme include improved balance, preventing falls, increasing confidence, meeting new friends and having fun and keeping mobile.',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.471633,-2.288057,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'healthy-hips-and-hearts',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(249,275,'Fit City Broughton Pool',NULL,'Great Cheetham Street West',NULL,NULL,'Salford','M7 2DN','0161 7922847','fitcitybroughtonpool@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-broughton-pool','Fit City Broughton Pool boasts a health and fitness suite containing the very best in resistance and cardio-vascular exercise equipment. The suite is managed by experienced and qualified staff to help you create a healthier lifestyle. There is also a sauna available for relaxation. A 25 metre swimming pool and separate teaching pool host many local and regional competitions throughout the year. In addition, there is a full programme of adult and children’s swimming lessons. Salford Swim Squad have most of their training sessions based here and the pool also hosts other aquatic clubs and organisations.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.500411,-2.264735,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-broughton-pool',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(250,276,'Fit City Clarendon',NULL,'Liverpool Street',NULL,NULL,'Salford','M5 4AY','0161 7361494','fitcityclarendon@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-clarendon','Fit City Clarendon provides excellent access and leisure opportunities for all members of the community. At Fit City Clarendon there are fantastic swimming facilities. These comprise of a 25 metre pool that is shallow at both ends and a separate teaching pool. There is a health and fitness suite, a four court multi-purpose sports hall, aerobics studio, squash court and outdoor synthetic pitch. This centre is an Inclusive Fitness Initiative (IFI) accredited centre. This means that special consideration is given to people with disabilities. There are specially designated car parking spaces, easy ground floor access, modified exercise machines and a fully inclusive exercise programme.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.482914,-2.286624,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-clarendon',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(251,277,'Fit City Eccles',NULL,'Barton Lane','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0DD','0161 7877107','fitcityeccles@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-eccles','Fit City Eccles is a modern facility offering a double storey 85-station gym equipped with the latest range of Pulse Fitness cardiovascular and resistance equipment. There is a comprehensive range of aerobic classes including, circuits, spinning, aerobics, boxercise, chair based exercise classes and tai-chi. There are also aqua-fit classes in the swimming pool. The 25m swimming pool provides a comprehensive programme of swimming activities from general public sessions to lane swimming, and competitive club. The large sports hall provides the opportunity to enjoy a range of traditional sporting activities and coaching classes.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.478871,-2.346207,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-eccles',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(252,278,'Fit City Ordsall',NULL,'Craven Drive','Ordsall',NULL,'Salford','M5 3DJ','0161 8480646','fitcityordsall@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-ordsall','The centre offers a fantastic 58 station suite, including the dynamic new concept \'Vibe express circuit range\' allowing you to have a full workout in 20 minutes. There is also a full class programme including young @ heart (age 50+), aerobics, legs, bums and tums, basic yoga, Vibe circuit class, zumba and more.  It is a dry sports facility comprising of a large sports hall which is suitable for a wide range of sporting activities. This centre has benefited from a recent refurbishment including upgraded changing facilities. The local ‘SAYO’ [Sports and Arts for Youths in Ordsall] youth project is also based at this facility creating further leisure opportunities for the local community. Fit City Ordsall is the new home of Salford Gymnastics Club. Relocated from North Salford sessions are run for pre-school (Fit City Tots) through to squad level. There is also a purpose built indoor bowls hall which hosts a popular winter league and is also available for public hire. Adjacent to the Fit City Ordsall is a full size synthetic pitch suitable for both football and hockey.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.469617,-2.280795,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-ordsall',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(253,279,'Fit City Pendlebury',NULL,'Cromwell Road','Pendlebury',NULL,'Salford','M27 9SZ','0161 7931750','fitcitypendlebury@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-pendlebury','Close to the centre of Swinton, Fit City Pendlebury has a 25 metre swimming pool which offers a wide range of aquatic activities from public swimming to swimming lessons for all ages and abilities. For the competitive swimmer, Swinton Swimming Club is based at this centre.  The swimming pool is an ideal venue for people with disabilities. There is a regular weekly session for this group, and the pool includes a hoist. It is also served by purpose built changing, toilet and showering facilities, all with easy access. We have an extensive fitness class programme which is delivered in our large sports hall. Classes include circuits, Boxercise, Zumba, Aerobics and many more. Our Fitness Suite has recently undergone a full refurbishment, which included the installation of state of the art Pulse Resistance and Cardio Vascular (CV) equipment. All CV equipment has it\'s own integrated Freeview TV.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.516161,-2.343715,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-pendlebury',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(254,280,'Fit City Worsley',NULL,'Bridgewater Road','Walkden',NULL,'Salford','M28 3AB','0161 7902084','fitcityworsley@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/fit-city-worsley','On entering the building you will notice a bright and welcoming reception and entrance area. There are three swimming pools that provide a child friendly environment and excellent facilities for public swimming. You will also find a new sauna suite, which is located adjacent to the main swimming pool. A brand new fully re-equipped fitness suite has been provided and this is complimented by a fantastic aerobics/dance studio which is already proving extremely popular.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.510784,-2.415101,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'fit-city-worsley',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(255,281,'Irlam and Cadishead Leisure Centre',NULL,'Liverpool Road','Irlam',NULL,'Salford','M44 6RB','0161 7754134','fitcityirlam@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/irlam-and-cadishead-leisure-centre','The \'new look\' facility boasts a four court sports hall, a squash court, dry side changing facilities, an extension to the existing fitness suite, a multi use/aerobic studio, outdoor team changing facilities, improved access for people with disabilities - including a lift to the first floor, an additional pool entrance in the wetside changing rooms for groups/lessons and additional car parking bays. The additional features of the facility allow more family friendly/co-ordinated activities to take place. There is more of an opportunity to cater for every age group (in particular families) in one building - at the same time. There is now the potential to add new sessions to the leisure programme, as well as expand on the existing ones. The sports hall caters for football, basketball, netball, trampolining, gymnastics, aerobic sessions and sports courses… to name but a few.',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.450242,-2.415671,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'irlam-and-cadishead-leisure-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(256,282,'Salford Sports Village',NULL,'Littleton Road',NULL,NULL,'Salford','M7 3NQ','0161 6047600','salfordsportsvillage@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/sport/locations/salford-sports-village','Fantastic on the outside - even better on the inside! The building has excellent changing accommodation perfect for even the muddiest of teams. There is a community room available for corporate hire and bookings in conjunction with sporting activities. Salford Sports Village is a state of the art facility providing a fantastic range of sporting and training opportunities for everyone. Services include a 32-station fitness suite, two fitness studios, full size third generation astroturf pitch, seven a side third generation astroturf pitch with shock pad (suitable for rugby training), four fully enclosed five-a-side astroturf pitches, nine 11-a-side grass pitches, six mini soccer grass pitches and  three nine-a-side grass pitches',NULL,'Sport_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.506626,-2.282668,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-sports-village',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(257,283,'Beesley Green Community Centre','Gordon, Dale or Diana','Greenleach Lane','Worsley',NULL,'Salford','M28 2QW','0161 7906124','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/beesley-green-community-centre','Activities and groups include Stretch & Relax (Mon 10-12pm); Latin Dance (Mon 12.15-1.15pm, Fri 1-3pm); Salford Photographic Society (Mon 8-10pm); Badminton (Mon 7.30-10pm, Thurs 8-7pm); American Line Dance - beginners (Wed 12.45-3.15pm); Art Club (Tues 1-3pm); Pilates (Tues 6-7); Step Aerobic (Tues 7.30-9.30); Worsley Intermate Theatre (Tues & Thurs 7.30-9.30pm); Healthy Hips & Heart; Yoga; Drawing and Art Class (Wed 7-9pm); Flower Arr