t Metro programme also offers lessons for complete beginners from 6 weeks old. For more information contact the Swimline on +44 (0)161 4290401. For general centre enquiries please call +44 (0)161 4747766.',NULL,'lifeleisureUK','https://www.facebook.com/lifeleisure',1,150,1,1,53.407132,-2.16011,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'grand-central-',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(277,303,'Bramhall U3A','Mike Hollingworth','St Michaels Church Hall','St Michaels Avenue','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 2PG','0161 4392865','enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk','http://www.bramhallu3a.org.uk/','The aim is to share learning and leisure interests with other retired or semi-retired people in the Bramhall area as well as encouraging social interaction between members. Monthly meeting, usually on the 3rd Thursday of the month, at St. Michael\'s Church Hall with a guest speaker. More than 40 groups taking part in creative activities (e.g. art, card making, choir, embroidery), physical activities (e.g. cycling, Pilates swimming, table tennis, walking), learning activities (e.g. archaeology, languages, science) and other leisure activities (e.g. discussion groups, family history, pub quiz). The U3A also organising day\'s outings and theatre visits plus holidays. How to join - contact the membership secretary by emailing enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk or come to one of our monthly meetings. £10 per year per person to join the U3A. There is a charge of £1 to come to the monthly meetings. Some activities take place in the homes of members where there is no charge. There will be a small charge for some activities where a room has to be hired. There are obviously charges for outings, theatre visits and holidays.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.363982,-2.163215,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(278,304,'Age UK Stockport',NULL,'Commonweal','56 Wellington Street