le',NULL,'Shiers Drive','Cheadle',NULL,'Stockport','SK8 1JR','0161 4283216','info@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/Cheadle','Just a five minute walk from Cheadle Village and John Lewis, Life Leisure Cheadle has facilities and activities for all the family. Facilities include: state of the art fitness suite, swimming pools (main pool and small pool), aerobics studio with weekly programme of classes, swim changing area, childrens soft play area, childrens classes and activities, Stockport Metro swimming lessons, and Variety fitness sports injury clinic and massage. In addition to general gym and aerobics classes we offer personal training and a number of specialised fitness courses. For more information on all our activities why not drop in for a look around or call a member of the team on +44 (0)161 4283216.',NULL,'lifeleisureUK','https://www.facebook.com/lifeleisure',1,150,1,1,53.386586,-2.209384,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'life-leisure-cheadle',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(310,336,'Life Leisure Hazel Grove',NULL,'Jackson\'s Lane','Hazel Grove',NULL,'Stockport','SK7 5JW','0161 4395221','info@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/HazelGrove','Ideally situated for local residents and businesses alike, Life Leisure Hazel Grove has facilities and activities for all the family. Facilities include: State of the art fitness suite, swimming pools (main and small pools), aerobics studio with weekly class programme, dedicated spin studio, sports performance zones, swim changing area, creche, children\'s classes and activities, Stockport Metro swimming lessons, JT physiotherapy clinic and massage,  and Essence of Beauty. In addition to general gym and aerobics classes we offer personal training and a number of specialised fitness courses. For more information on all our activities why not drop in for a look around or call a member of the team on +44 (0)161 4395221.',NULL,'lifeleisureUK','https://www.facebook.com/lifeleisure',1,150,1,1,53.369811,-2.13608,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'life-leisure-hazel-grove',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(311,337,'Grand Central ',NULL,'Grand Central Square','Wellington Road South',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 3TA','0161 4747766','info@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/GrandCentralPools','Located right in the centre of Stockport, next door to the train station, Life Leisure has recently taken over Grand Central Pools as management contractors and over the next few months the centre shall be revamped to the town centres most advanced fitness facility. Newly fitted with the latest fitness equipment it is planned to refurbish a number of areas in the facility over the coming months. Facilities include: state of the art fitness suite, brand new fitness equipment, performance training zone, aerobics studio, 50 metre swimming pool, and health suite. The centre is also home to Stockport Metro and a British Swimming Intensive Training Centre where world class swimmers and Olympic medallists train on a daily basis. The Stockport Metro programme also offers lessons for complete beginners from 6 weeks old. For more information contact the Swimline on +44 (0)161 4290401. For general centre enquiries please call +44 (0)161 4747766.',NULL,'lifeleisureUK','https://www.facebook.com/lifeleisure',1,150,1,1,53.407132,-2.16011,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'grand-central-',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(312,338,'Bolton CHA Rambling Club','Doreen Pearson',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bolton',NULL,'01204 394649','stridingout@hotmail.co.uk','http://www.boltoncha.org.uk/index.html','The Club is very active and extends a warm welcome to all walkers and lovers of the countryside. We particularly welcome new members of all ages to come along and join us on one of our many walks this summer. We are a local club, based around Bolton, Lancashire, with no affiliations and with members of all ages and from a range of backgrounds. For a modest annual fee you can enjoy all the hidden delights of rural Lancashire and beyond, the best way there is, on foot! Let us introduce you to walks you may not even know and in turn you can offer us your favourites. Bolton CHA Rambling Club is always keen to recruit new members. We organise walks for people of all ages, abilities and backgrounds and in addition we arrange a number of social activities throughout the year.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.584441,-2.428619,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-cha-rambling-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(313,339,'Bolton Ramblers','Pat Hall',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bolton',NULL,'01204 300602','boltonramblers@hotmail.co.uk','http://www.boltonramblers.org.uk/index.html','The group is part of the Manchester and High Peak Area of the Ramblers\' Association. The whole area includes many regions of excellent, scenic walking country and is also within easy access of the Peak District, the Lake District and the Yorkshire Dales National Parks. Currently we have about 550 members and new members are always welcome. We have a varied programme of walks. Coach Rambles are organised for the first Saturday and third Sunday of each month. Shorter Local Footpath Walks using the wealth of footpaths in the Bolton area are organised on the second Sunday of each month. These shorter walks are almost always accessible by public transport and provide a great way to get into walking as well as exploring the countryside in and around Bolton.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.584441,-2.428619,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-ramblers',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(314,340,'Get Active Bolton','','The Get Active Team, Floor 1 Bolton Arena','Arena Approach','Horwich','Bolton','BL6 6LB','0800 458 4029','getactivebolton@gmail.com','http://www.getactivebolton.co.uk/','<p>Get Active is a community physical activity programme for over 45&#39;s in Bolton and aims to encourage people to increase their levels of physical activity in with the national recommended guidelines of at least 5 x 30 minutes per week. Existing Get Active sessions include: salsa, gym sessions, boxing sessions, keep fit classes, Pilates, yoga, gentle stretch and exercise, swimming, dancing, bowls, tai chi, off road bike and many more...</p>\r\n','','GetActiveBolton','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Get-Active-Bolton/256539264415883',1,150,1,1,53.578966,-2.537925,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-06-19 11:18:50',NULL,NULL,'get-active-bolton',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(315,341,'Mud to Muscle','Rachael Ford','The Environment Resource Centre','499-511 Bury Road',NULL,'Bolton','BL2 6DH','01204 603754','rford@lancswt.org.uk','http://www.activebolton.com/page.aspx?Page=19','This project is aimed at adults who want to get outdoors, get active and get environmental. By having a go at practical conservation tasks in green spaces of Bolton the team can make improvements to the environment and their local community whilst also benefitting their health. The tasks include practical management to woodland, wetlands and grasslands and are varied and fun. All equipment is provided as well as brews! Our sessions are aimed at all levels of experience and fitness. If you have never done any outdoor practical work before don\'t let this put you off as our supervisors will provide you with all the information and support you need on how to use our tools. All volunteers are welcome - from those who want to move 40 wheelbarrows a day to those who just want to make the brews and have a chat!',NULL,'Lancswildlife','https://www.facebook.com/lancashirewildlifetrust',1,150,1,1,53.580802,-2.385594,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'mud-to-muscle',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(316,342,'Wigan Rambling and Climbing Club','Jill Shilladay','Wigan Cricket Club','Bull Hey','Parsons Walk','Wigan','WN1 1RU','01257 421926','jill.shilladay@btinternet.com','http://www.wiganwalkers.com/','Walks take place on Sundays throughout the year, and on Tuesday evenings during the summer months. Start times vary. We are just about to publish our programme for the next six months, which should be on the website soon. Walks are graded according to difficulty and anyone who is relatively active should find a walk within their ability. We advise those not used to walking to start with the easier walks to assess their fitness level. We also organise social events in the winter months. These are held at Wigan Cricket Club off Parsons Walk in Wigan and start at 8.15 pm each week. We are always keen to welcome new members. We charge a £10 annual membership fee which entitles members to go on any of the guided walks including those using a coach to reach the start of the walk. There is an additional charge of £10 per person when using the coach. At other times we use our own transport. It is customary to make a nominal contribution to the driver towards fuel costs.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/WiganRamblingAndClimbingClub',1,150,1,1,53.550641,-2.637151,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-rambling-and-climbing-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(317,343,'Get Active Wigan and Leigh',NULL,'Robin Park Indoor Sports Centre','Loire Drive',NULL,'Wigan','WN5 0UL','01942 488481','activeliving@wlct.org','http://www.getactivewiganandleigh.co.uk/','Active Living is part of Wigan Leisure & Culture Trust, and is responsible for helping people to become more physically active to improve their general health, well-being and quality of life. The team provide a wide range of sessions and activities to suit everyone, wherever you are in Wigan Borough. You can find details of all activities and health programmes, along with lots of information on health and well-being, by visiting their website.',NULL,'active_living','https://www.facebook.com/ActiveLiving',1,150,1,1,53.54569,-2.652535,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'get-active-wigan-and-leigh',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(318,344,'Salford U3A/ Salford Life Long Learning','Carole Bowler','Eccles Gateway','28 Barton Lane','Eccles','Salford','M30 0TU','0161 790 2372/0','carole@bowler.plus.com','http://www.salfordu3alll.colsal.org.uk/','U3A\' stands for The University of the Third Age. The \'Third Age\' is a time of creativity and fulfilment for older people. The \'Third Age\' refers to the periods of time after the First Age of childhood dependence and the Second Age of full time employment and parental responsibility. Salford Life Long Learning is a group of approximately 250 people within the U3A who are seeking to swell their numbers so why not join us. They have a range of groups which do different activities including: memories of Salford, discussion groups, bird watching, drama, gardening, family history, french, Mahjongg, music, poetry (Fri afternoon-please call), opera ballet on video, painting, science and maths, scrabble, walks, Eccles local history, A toast to Salford, Spanish, summer schools, no vices bridge, book club (first Wednesday of the month @ Walkden Gateway), quilting, theatre group and keep fit. Monthly general meetings take place at the Eccles Gateway.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482579,-2.338968,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-u3a-salford-life-long-learning',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(319,345,'Health Walks','Jo Bennett','Active Lifestyles Development Officer','Salford Watersport Centre','15 The Quays','Salford','M50 3SQ','0161 7780559','jo.bennett@scll.co.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/healthwalks.htm','Salford Community Leisure’s health walk scheme forms part of a national programme to help encourage and support people to become more physically active to improve their health. Health walks are led by trained volunteers and can be from 45 minutes to one hour in length. The health walks aim to promote the message of ‘doing at least 30 minutes of moderate activity on at least five days of the week’.  Nordic walking - A form of summer cross country skiing training, whereby you walk with specifically designed poles, using your upper and lower body at the same time, strengthening your back, legs and arms, and reducing neck and shoulder tension - all this while improving the health of your heart and lungs. Aimed at people who want to get more physically active. If you\'re interested in walking and would like some routes to try by yourself or with friends you can download six route cards for walks in Eccles, Winton and Barton. The routes have been created as part of an independent walking pack, which contains the route cards and information on health, physical activity and walking. Numbers are limited but If you would like to receive a pack please email your name and address to jo.bennett@scll.co.uk and we\'ll pop one in the post.',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.471633,-2.288057,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'health-walks',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(320,346,'Boothstown Community Centre','Marjorie or Susan','Standfield Drive','Boothstown','Worsley','Salford','M28 1NB','0161 7999425','fsoadmin@scll.co.uk','http://www.salfordcommunityleisure.co.uk/lifestyles/locations/boothstown-community-centre','Activities and groups include Cafe 55 (meals start at 11.30am); Older persons meeting (first Monday of the month); Grow your Own (6 weeks from 13th Feb, Mon 2-4pm); Healthy walking group (Mon 2-4pm); Men\'s Health Group (Mon 3-4.30pm); Writers Group (Mon 7-9pm); Curling; Healthy Hips and Hearts (Tues 2-3.30pm); Weight Watchers (Tues 5-6.30pm, 6.30-8pm); Zumba (Tues 8-9pm); Lunch Club (Wed 12.30-2pm); Over 60s Club (Wed 1.30-3.30pm); Local Histories (Third Wednesday of month 7.15-9.15pm); Ladies Group (last Wednesday of month 7.30-10pm); Art group (Thurs 11.45-1.45pm); Tai Chi (Thurs 2-3pm); Yoga (Thurs 7.15-9.15pm); Transport meeting; Reading Group (Fri 2-3pm).',NULL,'Lifestyle_SC','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Salford-Community-Leisure/394597987283835',1,150,1,1,53.504413,-2.417325,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'boothstown-community-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(321,347,'PARiS (Physical Activity Referral in Stockport)','Michelle Childs',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Stockport',NULL,'0161 4820900','gpreferral@lifeleisure.net','http://www.lifeleisure.net/enterprise/lifeleisurestockportgpreferral','Physical Activity Referral in Stockport (PARiS) is the GP Exercise Referral scheme in Stockport, designed to help patients with moderate medical conditions become and stay more physically active, whilst benefiting and or improving their health. A joint partnership between Life Leisure and NHS Stockport, the scheme is delivered by a strong and experienced team of health and exercise professionals, who provide guidance, support and pathways towards health improvement. Activities include health walks, chair based exercise, gym sessions, yoga and swimming as well as specialist sessions for those with COPD and Cardiac conditions. Some of the activities involve a cost which is subsidised and some are free such as the cycling program and health walks. The scheme operates throughout a variety of Life Leisure Facilities and community facilities also.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.406754,-2.158843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'paris-physical-activity-referral-in-stockport',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(322,348,'Bramhall U3A','Mike Hollingworth','St Michaels Church Hall','St Michaels Avenue','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 2PG','0161 4392865','enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk','http://www.bramhallu3a.org.uk/','The aim is to share learning and leisure interests with other retired or semi-retired people in the Bramhall area as well as encouraging social interaction between members. Monthly meeting, usually on the 3rd Thursday of the month, at St. Michael\'s Church Hall with a guest speaker. More than 40 groups taking part in creative activities (e.g. art, card making, choir, embroidery), physical activities (e.g. cycling, Pilates swimming, table tennis, walking), learning activities (e.g. archaeology, languages, science) and other leisure activities (e.g. discussion groups, family history, pub quiz). The U3A also organising day\'s outings and theatre visits plus holidays. How to join - contact the membership secretary by emailing enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk or come to one of our monthly meetings. £10 per year per person to join the U3A. There is a charge of £1 to come to the monthly meetings. Some activities take place in the homes of members where there is no charge. There will be a small charge for some activities where a room has to be hired. There are obviously charges for outings, theatre visits and holidays.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.363982,-2.163215,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(323,349,'Stockport Ramblers','Gwen Bennett',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Stockport',NULL,'07794 715265','gwen_22@hotmail.com','http://www.stockportramblers.org.uk/','We are the Stockport Ramblers. We are the largest of the ten Ramblers groups in the Greater Manchester and High Peak area, and part of the Ramblers, a nationwide charity whose aims are to promote walking for health, pleasure and an appreciation of our wonderful countryside. We offer walks in the Stockport area, but also further afield, such as the Peak District, Southern Pennines, Yorkshire Dales and Snowdonia. We also arrange walking weekends away, to places such as the Lake District, Wales and the Northern Pennines. We have walks to suit all abilities, so if you are new to walking you may choose a shorter and easier walk in the local area, or if you are more experienced you may choose a harder walk in the moorlands or possibly the Mountains of Snowdonia.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.406754,-2.158843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-ramblers',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(324,350,'Stockport Walking and Outdoor Group','Sue',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Stockport',NULL,'0161 4948220','Stockportwalkingoutdoors@gmail.com','http://www.stockportwalkingoutdoor.org.uk/','Stockport Walking & Outdoor Group is a multi-activity group with individual members aged 18 to 70+ as well as a number of families. New faces are always welcome ... just come along to any of our events. The annual subscription of £5 per person is collected in January each year. Activities include: Sunday walks, cycle rides, family walks, Wednesday walks. Other activities are arranged from time to time and will be published on our website and in the programme. These may include: theatre trips, meals, barbecues, cinema visits, walking, cycling & skiing holidays.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.406754,-2.158843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-walking-and-outdoor-group',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(325,351,'Hazel Grove Civic Hall','Tracey Banham or Kadijatu Mansaray','London Road','Hazel Grove',NULL,'Stockport','SK7 4DF','0161 4742200','tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk or kadijatu.mansaray@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: Hazel Grove TWG Craft Club (Wednesday PM), Gardening Club Meetings and Showing (Tuesday PM), Gardening Club Committee Meetings (Wednesday PM), North Cheshire Family History Meetings (Tuesday PM), H.G.C.A. Social Section Coffee Morning (Thursday AM), H.G.C.A. Social Section Tea Dance (Wednesday AM), H.G.C.A. Social Section Social Dance (Saturday PM), H .G. Brass Band Band Practice (Thursday PM), Poynton Youth Brass Band Meeting (Wednesday PM), Knitting Club Meeting (Thursday PM), H.G. Royal British Legion Meeting (Wednesday PM), High Peak Woodturners Meetings and Demonstration (Friday PM), Stockport Philatelic Society Meetings (Friday PM), Stockport Walking and Outdoor Group Meeting (Wednesday PM), H. G. Dance Group Sequence Dancing (Friday AM), Craft Club (Saturday AM), Yoga Training (Wednesday AM), Bunkai Karate Training (Wednesday PM), Bunkai Karate Karate Training (Monday PM), Grove School of Dance - dance lessons (Tuesday AM/PM and Thursday AM/PM), K. D. Dancing - sequence dancing (Thursday PM), H.G. Ward Committee Meeting (Tuesday PM) Hula Hoop Classes - dance lessons (Wed morn 9.45 am to 11am), and Sunshine Circle - meetings and chat (Wednesday AM). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.379632,-2.120795,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'hazel-grove-civic-hall',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(326,352,'Marple Senior Citizens Centre','Tracey Banham or Kadijatu Mansaray','Memorial Park','Marple',NULL,'Stockport','SK6 6BA','0161 4742200','tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk or kadijatu.mansaray@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: U3A (Monday AM/PM), Whist Drive (Monday PM), RSPB High Peak (Monday PM), WRVS (Tuesday AM/PM), Marple & District Rambling Club (Tuesday PM) Probus - retired or semi-retired professional or business people club (Wednesday AM/PM), Bingo (Wednesday PM), MSCA Dance (Wednesday and Thursday PM) WRVS Luncheon (Thursday AM/PM), Marple Carers (Thursday PM), and Marple Senior Citizens Dance (Saturday PM). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided. For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.396833,-2.060356,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'marple-senior-citizens-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(327,353,'Adult Learning in Bolton Libraries',NULL,'Central Library','Le Mans Crescent',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1SE','01204 333173 ','libraries@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/AdulteducationatBoltonLibraries.aspx','Activities include: English for Speakers of Other Languages (ESOL) - ESOL classes run at the Central Library in partnership with The Workers Educational Association. ICT Classes - many of our libraries run beginners’ ICT classes in partnership with Bolton Community College. These classes run for four or five weeks (with 10 hours tuition in all). Other classes - we offer a range of other courses for adult learners – for example Tai Chi at Oxford Grove and Local History at Astley Bridge – and there are new ones starting all the time. Do ask at any library for more details and to book your place.',NULL,'BoltonLMS','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonLibraries?fref=ts',1,150,1,1,53.577385,-2.431294,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'adult-learning-in-bolton-libraries',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(328,354,'Age UK Learning and Resource Centre Farnworth',NULL,'Cross Street','Farnworth',NULL,'Bolton','BL4 7AG','01204 701525','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/Our-services/Courses--activities/','If you thought life stopped at 50, then think again. A whole new world of opportunity and learning is waiting to be discovered. Just take a look at what’s on offer in our Learning and Resources Centre. Conveniently located at the heart of Farnworth, the Centre, which has its own parking area, is only a few minutes’ walk from the town’s main bus station and shopping area. This modern, comfortable and purpose-built facility, on two-levels, has been designed in partnership with older people, and offers full access, throughout, for people with disabilities. Hundreds of older people use the Centre each week and all are assured of a warm and friendly welcome. There are courses to suit all levels and all tastes, including: computers for ABSOLUTE beginners, intermediate level computer courses, internet for beginners, digital photography and image manipulation, family history workshop. And if computers aren’t your thing, there’s lots more to choose from: painting and drawing, modern languages, an attractive choice of crafts, music keyboard and guitar classes and literature groups.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.548993,-2.396181,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-learning-and-resource-centre-farnworth',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(329,355,'Bolton College Adult Learning',NULL,'Deane Road Campus','Deane Road',NULL,'Bolton','BL3 5BG','01204 482000','info@boltoncc.ac.uk','http://www.boltoncollege.ac.uk/key-area/5/Adult-Learning','Bolton College offers hundreds of excellent learning opportunities that are ideally suited to the needs of adults returning to education through adult education or community learning ranging from introductory courses and general interest to advanced courses and foundation degrees. Fees vary.',NULL,'BoltonCollege','https://www.facebook.com/BoltonCollege',1,150,1,1,53.57357,-2.44032,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-college-adult-learning',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(330,356,'Enjoy Learning Bolton','Tom Smith',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Bolton',NULL,'01204 811163','tomsmith.belmont@talk21.com','http://www.enjoy-learning.org.uk/','Enjoy Learning is a not for profit organisation that provides courses and events without examinations. Information is on our website. This is being updated over the next few weeks to include our 2012/13 programme and venue changes. We offer courses to anyone over the age of 18 but in reality the majority of people who attend are over 50 and around 60% are 60 and over. The courses and classes recruit well and we are growing year on year (we started in 2006) - we have had over 1000 enrolments this year. Most of our classes are languages, art and craft, history based, with a little music and creative writing included as well. We respond to demands and this determines our programme offer . This year however we have commissioned a report on what we can offer to stroke victims and are running a one day event in Bolton Library around older people and mobile digital devices as part of adult learners week (May 2012). We offer our courses in the north Bolton area at Delph Hill Community Centre Doffcocker, Horwich Resource Centre, St. John\'s Breightmet and Theatre Church. Fees vary.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.584441,-2.428619,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'enjoy-learning-bolton',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(331,357,'Bolton U3A','Ann Waring','St Andrew and St George URC','St George Street',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 2BS','01204 492343','ann.waring@hotmail.co.uk','http://u3asites.org.uk/code/u3asite.php?site=495&page=1','U3A stands for the University of the Third Age, which is a self-help organisation for people no longer in full time employment providing educational, creative and leisure opportunities in a friendly environment. Interest Groups meet at various venues in the town centre in these subjects; archaeology, art appreciation, basic Italian, biology, crafts (cards), creative writing, European studies, film forum, gardening, French, history, literature, local history, mah-jong, play reading, philosophy, poetry for pleasure, recorded music, scrabble, Saturday ramblers, singing for pleasure, solo whist - cards, walkabout, transactional analysis, world’s religions, women’s history. General meeting are held on the 4th Friday of the month, 2pm – 4pm. Annual Subscription; £18.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.581602,-2.432203,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(332,358,'Leigh Library',NULL,'Turnpike Centre','Civic Square','Market Street','Leigh','WN7 1EB','01942 404404','Leigh.Library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/leigh-library.htm','Mondays - Writers Group (fortnightly) 5:30pm – 6:45pm. A friendly and supportive creative writing session. Everyone Welcome. Leigh Family History Society 1:30pm – 3:30pm (Local History Desk). Tuesdays - My Guide 10am – 12 noon (In The Library) Internet course for beginners. Get into Reading 11:30pm - 1pm (In The Library), enjoy stories and poems read aloud, Bookchat 7:15pm - 9pm, Adult reading group runs on the 1st Tuesday in the month. Wednesdays - Carpe Diem Sewing Group 10am – 12noon (In The Derby Room). Thursdays - \'Chatterbooks\' - 11am – 12 noon 1st Thursday of the month. (In The Library), Your Bard (Shakespeare Reading Group) 5:30pm – 7pm. 4th Thursday of the month. (In The Derby Room), Poetry Reading Group 7:15pm – 8:30pm 2nd Thursday in month. Fridays - My Guide 10am – 12 noon Internet course for beginners. (In The Library). Saturdays - The Open Book Club 11am - 12noon (monthly). Reading group for adults. Read and discuss our featured book voted for by you. Craft Circle: Whatever your interests - card making, knitting, embroidery or any other crafts - the Craft Circle is the place to meet like-minded people and share tip and ideas. It\'s free and there\'s no need to book, just turn up on the day. We meet on the 1st Friday of the month 1-3pm. For further information telephone Louise on +44 (0)1942 404469.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.496922,-2.518982,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'leigh-library',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(333,359,'Wigan Library','Wigan Library','Rita Musa','Wigan Life Centre','The Weind','Wigan','WN1 1NH','01942 404126','wigan.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/wigan-library.htm','English Conversation Wednesdays 4.30pm - 6.00pm and Bookchat for Adults - 1st Wednesday every month 10.30am - 11.30am. Fridays - BBC First Click IT Course 10 - 11.30am. Fridays - Craft Chat 2.30pm - 3.30pm. Saturdays - Knitted Bliss 10.30am - 11.30am.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.545508,-2.631163,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-library',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(334,360,'Salford U3A/ Salford Life Long Learning','Carole Bowler','Eccles Gateway','28 Barton Lane','Eccles','Salford','M30 0TU','0161 790 2372/0','carole@bowler.plus.com','http://www.salfordu3alll.colsal.org.uk/','U3A\' stands for The University of the Third Age. The \'Third Age\' is a time of creativity and fulfilment for older people. The \'Third Age\' refers to the periods of time after the First Age of childhood dependence and the Second Age of full time employment and parental responsibility. Salford Life Long Learning is a group of approximately 250 people within the U3A who are seeking to swell their numbers so why not join us. They have a range of groups which do different activities including: memories of Salford, discussion groups, bird watching, drama, gardening, family history, french, Mahjongg, music, poetry (Fri afternoon-please call), opera ballet on video, painting, science and maths, scrabble, walks, Eccles local history, A toast to Salford, Spanish, summer schools, no vices bridge, book club (first Wednesday of the month @ Walkden Gateway), quilting, theatre group and keep fit. Monthly general meetings take place at the Eccles Gateway.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482579,-2.338968,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'salford-u3a-salford-life-long-learning',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(335,361,'Willow Tree Centre',NULL,'94 Littleton Road','Salford',NULL,'Greater Manchester','M7 3SE','0161 2125700','willowtree@thebiglifecompany.com','http://www.willowtreehlc.co.uk/','The Willow Tree Centre in Lower Kersal, Salford, provides a range of services to improve and maintain your health and happiness. It\'s also a place for you to come along, meet other people and find out what\'s going on in your local community. Activities and groups include: B fit B Smart – gentle exercises for over 50’s. Energise With Music – music wellbeing drop in group, come & listen or join in. £3 donation. The Salford Community Carers Group - drop in for carers & their families. Legends – Stop Smoking Service Tel: +44 (0)161 2124050. Women of the World – local women’s group meet every Friday, contact Gaynor +44 (0)161 2125700. Skills & Works – Come along & get signed up with Skills & Work to get help with looking for work, training & writing C.V.’s etc',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.502472,-2.277843,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'willow-tree-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(336,362,'Energise Centre',NULL,'3 Douglas Green','Charlestown',NULL,'Salford','M6 6ES','0161 2125700','energise@biglifecentres.com','http://www.energisecentre.co.uk/','The Energise Centre provides a range of services to improve and maintain your health and happiness. It\'s also a place for you to come along, meet other people and find out what\'s going on in your local community. Some of the services we offer are: Rowland\'s Pharmacy, General Practice, Drinks & Chat, Counselling service, Computer training suite, Hair Today Gone Tomorrow, Computerised Cognitive Behavioural Therapy, The Creativity Group - \"Drop in to relax using colouring/drawing, simply arty stuff & you don’t need anything, all materials provided!\" £1 donation requested.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.4975,-2.283695,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'energise-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(337,363,'Age UK Stockport',NULL,'Commonweal','56 Wellington Street',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 3AQ','0161 480 1211','info@ageukstockport.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/stockport/','Our services consist of the Practical and Specific Support service team and the Wayfinder Team. The Practical and Specific Support service team deliver a range of services built around each individual\'s needs. Overview of Practical & Support services: Practical support including Handy Help, shopping and pension collection, and digital support; Social activities - find out about the Pop In Centre, volunteering, and other social opportunities; Support for carers - we offer respite services for carers; Support for health & wellbeing including counselling, a health check service and tai chi classes and support for access to care information and support for those considering care options. The Way finder team is the main entry point to the wide range of support, services and activities. The experienced Wayfinder team will assist each person to find their way to what they need. Costs apply to some of the services and activities that Age UK Stockport delivers. For further information, please contact the Age UK Stockport Wayfinder and Community office.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.408751,-2.157029,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-stockport',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(338,364,'Bramhall U3A','Mike Hollingworth','St Michaels Church Hall','St Michaels Avenue','Bramhall','Stockport','SK7 2PG','0161 4392865','enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk','http://www.bramhallu3a.org.uk/','The aim is to share learning and leisure interests with other retired or semi-retired people in the Bramhall area as well as encouraging social interaction between members. Monthly meeting, usually on the 3rd Thursday of the month, at St. Michael\'s Church Hall with a guest speaker. More than 40 groups taking part in creative activities (e.g. art, card making, choir, embroidery), physical activities (e.g. cycling, Pilates swimming, table tennis, walking), learning activities (e.g. archaeology, languages, science) and other leisure activities (e.g. discussion groups, family history, pub quiz). The U3A also organising day\'s outings and theatre visits plus holidays. How to join - contact the membership secretary by emailing enquiries@bramhallu3a.org.uk or come to one of our monthly meetings. £10 per year per person to join the U3A. There is a charge of £1 to come to the monthly meetings. Some activities take place in the homes of members where there is no charge. There will be a small charge for some activities where a room has to be hired. There are obviously charges for outings, theatre visits and holidays.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.363982,-2.163215,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bramhall-u3a',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(339,365,'Bridgehall Community Centre','Tracey Banham or Kadijatu Mansaray','Siddington Avenue','Bridgehall',NULL,'Stockport','SK3 8NR','0161 4742200','tracy.banham@stockport.gov.uk or kadijatu.mansaray@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.stockport.gov.uk/services/communitypeopleliving/yourcommunity/communityandneighbourhood/communitybuildings/','Activities include: IT Training (Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays and Thursdays), Bridgehall Badminton Club - badminton (Monday PM), Jackie Axon Rythmics - dance exercise for young people (Tuesday PM), Bridgehall Kids Club (Tuesday PM), Parents/Carers Drop In - meeting (Wednesday AM), Community Karate Academy - karate (Thursday PM), Golden Circle Over 60\'s Club (Friday PM), Cook & Taste -food (Wednesday AM), Bridgehall Cookery Class - cooking (Wednesday PM), Remploy (Tuesday and Thursday AM/PM), Line Dancing (Wednesday AM) and Bridgehall Brownies (Wednesday PM). For further information on groups and activities please contact the Community Resource Team on the number provided.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.394261,-2.172504,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bridgehall-community-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(340,366,'Asian Elders Resource Centre',NULL,'61 Northfield Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 5JH','01204 651123','eamil@aercbolton.co.uk','http://www.aercbolton.co.uk/page/737-welcome.aspx','We provide specialised day care and day centre provision for local older Asian people. We provide a wide range of activities, and entertainment, along with useful information. Daily activities and services include: ESOL English classes, ICT with basic English, cookery class, art & craft, massage & holistic therapy, yoga, chair based exercise, swimming sessions, local & abroad trips, advocacy work, home visits (additional support), interpretation and translation service, transport facility, vegetarian and halal meal provision, chiropody service, health checks, information sharing sessions with various topics, eye tests arranged through AERC, indoor games and entertainment. The Service Users Forum, and Asian Carers Forum are our two main groups, developed to empower and support our service users and their carers. To become a member it is £10 per year.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.571009,-2.447911,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'asian-elders-resource-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(341,367,'Bolton Carers Support','','Bolton Carers Centre','Thicketford House','Thicketford Road','Bolton','BL2 2LW','01204 363056','','http://www.boltoncarersupport.org.uk/','<p>Anyone who looks after a family member who is ill, elderly or who has a disability is welcome to contact Bolton Carers Support. We offer a carers helpline, carers newsletter, carers outings, courses and special events. Please contact us for a free Carers Information Pack.</p>\r\n','','','',1,150,1,1,53.58968,-2.405844,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2014-05-30 11:45:55',NULL,NULL,'bolton-carers-support',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(342,368,'Thicketford House Community Care Centre',NULL,'Thicketford Road',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL2 2LW','01204 337537',NULL,'http://www.housingcare.org/service/ser-info-6088-carers-assessme.aspx','The centre is a hive of activity – including entertainment, reminiscence sessions, and an art group, to name a few. People can learn computer skills, including e-mailing relatives abroad. We offer an active carers support group, with a dedicated worker. Carers are much in evidence in the centre, and they are an integral part of our community. Local people over the age of 60 drop in to join in the activities, have a cup of tea, a snack or a hot meal for a small charge. For people who want to sit quietly, we have a sensory garden. Older people who live for a short time at Thicketford often join in the activities that are offered. The centre also accommodates Asian Elders day care. We promote independence in older people whilst having a strong belief in maintaining the rights of the individual. We are located in the heart of the community and are part of older peoples lives in our neighbourhood.',NULL,'boltoncouncil','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bolton-Council/102011083185130',1,150,1,1,53.58968,-2.405844,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'thicketford-house-community-care-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(343,369,'Westhoughton Visiting Service','Jean Jones','Community Learning Centre','Central Drive','Westhoughton','Bolton','BL5 3DS','01942 799374','westhoughtonvisitingservice@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.localdirectory.bolton.gov.uk/ProviderDetails.aspx?ProviderID=842774','Befriending older people, including a sitting-in service for older people with special needs i.e. Dementia. Also offer support for carers and two luncheon clubs Thurstons H.D.U. Bolton, Wigan Road, Westhoughton Mon 12 - 2.30 and Ryelands Court Ryelands, Westhoughton, Bolton, BL5 2PW Thurs 12.00 2.30.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.551492,-2.518905,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'westhoughton-visiting-service',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(344,370,'Winifred Kettle Community Care Centre','Alison  Leaver','Leigh Road','Westhoughton',NULL,'Bolton','BL5 2NE','01942 634566',NULL,'http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/Communityanddaycentres.aspx','We are open 365 days a year from 8.45am to 5.15pm. On Tuesdays and Fridays the centre has a specialised service for people with Dementia, which can accommodate 12 people, whilst on the remaining days of the week we have 25 places offering personal care, respite for carers and social activities. Snacks, a two-course hot meal and transport to and from the centre are available at a nominal charge. A bathing service is also available and a hairdresser visits once a week. Our aims at Daycare are to provide care to meet the physical, psychological, social and spiritual needs of the vulnerable older people within the communities of Westhoughton, Blackrod and Over Hulton and from outside these areas for specialist services. We are committed to providing a quality service and to achieve this we welcome your feedback through group meetings, having a comments book available and by regular individual reviews. Our aim is to maintain the independence of all our service users wherever possible and to work closely with community groups in our area including such as Age Concern, W.A.S.P.S, W.V.S, W.O.A.P.A, Townswomen’s Guild and Rotary Club, who use our facilities for some of their activities.',NULL,'boltoncouncil','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bolton-Council/102011083185130',1,150,1,1,53.541291,-2.516206,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'winifred-kettle-community-care-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(345,371,'Wigan and Leigh Carers Centre',NULL,'3-5 Frederick Street','Hindley',NULL,'Wigan','WN2 3BD','01942 705959',NULL,'http://www.wiganandleighcarerscentre.org.uk','The new Wigan and Leigh Carers Centre opened in June 2010 and is a resource for carers of all ages from across the borough. The role of the Carers Centre is to actively support carers of all ages through the provision of information, training and support. In addition it offers an activity programme tailored to the needs of carers, including: (Free service and carers need to register with us) benefit advice, carers information pack, access to leisure activities, complenmentary therapies and short breaks, access to health checks, training and assisting carers back into education and employment.',NULL,'WiganLeighCarer','https://www.facebook.com/wiganleigh.carerscentre',1,150,1,1,53.534593,-2.581549,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wigan-and-leigh-carers-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(346,372,'Pensioners Link','Anne Deacon','Wigan & Leigh Pensioners Link','Allan Taylor House','27 Charles Street','Leigh','WN7 1DB','01942 261753','anne_counsellor@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.pensionerslink.org.uk','Pensioner Link works with and for the benefit of the over 50’s throughout the borough of Wigan. It currently provides a range of services which support older people and carers of all ages by providing information, advice and signposting on a wide number of issues and works very closely with the Carers Helpline. It hosts Wigan Independent Advice Centre one morning/week for benefits advice, and the Health Trainers use our centre for consultations. We also offer a one-to-one counselling service provided by fully qualified counsellors. Very importantly, Pensioners Link provides a wide range of social activities, which are very well attended by older people and carers. Activities include arts and crafts, exercise and relaxation, holistic therapies, good food club, coffee mornings, tai chi, discussion group, Spanish and IT.',NULL,'penlinkhouse','https://www.facebook.com/leigh.pensionerslink',1,150,1,1,53.497205,-2.513966,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pensioners-link',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(347,373,'Age UK Salford',NULL,'108 Church Street','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0LH','0161 7887300','administrator@ageconcernsalford.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/salford/','Range of services for older people. Information on housing, financial & care issues. Day care with activities, meals, chiropody, bathing & hairdressing. Drop-in centre. Home services: shopping. Advocacy. Hospital aftercare service. Dementia support service for carers of people with dementia. Buddy service for clients with early onset dementia (under 65). Social inclusion & insurance services.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482985,-2.337389,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-salford',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(348,374,'The Princess Royal Trust Salford Carers Centre',NULL,'Angel Healthy Living Centre','1 St. Philips Place',NULL,'Salford','M3 6FA','0161 8330217','carers.centre@salford.gov.uk','http://www.salford.gov.uk/carers.htm','If you look after someone, Salford Carers Centre could help you. If you look after someone who can\'t get by on their own, whether it is your partner, relative, friend or neighbour you\'re considered to be a carer. A carer is someone, of any age, who provides unpaid support to family or friends. This could be caring for a relative, partner or friend who is ill, frail, disabled or has mental health or substance misuse problems. At Salford Carers Centre we can help you access a wide range of services that could help make things easier for you. Carers have different needs and the Centre can assist you with helpful information, practical advice or support in your caring role and concerns such as: health issues, equipment, entitlements, Carers Personal Budgets, or emotional support. Carers may even be juggling paid work with their unpaid caring responsibilities at home. For more information about the advice, information or services we offer please contact the Centre.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.483522,-2.263297,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'the-princess-royal-trust-salford-carers-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(349,375,'Age UK Stockport',NULL,'Commonweal','56 Wellington Street',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 3AQ','016