,53.422318,-2.156517,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'stockport-care-schemes',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(381,407,'Contact the Elderly','Kathleen Sheridan',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Greater Manchester',NULL,'0800 716543 or ','info@contact-the-elderly.org.uk','http://www.contact-the-elderly.org.uk/','Contact the Elderly is the only national charity solely dedicated to tackling loneliness and social isolation among older people. We aim to do this by organising monthly Sunday afternoon tea parties for small groups of older people (aged 75+) who live alone, and volunteers within their local community, offering a regular and vital friendship link every month. Each older person is collected from their home by a volunteer driver and taken to a volunteer host’s home for the afternoon. The group is warmly welcomed by a different host each month, but the drivers remain the same which means that over the months and years, acquaintances turn into friends and loneliness is replaced by companionship. Our tea parties are a real lifeline of friendship for our older members who have little or no contact with any family or friends. They bring people of all ages together, develop fulfilling friendships and support networks, and give everyone involved something to look forward to each month.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.497848,-2.318776,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'contact-the-elderly',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(382,408,'ABLED Project','Jeanette Green','South Reddish Clinic','Reddish Road','South Reddish','Stockport','SK5 7QU','0161 4269111','jeanette.greene@nhs.net',NULL,'ABLED is a NHS Stockport Project set up to help the elderly and disabled people of Stockport. The service offers volunteers to befriend, shop, dog walk or just chat. We rely on volunteers for these services.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.422318,-2.156517,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'abled-project',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(383,409,'Age UK Bolton',NULL,'72/74 Ashburner Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1TN','01204 382411','postmaster@ageukbolton.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/bolton/','Activities and services include Aromatherapy and Reflexology Services - to relieve stress, tension or just to pamper yourself. Café - serving an excellent choice of good quality meals, snacks, drinks in a welcoming and comfortable environment. Community-based Services and Activities - community-based services and activities, including, befriending services; keep fit and other exercise classes; special interest and hobby groups; lunch and leisure clubs etc. to enable and support older people to remain active (physically and mentally) and independent within their own communities. Counselling - confidential counselling services provided by professionally trained and qualified counsellors. Courses and Activities - an attractive and imaginative choice of short courses and activities at our Learning and Resources Centre. Fundraising - help us to raise funds to provide services/activities, with and behalf of older people in Bolton. \"Handyman\" (Practical Support) Service - for good quality, reliable and affordable help with decorating, gardening and small repairs. Information and Advice/Legal Advice Service - free, confidential advice on all issues, including legal matters, affecting older people. Insurance and Other Products - The Age UK Group offers a range of products and services tailor-made for the over 50s. Volunteering Opportunities - find out how you can join our team of first class volunteers. Walking clubs - offering a choice of demanding and less demanding walks. Wheelchair Hire - short-term loans. Will-Making Service - available at a specially negotiated price. ',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.576827,-2.432148,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-bolton',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(384,410,'Bolton Care and Repair',NULL,'154/162 Blackburn Road',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 8DR','01204 335679','boltoncareandrepair@boltonathome.org.uk','http://www.homesforbolton.org.uk/48.html','Bolton Care and Repair aims to help residents, who are older or disabled, with the repair and maintenance of their home. We recognise that more and more people want to remain living in their own home, but occasionally may need a little help to do so. Our case workers will work with customers to find out what services are available to help solve home improvement issues. Our range of services are really quite varied and we signpost to other agencies for support as well. Bolton Care and Repair provides a handyperson service to help with those odd jobs around your home. For example, nailing down loose carpets, fixing gutters, draught proofing windows and doors, fixing a dripping tap or fitting a door chain. We have a handy person who can do all those odd jobs which can be difficult to have done. The core team is available Monday to Friday, 9.00am to 5.00pm. Some of the services are free, while others have a small charge; some of the services are available to any tenure, while others are only available to owner occupiers.',NULL,'boltonathome','https://www.facebook.com/fbboltonathome?ref=ts',1,150,1,1,53.591198,-2.430894,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-care-and-repair',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(385,411,'Community Meals Bolton Council',NULL,'Bolton Council','Town Hall','Victoria Square','Bolton','BL1 1RU','01204 333365','Bolton@Bolton.gov.uk','http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/pages/Mealsonwheelsandluncheonclubs.aspx','Community meals (including meals on wheels) can help people who are finding it difficult to cook for themselves. Having meals delivered to your home may help to keep you independent. Attending a luncheon club gives you the opportunity to socialise and meet with other people outside the home. A variety of nutritionally balanced meals are delivered. The meals can be: hot - delivered by Adult Services staff, between 11.30 am and 1.30pm daily, frozen - delivered by a private Company, weekly, fortnightly or monthly, suit special diets - including diabetic, vegetarian, low salt, low fat and gluten free, fit in with cultural needs - including Asian Vegetarian, Asian Halal, Kosher, Caribbean, West Indian, Middle and Far Eastern and African. There is a small charge for your meal, including sweet. You pay by settling a monthly bill. The current cost of a community meal at home or at a Luncheon Club is: £3.00. The first step is to contact the Older People\'s Helpdesk (using the Contact details tab above) and consider the measures we use to decide if people qualify (eligibility criteria). Not everyone will be entitled to receive meals. You will be asked various questions and if after discussion, you qualify for meals, a member of staff from the community meals team will contact you by phone to discuss the type of meals you require and set the service up.',NULL,'boltoncouncil','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bolton-Council/102011083185130',1,150,1,1,53.578098,-2.430875,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'community-meals-bolton-council',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(386,412,'Home Instead Senior Care Bolton','David Deller','Office 18 112A-116','Hamill House','Chorley New Road','Bolton','BL1 4DH','01204 498949','david.deller@homeinstead.co.uk','http://www.homeinstead.co.uk/bolton','Home Instead Senior Care provides quality care for people in their own homes. Care is personalised for each individual with a broad range of services available to help people remain independent. These range from companionship, accompanying on trips out, home help, intermediate care, personal care, respite care and specialist Dementia and Alzheimer\'s care. Our service is available 24 hours per day.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Home-Instead-Senior-Care-Bolton/171999296171516',1,150,1,1,53.579801,-2.466971,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NU