','stockport@wiltshirefarmfoods.co.uk','http://www.wiltshirefarmfoods.com/','We are a meals delivery service direct to the door, supplying fully nutritional frozen meals to our clients. All meals are made in our own factory in Trowbridge. Lines open: Monday to Thursday 9am to 5pm and Friday 9am to 4.30pm.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.400893,-2.146587,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'wiltshire-farm-food-ltd',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(404,430,'Bolton and District CAB',NULL,'26-28 Mawdsley Street',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1LF','0844 8269707','office@boltoncab.co.uk','http://www.boltoncab.co.uk','Bolton Citizens Advice Bureau we focus on our clients as individuals. We will give you free, confidential, impartial and independent information and advice and work with you to solve your problems. For example, we can help you sort out any debt worries and ensure you claim all the benefits you may be entitled to. We can help with housing and employment problems or deal with queries about consumer or tax issues. We can advise on legal matters, answer questions about immigration and we have lots of experience on family and personal matters too.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bolton-CAB/8649728132',1,150,1,1,53.577387,-2.428228,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-and-district-cab',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(405,431,'Bolton One Stop Shop',NULL,'Bolton Town Hall','Victoria Square',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 1RU','01204 333333','bolton@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.boltonathome.org.uk/website/Pages/Onestopshops.aspx','Provides free advice and surgeries. You can access our services or report an issue at the council\'s one stop shop at Farnworth. The council\'s one stop shop at Bolton town hall can\'t handle enquiries or provide services directly, but it can point you in the right direction. You can also visit our neighbourhood offices or the council\'s access points across the borough.',NULL,'boltonathome','https://www.facebook.com/fbboltonathome?ref=ts',1,150,1,1,53.578098,-2.430875,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-one-stop-shop',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(406,432,'Bolton Shopmobility',NULL,'Car Park Kiosk','Topp Way Car Park','Bath Street','Bolton','BL1 2DJ','01204 392946','shopmobility@comco.org.uk','http://www.comco.org.uk/shopmobility2.html','Provides wheelchairs and scooters to enable access to the shops in Bolton for people with limited mobility.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.582646,-2.431262,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-shopmobility',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(407,433,'Breightmet Ucan Centre','Rosanne Podmore','33 New Lane','Breightmet',NULL,'Bolton','BL2 5BN','01204 333662','rosanne.podmore@bolton.gov.uk','http://www.boltonathome.org.uk/website/pages/UCANcentrecourses.aspx?bid=221','UCAN - Urban Care and Neighbourhood Centre is a place where customers can ask for help and access information and guidance on issues such as employment, training, health and community safety. We offer free IT facilities, volunteering opportunities, free phone facility and links to community groups and local activities. Activities include: computer access, learn direct courses and work club that helps with CV\'s and a Knitt and Natter group.  Please contact the centre as there may be other activities available that are not listed.',NULL,'boltonathome','https://www.facebook.com/fbboltonathome?ref=ts',1,150,1,1,53.590988,-2.395474,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'breightmet-ucan-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(408,434,'Great Lever Ucan Centre','Angela Duffy','98 Calvert Road','Great Lever',NULL,'Bolton','BL3 3BT','01204 654 377','ucan@irwellvalleyha.co.uk','http://www.greatleverucan.co.uk/','UCAN - Urban Care and Neighbourhood Centre is a place where customers can ask for help and access information and guidance on issues such as employment, training, health and community safety. We offer free IT facilities, volunteering opportunities, free phone facility and links to community groups and local activities. Activities include: Card making, Learn Direct courses, computer courses and ESOL classes and a drop in on some Fridays. We also provide housing advice, budgeting advice and floating support services.',NULL,'boltonathome','https://www.facebook.com/fbboltonathome?ref=ts',1,150,1,1,53.561027,-2.431082,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'great-lever-ucan-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(409,435,'Home Instead Senior Care Bolton','David Deller','Office 18 112A-116','Hamill House','Chorley New Road','Bolton','BL1 4DH','01204 498949','david.deller@homeinstead.co.uk','http://www.homeinstead.co.uk/bolton','Home Instead Senior Care provides quality care for people in their own homes. Care is personalised for each individual with a broad range of services available to help people remain independent. These range from companionship, accompanying on trips out, home help, intermediate care, personal care, respite care and specialist Dementia and Alzheimer\'s care. Our service is available 24 hours per day.',NULL,'','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Home-Instead-Senior-Care-Bolton/171999296171516',1,150,1,1,53.579801,-2.466971,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'home-instead-senior-care-bolton',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(410,436,'Older People - Bolton Council',NULL,'Bolton Council','Town Hall','Victoria Square','Bolton','BL1 1RU','01204 338027',NULL,'http://www.bolton.gov.uk/website/OlderPeople/Pages/default.aspx','These pages are a gateway to information for older people living in Bolton, to help you find out more about activities and services including information about care homes, day care, meals on wheels and activities.',NULL,'boltoncouncil','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Bolton-Council/102011083185130',1,150,1,1,53.578098,-2.430875,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'older-people---bolton-council',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(411,437,'Oldhams UCAN Centre','Margaret Miller','92-94 Mackenzie Street','Astley Bridge',NULL,'Bolton','BL1 6QP','01204 332851','margaret.miller@boltonathome.org.uk','http://www.boltonathome.org.uk/website/pages/UCANcentrecourses.aspx?bid=221','UCAN - Urban Care and Neighbourhood Centre is a place where customers can ask for help and access information and guidance on issues such as employment, training, health and community safety. We offer free IT facilities, volunteering opportunities, free phone facility and links to community groups and local activities. Activities include: Rite Weight - healthy eating with a view to loosing pounds..., IT and photography - learn basic IT skills – how to use a computer – get on line, Next Steps - advice on job seeking and any training needs, Keyboard skills - learning the QWERTY keyboard skills – touch typing, healthy walks - get fit and healthy and meet new friends, Adult literacy - helping people with basic English and writing skills, Arts and crafts - knitting, card making and other art work, and a Work club - CV building, Job search, interview techniques. Please contact the centre as there may be other activities available that are not listed.',NULL,'boltonathome','https://www.facebook.com/fbboltonathome?ref=ts',1,150,1,1,53.603473,-2.440905,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'oldhams-ucan-centre',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(412,438,'Age UK Wigan',NULL,'68 Market Street',NULL,NULL,'Wigan','WN1 1HX','01942 241972','enquiries@ageukwiganborough.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/wiganborough/','At the heart of the work of Age UK Wigan Borough are the services provided for older people across the Borough. These are locally determined, as a response to identified needs and the availability of appropriate resources. Services include advocacy - providing information to allow people to make informed choices and decisions. Bright Days Programme - offering a wide range of activities to encourage you to feel good and have fun. Care Homes Admission Service - help, advice and support for you and your family when choosing a care home. Direct Payments - Age UK Wigan Borough has been funded to help people in use of Direct Payments. Handyperson service - helping you maintain independence and improve safety and security in the home. Hospital Information & Support Service - short term support for older people who are admitted to the Royal Albert Edward Infirmary, Wigan. Information & advice - available to people aged 50 and over, their relatives, friends and carers in the Borough of Wigan. Paveways Plus - Information and advice service for people with a disability and their carers. Products and  services - A range of products and services tailor-made for the over 50s. Starting Point - a telephone helpline offering information and support to people aged 50 and over and  Support at Home Services - offering practical and emotional support in order for older people to retain their independence and volunteering - volunteers undertake a wide range of activities in our offices and in the community.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.548295,-2.633729,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-wigan',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(413,439,'Starting Point Telephone Helpline – Age UK Wigan',NULL,'Age UK','Pennyhurst Mill','Haig Street','Wigan','WN3 4AZ','01942 826079','john.mcardle@acwiganborough.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/wiganborough/Our-services/Starting-Point-telephone-helpline/','Starting Point service has been contracted through Wigan Council since April 2005. The purpose of the service is to provide a telephone helpline for people who are no longer eligible for help from Wigan Council. This service provides information and advice on how to access reputable Domiciliary Care Agencies to help with everyday needs such as shopping, cleaning, ironing and low level personal care. In addition, if any other needs are identified by the Liaison Officer these will be discussed with you, and with your permission, you will be signposted to the appropriate service. If necessary a home visit can be arranged from our Liaison Service to further discuss your needs in the comfort of your own home. We aim to ensure that your requests are responded to within ten working days and aim to provide services within 28 days. Starting Point can also put you in touch with a number of local reputable companies and people who offer services at a reasonable charge: cleaning services, shopping services, foot and nail care, handymen, lunch clubs, companies that provide or prepare meals, joiners, plumbers, electricians, plasterers, tilers, painters and decorators, gardeners, benefit information and advice, laundry services - washing and ironing, hairdressers, dog walking, befriending, personal care, home security, and many others… If you would prefer, someone from Starting Point can visit you at home to discuss your needs in more detail.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.542466,-2.641195,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'starting-point-telephone-helpline-–-age-uk-wigan',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(414,440,'Pensioners Link','Anne Deacon','Wigan & Leigh Pensioners Link','Allan Taylor House','27 Charles Street','Leigh','WN7 1DB','01942 261753','anne_counsellor@yahoo.co.uk','http://www.pensionerslink.org.uk','Pensioner Link works with and for the benefit of the over 50’s throughout the borough of Wigan. It currently provides a range of services which support older people and carers of all ages by providing information, advice and signposting on a wide number of issues and works very closely with the Carers Helpline. It hosts Wigan Independent Advice Centre one morning/week for benefits advice, and the Health Trainers use our centre for consultations. We also offer a one-to-one counselling service provided by fully qualified counsellors. Very importantly, Pensioners Link provides a wide range of social activities, which are very well attended by older people and carers. Activities include arts and crafts, exercise and relaxation, holistic therapies, good food club, coffee mornings, tai chi, discussion group, Spanish and IT.',NULL,'penlinkhouse','https://www.facebook.com/leigh.pensionerslink',1,150,1,1,53.497205,-2.513966,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'pensioners-link',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(415,441,'Shevington Library','Bill Gaskell','Gathurst Lane','Shevington',NULL,'Wigan','WN6 8HA','01257 252618','shevington.library@wlct.org','http://www.wlct.org/library-services/library-locations/shevington-library.htm','Tuesdays - Bookchat – adult reading group (last Tuesday in month 2-3pm). 2nd and 4th Tuesday in mon - Councillor 5.45-6.45pm. Wednesdays - One Stop Shop - Police, councillor, Resident and Tenants Association 1.30-3.30pm.',NULL,'WLCT','https://www.facebook.com/WLCTrust',1,150,1,1,53.566516,-2.695558,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'shevington-library',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(416,442,'Age UK Salford',NULL,'108 Church Street','Eccles',NULL,'Salford','M30 0LH','0161 7887300','administrator@ageconcernsalford.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/salford/','Range of services for older people. Information on housing, financial & care issues. Day care with activities, meals, chiropody, bathing & hairdressing. Drop-in centre. Home services: shopping. Advocacy. Hospital aftercare service. Dementia support service for carers of people with dementia. Buddy service for clients with early onset dementia (under 65). Social inclusion & insurance services.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.482985,-2.337389,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-salford',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(417,443,'Salford One Stop Shop (SHOP)',NULL,'Salford Opportunities Centre','2 Paddington Close','Salford',NULL,'M6 5PL','0161 793 2020 o