g including counselling, a health check service and tai chi classes and support for access to care information and support for those considering care options. The Way finder team is the main entry point to the wide range of support, services and activities. The experienced Wayfinder team will assist each person to find their way to what they need. Costs apply to some of the services and activities that Age UK Stockport delivers. For further information, please contact the Age UK Stockport Wayfinder and Community office.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.408751,-2.157029,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-stockport',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(420,446,'My Care, My Choice',NULL,'Information & Publicity (Adult Social Care)','Stopford House (4th Floor)','Piccadilly','Stockport','SK1 3XE','0161 217 6029','adult.social.care@stockport.gov.uk','http://www.mycaremychoice.org.uk/','My Care, My Choice is Stockport Council\'s dedicated website which provides information and advice about what adult social care services are available and how to receive them. The \'My Care, My Choice\' website is designed to help people find the information they need as quickly and easily as possible. It also features: a self assessment tool to enable you to determine how much help they (or their friend, neighbour or relative) might need, a calculator that lets you work out how much certain services might cost you and a facility to search for a residential or nursing home in a particular area and for a particular condition.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.407968,-2.15829,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'my-care,-my-choice',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(421,447,'FLAG','Pam Coombs, Wayne Morrison, Margaret Newton or Rosie Deveral','Graylaw House','Chestergate',NULL,'Stockport','SK1 1LZ','0161 3741042','info@stockportflag.org.uk','http://www.stockportflag.org.uk/','FLAG is an independent service that puts people in need of practical or emotional help and guidance in touch with those local organisations best able to provide it. We are your link to the health and social care services provided by a consortium of independent voluntary organisations in the area, as well as the services provided by Stockport Council. Whatever you are concerned about talk to FLAG first. If help exists locally, we will find it for you. Our service is free, informed and confidential. We make it easy for you to talk to us, in confidence, about the help and support you need. You can visit the FLAG town centre office, talk to one of the four FLAG advisors working in the community, or call the FLAG helpline. Once we fully understand the help you need we will point you in the right direction.',NULL,'StockportMBC','https://www.facebook.com/StockportMBC',1,150,1,1,53.409873,-2.160111,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'flag',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(422,448,'Bolton Community Transport',NULL,'Unit 4 Lecturers Close',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 6DG','01204 393777','bctfs@btconnect.com','http://www.bctfs.co.uk/','Provides transports for people who find it hard to use public transport services. Transport is available for individuals and groups who live in the Borough of Bolton. They have 4 fully accessible minibuses which offer a door to door service and take passengers on outings, excursions, holidays, shopping trips and many other  destinations. Offices open Monday to Friday 9.00am - 5.00pm. Cost varies.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,150,1,1,53.57171,-2.431239,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-community-transport',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(423,449,'Bolton Ring and Ride',NULL,'Unit 8 Summerfield Road',NULL,NULL,'Bolton','BL3 2NQ','01204 388500','bolton@ringandride.info','http://www.tfgm.com/ringandride/Pages/Depot-Bolton.aspx','Provides accessible transports for people who find it hard to use public transport services. They provide a door to door service and can be booked for short local journeys to access shops, social or leisure activities, work, further education and attend health appointments or places of worship. They also organise day trips and evenings out for members. Open Monday - Saturday 8am - 10.45pm. Sunday 8.15am - 10.10pm. Cost varies.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.564186,-2.414151,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'bolton-ring-and-ride',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(424,450,'Local Link Bolton',NULL,'2 Piccadilly Place','Manchester',NULL,'Manchester','M1 3BG','01204 364566',NULL,'http://www.tfgm.com/buses/local_link/Pages/default.aspx','Local Link is a door-to-door flexible transport service that will pick you up and take you where you want to go. The services can be used by anyone and are available in defined areas. You must book your journey at least one hour in advance, but you can book all your journeys at the same time, up to a week ahead. Local Link uses minibuses or taxis that you share with other passengers. For further information please take a look at the website provided.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.478372,-2.23295,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'local-link-bolton',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(425,451,'Travel Vouchers',NULL,'Passes and Permits','Transport for Greater Manchester','2 Piccadilly Place','Manchester','M1 3BG','0161 2441050',NULL,'http://www.tfgm.com/journey_planning/Tickets/Pages/tickets_travel_vouchers.aspx','Travel vouchers are for people who are not able to use ordinary buses, trains or Metrolink and who have serious walking difficulties or are registered blind. They can be used to pay for taxis and for travel on accessible bus services such as Ring and Ride and community transport.',NULL,'OfficialTfGM','',1,150,1,1,53.478372,-2.23295,'eng','2013-05-20 12:00:00','2013-05-20 12:00:00',NULL,NULL,'travel-vouchers',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:01'),(426,452,'Travel Vouchers',NUL