p>Morning coffee, lunch and bingo in the afternoon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have occasional outings and entertainment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All are welcome so do come along and join us.</p>\r\n','Thurs: 10.30-3pm','','',60,150,1,1,50.7576386,-1.28747720000001,'eng','2014-08-10 15:20:47','2014-09-04 17:01:12',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-iw-1',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:02'),(631,657,'Age UK IW Active Network Club','Alan Wiles','Gobells Close Sheltered Housing','','','Ryde','PO33 2HJ','01983 525282 ','info@ageukiw.org.uk','http://www.ageuk.org.uk/isleofwight/our-services/active-networks/','<p>~~Active networks aims to overcome loneliness and isolation in older people by enabling them to rebuild their confidence, maintain their health and wellbeing and independence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>~~Age UK Isle of Wight offer groups of older people the opportunity to take part in social and physical activity within and outside of the clubs. We can also assist you with transport should this be required.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>~~Cost</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Social club members pay a small amount for entry and raffle tickets. Those requiring transport also pay a nominal charge towards costs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What to do next?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact us on 01983 525282 or email us if you are interested in Active Networks of support.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alan Wiles, the ANS Development Officer will be pleased to discuss the opportunities within networks or issue an invitation to one of our social clubs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Snapshot</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Several people have commented on meeting old friends, or making new ones. Many have said how much they look forward to the clubs for company and the chance to get out of their homes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Active Network Clubs differ from others in existence by ensuring that people are not excluded. They are helped to attend through the provision of transport from home, to the club and back home again.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Each club has between 15 and 30 regular attendees, all over 60, with many in their 80s and 90s.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Activities include scrabble, dominoes, cards, quizzes and occassional speakers. Each club arranges a number of outings in the year which are very popular.</p>\r\n','On the 2nd and 4th Thursday of the month 2.00 â€“ 3.45 pm','','',60,150,1,1,50.7284755,-1.1542680999999702,'eng','2014-08-10 16:42:19','2014-09-04 17:00:34',NULL,NULL,'age-uk-iw-active-network-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:02'),(632,658,'Alzheimer\'s Cafe','Paulette Thompson','All Saints Church, Church Hall','Queens Road','','Ryde','PO33 3BG','01983 220200','','http://www.alzheimercafeiow.org.uk/showsite/2','<p>For people living with dementia, their families and friends, carers and those with an interest in dementia.</p>\r\n','1st Friday monthly 11.30-2pm (except January)','','',1,150,1,1,50.727324,-1.16922210000007,'eng','2014-08-10 16:51:27','2014-09-04 16:59:20',NULL,NULL,'alzheimer-s-caf-3',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:02'),(633,659,'American Square Dancing','Mr Dunningon ','Parish Church Hall','Queens Road','','Ryde','PO33 3BG','01983 565718 ','','','','Tuesdays 7.30 pmâ€“ 9.30 pm','','',1,150,1,1,50.727324,-1.16922210000007,'eng','2014-08-10 16:55:40','2014-09-04 16:58:23',NULL,NULL,'american-square-dancing-1',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:02'),(634,660,'Appley Women\'s Institute','','The Park Centre','','','Ryde','PO33 1BP','01983 884128','','','','2nd Thurs of the month 7.30-9.30pm','','',1,150,0,1,50.7224868,-1.14815659999999,'eng','2014-08-10 17:00:55','2014-09-04 16:58:01',NULL,NULL,'appley-women-s-institute',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:02'),(635,661,'Chatters Cafe','Lilian Burden','Ryde Baptist Church','The George Street Centre','George Street','Ryde','PO33 2JF','01983 812774','George@rydebaptist.org','http://www.rydebaptist.org/chatterscafe.htm','<p>~~ the NHS wrote this about Chatters Caf&eacute;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Lilian Burden, manager of Chatters caf&eacute; which is based in the George Street Centre, Ryde and her team provide an excellent service within the local community. The centre is open 6 days a week and provides hot drinks, snacks and lunches for a number of groups in the community who use the centre including mother and toddler, Friend to Friend for older people, bridge, and scrabble clubs and painting classes as well as mothers using the Sure Start centre located at the rear of the George Street Centre. It alsocustomers being served on the patio caters for those working in the neighbourhood in Ryde, it is an oasis of calm from work pressures in the middle of the day. The food is freshly-prepared, wholesome and attractively priced. A number of homeless people use the centre as it is so reasonably priced and sometimes those in desperate need are fed for free.&nbsp; Many of the users of the caf&eacute; are elderly and attend regularly making the caf&eacute; an important part of the community and of people&rsquo;s social life.&nbsp; The centre is staffed by mostly volunteers from the community including a number with learning difficulties for whom the work is an important part of their involvement in society and gives them a real sense of purpose.&nbsp; All in all the caf&eacute; provides a very much needed service for the caf&eacute; users and staff and is worthy of this award.&quot;</p>\r\n','Mon-Thurs and Sat mornings 10-12','','',1,150,1,1,50.729454,-1.16150489999995,'eng','2014-08-10 22:07:48','2014-09-04 16:57:39',NULL,NULL,'chatters-caf',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:02'),(636,662,'Bembridge Heritage Society','','Bembridge Village Hall','High Street','','Bembridge','PO35','01983 873606','enquiries@bembridgeheritage.org.uk','http://www.bembridgeheritage.org.uk/','<p>Activities include visits and walks. Wheelechair access available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Bembridge Heritage Society on the Isle of Wight was formed in 1996 to record and present the rich history and heritage of Bembridge and its surrounding areas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Centre was once part of the Village School and is located at the rear of what is now the library in the old part of the village. Displays cover much of Bembridge&rsquo;s early history, not only in photographs, paintings, maps and written descriptions but also through the many artifacts and medals that have been donated to the Society.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Information can be found not only about the village itself but of wider industrial and archaeological interest within the Parish such as Bembridge Fort.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Society has grown steadily since the mid 1990&rsquo;s and is a popular part of Village life with meetings throughout the autumn, winter and spring and members providing enthusiastic and knowledgeable support as volunteers to man the Centre through the summer. Visits to other attractions and heritage walks are often undertaken by members.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All visitors are very welcome to attend our meetings which are held in the Village Hall. Events are advertised on local notice boards, in magazines and the IW County Press.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Society produces its own publications and these are available for sale through the Centre and local outlets.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is a small annual membership fee and this entitles free entry to the Centre and reduced or free entry to the meetings.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Admission &pound;1.</p>\r\n','Last Thursday of every month, 7:00-7:30pm','','',1,150,1,1,50.6793881,-1.10002529999997,'eng','2014-08-10 22:27:40','2014-09-04 16:57:04',NULL,NULL,'bembridge-heritage-society',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:02'),(637,663,'Bembridge Wheelers','Tim Thorne','Meet at Holy Trinity Church','Church Road','','Bembridge','PO35 5NA','01983 872953','','http://www.cyclewight.org.uk/bembridge-wheelers.html','<p>~~This group continues to go from strength to strength. They meet regularly on a Thursday and do &lsquo;easy rides&rsquo; on the Island and