ridge Club','Ingrid Gaches','The Ryde Club','5 Spencer Road','','Ryde','PO33 2NY','01983 562486','therydeclub@uwclub.net','http://www.bridgewebs.com/therydeclub/','<p>Welcome to the Ryde &nbsp;Club on the Isle of Wight.&nbsp; We have our own premises and are&nbsp;located in Spencer Road, a short walk from the pier.&nbsp; Duplicate Bridge is played three times a week and we use the BridgeMate/ScoreBridge system.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The club also offers a snooker room with two well looked after full size snooker tables</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Visitors are very welcome at all times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tuesday evening starting at 1845</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wednesday evening starting&nbsp;at 1845</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saturday evening starting at 1845</p>\r\n','Mon, Tues, Wed, Fri and Sat','','',1,150,1,1,50.7311054,-1.16480520000005,'eng','2014-08-11 17:34:15','2014-09-04 14:22:38',NULL,NULL,'bridge-club-2',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:02'),(695,721,'Scrabble Club','Ian Caws','The Community Centre','George Street','','Ryde','PO33 2JF','01983 565484','iancaws@msn.com','http://newportiwsc.org.uk/iwscrab.html','<p>The Island&#39;s Scrabble Clubs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Island possesses two Scrabble Clubs, now known as Newport (Isle of Wight) Scrabble Club, and Ryde (Isle of Wight) Scrabble Club. As will be seen from the history, both Clubs, in their present form, sprang, originally, from the same source. Large numbers of players attend both Clubs, and both Clubs have had to find solutions to the same sorts of problems when deciding on their playing formats, so it should not be surprising that both are very similar. Both meet at 7.15pm for a 7.30pm start, the Ryde Club on a Monday evening, and the Newport Club on a Tuesday. Both play three games of Scrabble until 10pm. Both contain two main groups; an &quot;A&quot; group, playing &quot;Matchplay&quot; Scrabble using tournament rules taken from the ABSP, and a &quot;B&quot; group playing less competitive Scrabble for beginners, or simply for the more socially-minded.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Teams from both clubs take part in the Southern Counties&rsquo; League.</p>\r\n','every Monday evening, at 7.15pm ready for a 7.30 start','','',1,150,1,1,50.729454,-1.16150489999995,'eng','2014-08-11 17:36:20','2014-09-04 14:16:59',NULL,NULL,'scrabble-club',NULL,NULL,'2015-03-05 16:03:02'),(696,722,'Bembridge Afternoon TownsWomen  Guild','Mrs H Ransome','Bembridge Village Hall','High Street','','Bembridge','PO35 5XN','01983 874241','','','<p>The Isle of Wight Federation meets bi-monthly on the 4th Monday 10.15am at the Broadway Centre, Sandown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Federation, as well as supporting the eleven Island Guilds, hosts annually an Arts &amp; Crafts Exhibition, an inter-guild Quiz, both a Luncheon and a Christmas Concert. The Federation organises many enjoyable holidays and outings for both members, friends and husbands, and there is always a waiting list as these are so popular.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The fastest growing guild on the Island, Lake Morning, has decided to continue not only with their personal recruitment events but to raise awareness of TG in general at several of the annual Island shows again this year.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>ISLE OF WIGHT GUILDS</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Bembridge Afternoon 1st Tues. - 2.15pm - Village Hall, Bembridge</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bembridge Vectis 3rd Thurs. - 2.15pm - Village Hall, Bembridge</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bembridge Evening 1st Tues. - 7.30pm - Methodist Church Hall, Bembridge</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Cowes Afternoon 2nd Mon. - 2.30pm - St. Mary&#39;s Church Hall, Cowes</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Lake Morning 2nd Thurs. - 10.30am - Lions Community Centre, Lake</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Newport Afternoon 1st Mon. - 2pm - Newport Parish Hall, Newport</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rydewight Evening 1st Mon - 7pm - Ryde Baptist Church</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sandown Afternoon 3rd Wed. - 2pm - Broadway Centre, Sandown</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sandown Evening 2nd Thurs. - 7.15pm - St. Johns Annexe, Sandown</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shanklin Afternoon 3rd Mon - 2.15pm - Methodist Church