Ryde Library','','101 George Street ','','','Ryde','PO33 2JE','01983 562170','','http://www.iwight.com/Council/OtherServices/Ryde-Library/Introduction-to-Ryde-Library','<p><strong>Various activities: </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The library provides a safe and welcoming space in the heart of Ryde.&nbsp; As well as providing the usual library facilities we also host Ryde Help Centre, and have regular Citizens Advice sessions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The library is&nbsp;in the process of recruiting people for a new Friends&#39;&nbsp;Group which will help raise money for the library as well as helping us to provide regular events of all kinds.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please have a look at our other web pages for more information about what we do. We look forward to seeing you soon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Service Description:</strong>&nbsp;Children&#39;s and adults&#39; books, large print books, talking books on CD, DVDs, compact discs, reference collection, newspapers, photocopying, fax service, free internet access, free computer access. Ryde Library also has a gallery space for art exhibitions, and holds weekly Rhymetimes.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRyde Library is also the home of the Ryde Help Centre</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Services available at this library:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Books</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>DVDs*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>CDs*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Energy Saving Monitors&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Talking Books on Cassette/CD*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Large Print&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Computer facilities&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Free Internet access</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Free online language courses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Over 500 free online courses</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>e-magazines</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Free access to Find My Past&nbsp; family history website</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Online reference resources</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Word processing&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Scanning facilities&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Printing*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Colour/B&amp;W photocopying service*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fax service*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reference Collection&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Local Studies Collection&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Newspapers&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Garden Refuse Sacks*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bus Pass Applications&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Teenage Area&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Children&rsquo;s Area&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Rhyme Time</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Story Time</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Gallery</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Help Centre</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Regular Events</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&#39;Knit and Natter&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This new group will meet once every 4 weeks at Ryde Library from 5.30pm to 7pm on a Wednesday evening.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bring your knitting - we&#39;ll provide the refreshments - and make new friends.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suitable for all ages and abilities, this group is free of charge and there&#39;s no need to book. Please note that this is not a tuition group.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"line-height:1.6em\">Free Health Walks and Book Talks</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Join us on the last Friday of the month for a walk from Ryde Library&nbsp;followed by a book chat and refreshments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This event is free but numbers are limited, so please call in to the library or phone us using the number on the contact tab above to book a place.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reading Groups</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Reading groups meet once a month. Please ask at the&nbsp;help desk&nbsp;or call us using the number on the contact tab above for further details.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Poetry Group</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ryde Library&rsquo;s poetry group is held on the first Monday of the month from 5pm &ndash; 6pm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you would like to join the group, please contact the library using the number on the contact tab above, or pop in to leave your details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Museum Display</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Come and study the case of artefacts and visual display, which has been provided by the Island Museum Service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Find my Past</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ryde Library has free access to ancestry website, &lsquo;Find My Past&rsquo;. Search for your ancestors in census records and use parish records to find births, marriages and deaths dating back to 1538!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPop in to the library for more information or give us a ring.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Gallery space</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Gallery on the library&#39;s upper floor is free to book for your art or photography exhibition. Please ask in the library for details of available dates, and for booking conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you enjoy art, come and look at a selection of paintings or photographs displayed each month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Book Sale</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our recently expanded section of withdrawn library books and other stock (CDs, DVD&rsquo;s, talking books) for sale are to be found towards the centre of the adult lending library, and feature in the library on a permanent basis.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Teen Book Group</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ryde Library has started a new monthly book group for 13-17 year olds.&nbsp; There&#39;s no fee, and you don&#39;t even need to be a library member!&nbsp; 2nd Tuesday of every month, 3.30pm - 4.30pm.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact Diane at Ryde library for more details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LEGO Club</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LEGO Club takes place on the 2nd and 4th Tuesday of each month,&nbsp;for&nbsp;children aged 5+.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The club&nbsp;runs 3.30pm - 4.30pm in the children&#39;s library. There will be free refreshments available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&#39;s totally free of charge, and you don&#39;t need to book a place. Come along for as long as you like!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Koko the Library Bear</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Are you going on holiday? Whether you&rsquo;re camping in Devon, or backpacking in Australia, Koko the bear would love to go with you!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTake Koko on your holiday and bring him back to the library along with a photo and some information about your trip. It&rsquo;s a great chance to get your child talking about what they&rsquo;ve seen, and what books they enjoyed while they were away.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIn&nbsp;the children&rsquo;s library we have a folder with all of Koko&rsquo;s adventures inside, and he is ready to go on holiday again!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSpeak to a member of staff if you would like to book a date to take Koko away with you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rhyme time for under 5s</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rhyme time is an informal session of rhymes and songs for babies and toddlers, using bells and rattles, and making lots of noise!<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe &lsquo;Rhyme Time&rsquo; session, which takes place every Monday (except bank holidays), runs from 10am &ndash; 11am.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFrom 10am &ndash; 10.30am, parents are able to arrive and settle their children, whilst catching up with other parents and children alike (there will be toys and books to play with). The rhymes then begin at 10.30am for half an hour, run by a member of staff, ending the session at 11am.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe session takes place in the children&rsquo;s library and there are lovely toys, rattles and puppets for the children to enjoy. There&rsquo;s no need to book; just come along and join in! Children should be supervised by an adult at all times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Children&#39;s Storytime</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A regular half-hour storytime for younger children, (ideally between 3 &ndash; 8 years) from 11am - 11.30am every Saturday.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt&rsquo;s free to come along, and you don&rsquo;t need to book in advance. Children should be supervised by an adult at all times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Become a Storytime Superstar with our reward system! Every time you come to Storytime, receive a star on the chart. When you&#39;ve collected 4 stars, you can take home a free weekly children&#39;s DVD rental!</p>\r\n','Opening Times: Monday 9.00am - 5.30pm, Tuesday 9.00am - 5.30pm, Wednesday 10.30am - 7.00pm, Thursday CLOSED, Friday 9.00am - 5.30pm, Saturday 9.00am - 5.00pm, Sunday CLOSED','','',1,150,1,1,50.7281859,-1.1614849999999701,'eng','2014-08-11 11:07:17','2015-10-28 09:33:19',NULL,0,'ryde-library','2,3,4,5,13,14,25',NULL,'2015-10-28 09:33:19'),(750,779,'Knit & Natter','Ryde Library','','101 George Street','','Ryde','PO33 2JE','','','','<p><strong>Wed 28 Oct 2015 5:30 PM 7 PM</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ryde Library</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Come along to Knit and Natter! Suitable for all ages and abilities, this group takes place once a month on a Wednesday evening. This event is free and refreshments are provided. Please note, this is not a tuition group - bring your knitting and chat with others!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Indoors or Outdoors:&nbsp;</strong>Indoors</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Event Type:&nbsp;</strong>Miscellaneous</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intended Audience:&nbsp;</strong>All</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Disabled Facilities:&nbsp;</strong>Toilets, Wheelchair Access</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Charges:&nbsp;</strong>Free of Charge</p>\r\n','Weds 5.30 - 7pm','','',0,100,1,1,50.7281859,-1.1614849999999706,'eng','2015-10-28 15:40:32','2015-10-28 15:40:32',NULL,0,'knit-natter','3',NULL,'2015-10-28 15:40:32'),(751,496,'Knit and Natter Group ','','Lord Louis Library','Orchard St, ','','Newport','PO30 1LL','527655','','','','First Weds 2pm-3.30pm & third Thursday 5.45-7pm','','',1,150,1,1,50.6978201,-1.29365089999999,'eng','2014-07-10 14:15:36','2015-10-28 15:44:53',NULL,0,'knit-and-natter-group','3',NULL,'2015-10-28 15:44:53'),(752,779,'Knit & Natter','Ryde Library','','101 George Street','','Ryde','PO33 2JE','','','','<p><strong>Wed &nbsp;5:00 PM 7 PM (Every four weeks - pick up dates in the library)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ryde Library</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Come along to Knit and Natter! Suitable for all ages and abilities, this group takes place once a month on a Wednesday evening. This event is free and refreshments are provided. Please note, this is not a tuition group - bring your knitting and chat with others!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Indoors or Outdoors:&nbsp;</strong>Indoors</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&